title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Crumble flour, butter and brown sugar; mix in wheat germ, oats, spices and pecans to form the topping. Peel and slice apples and spread into a greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle topping over all.
Bake 45 minutes or until brown.
Serve warm.

title: marj's quick crab appetizer
directions: Put cream cheese in the middle of a serving plate and make a well with the back of a spoon.
Dump the crabmeat on top of and around sides of cream cheese.
Cover with seafood cocktail sauce. Arrange cracker around the outside of the cheese and crab mixture on the serving plate.
Pepperidge Farms English water crackers are particularly good with this.

title: macho nacho
directions: Heat chili.
Spoon over chips.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Heat until cheese melts, 1 to 2 minutes, and serve.

title: pinto beans with sage-garlic
directions: In a large nonstick skillet, heat oil over medium heat. Then add garlic, peppers and bay leaf and saut until peppers are tender; do not brown garlic.
Add beans, sage and hot pepper sauce and saut until heated through.
Remove bay leaf and serve hot as an appetizer or side dish with garlic bread or warm, soft corn tortillas.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: cold vegetable dish
directions: Mix ingredients the day before you are ready to serve.
Serve cold.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: bacon wrap chicken cutlets
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.

title: chicken cutlets with peppers and mushrooms
directions: Place each piece of chicken between 2 sheets of heavy-duty plastic wrap; flatten to 1/4 inch thickness, using a meat mallet or rolling pin. Place breadcrumbs in shallow dish; dredge chicken in breadcrumbs.

title: party potatoes
directions: Whip potatoes. Add cream cheese, sour cream, butter, salt and pepper. Top with grated cheese, bacon and onion tops.

title: blueberry cream cheese squares
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar, water and blueberries.
Cook while stirring over medium heat until sauce bubbles and thickens.
Cool. Combine cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Press half of crumb mixture into bottom of foil-lined 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mash cream cheese until soft.
Gradually beat in sugar and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread 1/2 of cream mixture carefully over the crumb layer.
Then spread cooled blueberry filling evenly over cheese layer.
Spread remaining cheese mixture over blueberry layer.
Top with remaining cracker crumb mixture.
Chill overnight.
Using foil to remove from pan, place dessert on a platter and cut into squares.
Makes 15 servings.

title: another basic vinaigrette
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender.
Store in refrigerator.

title: red devil's food cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until fluffy.
Add salt and vanilla.
Combine cocoa and 1/3 cup water; add to mixture.
Add flour to mixture with water.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 3/4 cup sugar.
Fold egg whites into batter.
Combine soda and 1/3 cup cold water; add to mixture.
Put in 3 greased pans and cook in 350° oven.
Ice with your favorite icing.

title: stewed okra
directions: Melt butter in a 2-quart pot.
Add onion and stir 5 minutes or until onion is clear.
Stir in tomatoes and garlic; simmer for 5 minutes.
Add okra, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Stir until well blended.
Cook on low heat for 25 to 30 minutes or until okra is tender.

title: rice pudding
directions: Wash rice; mix 4 ingredients together in saucepan.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer until thick and creamy, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and cool.

title: cranberry loaf cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix Bisquick, sugar, butter, eggs and milk (half at a time) and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add cranberries and nuts last.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Chill 7-Up and pineapple juice.
Pour into punch bowl.
Then add sherbet.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Grease and flour a tube or Bundt pan.
Place wafers in blender or food processor and crumble.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time and cream after each.
Add crumbs alternately with milk and blend.
Add coconut and pecans.
Place in 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheese soup
directions: Combine water and bouillon; add veggies and simmer until tender.
If you use fresh veggies, add broccoli and cauliflower towards the end as they cook faster and will get mushy if cooked too long.
Drain off liquid.
Add milk, cheese and margarine.
Heat until cheese melts; do not boil.
Add more veggies if you like to make it more like a stew.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Bake yellow cake mix in a 13 x 9-inch pan (according to package directions) and let cool.
In saucepan, cook water and cornstarch until clear; let cool.
Add powdered sugar, margarine and vanilla.
Whip until fluffy.
Cut cake into 2 layers with piece of thread.
Spread filling between layers.

title: sour cream noodles
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a casserole.
Put butter on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: gertie's sausage cheese balls
directions: Cook sausage; drain thoroughly.
In a double boiler or microwave melt cheese; cool slightly.
Stir in crumbled sausage and Bisquick.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes until brown.
Or, freeze balls before baking, then bake as needed.
Yield:

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all veggies.
Blend sour cream, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing.
Pour over veggies and refrigerate.

title: creamy mints
directions: Combine ingredients, cream well with hands until smooth.
Make small balls, dip top of balls with granulated sugar.
Press design in candy mold.
Pop out.
Makes 85 pieces.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Cut up chicken strips and fry in a small amount of oil.
Add onions, mixed vegetables, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes or until vegetables are barely tender, stirring occasionally so it won't stick.
Add soup and cook until steaming hot.
Serve over rice.

title: chocolate butterscotch cereal bars
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup in large saucepan. Bring just to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter. Stir in cereal. Press into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Microwave chocolate and butterscotch morsels in medium, microwave-safe bowl on High power for 1 minute. Stir. Microwave at additional 10 to 20 second intervals, stirring until smooth. Spread over cereal mixture. Chill in pan for 20 minutes or until firm. Cut into bars. Makes 4 dozen bars.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and eggs.
Rinse.
Dice potatoes, eggs, celery, green pepper and onion.
Mix in Miracle Whip, 1/2 cup relish, salt and pepper.

title: sweetheart salad
directions: Mix cream cheese with diced cherries and cherry juice.
Cream until smooth.
Dissolve gelatin in 1/3 cup warm water and make sure to stir as you mix to prevent lumps.
Have pineapple and sugar heating on stove.
When hot, pour gelatin into pineapple.
Cook until almost boiling.

title: sugarless banana bread
directions: Blend all ingredients in order listed.
Bake in two greased 5 x 9 loaf pans in 350° oven for 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: german chili
directions: Brown ground beef; drain grease.
Boil potatoes and onion until tender; drain liquid.
Combine all ingredients and simmer 1 to 2 hours or until ready to serve.

title: jogging in a jug
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Put in container and refrigerate. Drink 1/4 cup each day.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook all ingredients except berries and whipped cream until thick, then pour cut up berries into mixture.
Put in icebox and chill.
Cover with whipped cream.

title: michael's scrambled eggs
directions: Beat eggs with a fork in a bowl and add dollop of milk.
Mix well.
Heat skillet and add pat of butter.
After butter is melted, pour eggs into skillet, stirring while cooking.
When eggs are done, slide onto plate and top with picante sauce.

title: stewed prunes and raisins
directions: Place the prunes
and
raisins
in
a
pot.
Cover with water; bring to a boil
and
cook
over a low fire for 30 minutes.
Add the sugar
and lemon wedges.
Cook another 15 to 20 minutes. Serve hot or cold.
Serves 3 to 5.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix and dissolve.
Slice onions to suit yourself.
Slice cucumbers and pack in 1 gallon jar.
Heat vinegar solution to boiling point and pour over cucumbers and onions.
Refrigerate 24 hours before using.
Will keep 1 year.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: spice cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth.
Pour into pan and bake at 350° until done.
Let cool and put apple butter on it for topping.

title: scalloped asparagus with artichokes
directions: Layer vegetables in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Melt butter; blend in flour slowly.
Add milk and artichoke juice, stirring to make cream sauce. Add salt, pepper, Accent and half of the cheese. Pour over vegetables.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: elma's bahamian bread
directions: Mix yeast, water and 2 Tbsp sugar and let sit for 10 minutes. Add rest of sugar, margarine, salt and 3 c. of flour and beat with mixer for 2 minutes.
Add enough flour to make workable dough. Knead for 8 minutes.
Let rise until doubled.

title: deluxe pecan pie
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Remove from heat and mix in sugar and corn syrup.
Blend in eggs and vanilla extract.
Add pecans and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: baked spinach
directions: Melt butter and add cream cheese. Fold in spinach and onion soup mix. Place in an 8 x 8 baking dish. Top with bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cooked through.

title: unbaked cookies(chocolate - peanut butter)
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in pan.
Heat and cook until it starts to boil.
Boil approximately 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Cool for 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.

title: quickie chili
directions: Brown ground meat and onion. Add chili mix, water, puree, beans and salt.
Cook 15 minutes.

title: cheese and sausage grits casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Cook grits in salted water for 5 minutes.
When grits are the consistency of oatmeal, stir in cheese.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand for a few minutes. Stir in butter, eggs, milk and garlic until well blended.
Stir in sausage.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Wonderful for breakfast, lunch or supper!

title: taco salad
directions: Break up lettuce in large salad bowl.
Add chopped peppers. Cook ground beef in skillet; remove excess grease and add taco seasoning mix.
Let cool, then add to lettuce and peppers.
Toss. Crumble bag of Doritos and add to mixture.
Add bag of shredded cheese.
Pour bottle of dressing over mixture.
Toss.
May serve sour cream and taco sauce on the side.

title: mike's lasagna
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Combine with all other ingredients, except noodles and the 2 cheeses.
Bring to boil; simmer, stirring occasionally.

title: banana split cake
directions: Break up angel food cake in 1 1/2-inch pieces and place in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Slice bananas over cake.
Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water; mix with strawberries and pour over bananas.
Set in refrigerator for 1/2 hour.
Mix pudding and pour over strawberries.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: where's the fat chocolate sauce
directions: Stir together sugar, cocoa and cornstarch.
Add milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla. Serve warm or cool.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt, and spices in a small bowl. Beat eggs in a large bowl, stir in pumpkin and sugar and spices. Gradually stir in milk. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 425 degrees for 15 minutes then reduce temperature to 350 degrees and bake 40 minutes longer.

title: crab meat pizza
directions: Add salt, curry powder, onion, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce to cream cheese and mix well.
Spread on 10-inch plate and top with 1/2 bottle chili sauce.
Sprinkle drained crab meat evenly over all.
Top with fresh parsley.
Serve with crackers (Town House/Ritz).

title: ready rye appetizers
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Spread about 1 tablespoon on each rye cracker.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 7 minutes or until bubbly or 45 seconds in a microwave.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: vegetable au gratin
directions: Cook vegetables and drain well.
Press water out with paper towels. Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Sprinkle crushed Ritz crackers on top. Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6 deliciously.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix stale bread and crab meat together.
Blend remaining ingredients together and then fold into the crab mixture.
Make patties or cakes.
Deep fry until golden brown at 375°.

title: lobster au gratin
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into a buttered casserole. Sprinkle with ground bread crumbs and dot with butter. Bake in a hot oven, 400°, for 15 to 30 minutes.

title: pecan fruit cake
directions: Cream the butter and brown sugar.
Cream well.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift 2 cups of flour with baking powder.
Add alternately with vanilla to creamed mixture.
(This may be done in mixer.)
Use remaining 2 cups of flour to dredge nuts and fruits.
Add to first mixture, stirring with a spoon.
Beat egg whites stiff and fold into mixture.
Let stand overnight at room temperature.
Next day, pour into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 225° for 3 hours and 15 minutes.
Turn upside down to cool.
Keeps well in tin or freezes well.

title: excellent pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine and sift all dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients and sour cream to creamed mixture.
Add flavoring to mixture.

title: one-crust turkey or chicken pie
directions: Heat 1/3 c. margarine in 2-quart saucepan over low heat, stir in 1/2 cup biscuit mix, onion, pepper and thyme.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until bubbles.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chicken broth and milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly; boil and stir for 1 minute.
Stir in chicken and frozen vegetables; heat through.
Keep warm.

title: easy mix cookie bars
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl in order listed.
Add boiling water last and mix well.
Spread on greased cookie sheet and bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Frost with your favorite frosting and cut in squares.

title: ham it up crescent snacks
directions: Separate dough into 4 rectangles.
Lay ham, spread mustard and sprinkle cheese.
Roll and seal edges. Roll in sesame seed.
Cut into 5 slices (may need to secure with toothpicks).
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute sliced zucchini in butter and garlic powder.
Layer zucchini, onion, tomato and cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: In large skillet, brown chicken in oil.
Add peppers.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes.
In small bowl, mix soy sauce and cornstarch.
Add soy sauce mixture, pineapple with juice, vinegar, brown sugar, ginger and garlic powder to skillet.
Bring to boil.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Serve chicken mixture over rice.

title: aunt erna's vegetable casserole
directions: Put vegetables and cheese in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine crackers and melted margarine.
Spread on top of vegetables.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: mad hatter's apple torte
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Bake pecan halves until fragrant, about 5 minutes.
Set 8 pecans aside.

title: best peanut butter fudge
directions: Grease a 9 X 13 inch baking dish, set aside. In a saucepan, combine sugar, milk and butter. Bring to a boil, and cook 5 minutes. Remove from the heat. Stir in the marshmallow creme and peanut butter. Gradually stir in the flour. Spread into the prepared pan, and let cool.

title: super wonderful spinach salad dressing
directions: Mix well.
Pour into jar and refrigerate.
It keeps for months.
Pour over 2 bunches, fresh, washed torn spinach.
Top with 2 sliced hard-cooked eggs and bacon bits, crumbled.

title: chop and kraut casserole
directions: Sprinkle salt and pepper on the loin pork chops.
Place chops on the bottom of the casserole dish.
Pour sauerkraut over the chops.
Place the sliced potatoes on top of the sauerkraut.
Cover the dish and bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: brunch quiche
directions: Freeze enough bread to cover the bottom of a large cake pan, then cube it.
Mix bread and meat.
Spread over bottom of pan. Sprinkle cheese over this.
Mix eggs, milk, 1/2 teaspoon dry milk and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Pour over it.
Drizzle the butter.
Cover and let set overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
This feeds a crowd.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Cream the butter, peanut butter and sugars.
Add egg and vanilla. Stir together flour, baking soda and salt.
Blend into creamed mixture to make dough.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and place into ungreased mini muffin pans (tassi pans).
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Immediately after removing cookies from oven, press peanut butter cup into center until only top of cup shows.
Cool and store in airtight container. Makes 48 cookies.

title: beef tips dish
directions: Mix together.
Put in casserole dish with lid.
Cook 4 hours at 250°.
Serve on top of rice.

title: salmon appetizers
directions: Drain salmon in small bowl, then combine all ingredients. Spread mixture over each of the tortillas.
Roll each one up tightly and wrap individually with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Slice into bite size pieces.
Makes about 48 appetizers.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Can add seedless grapes, halved, about 1 cup, if desired.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain, set aside.
Combine mushroom soup, onion, milk, black pepper and green peppers together.
Place over low heat.
Add cheese and stir until cheese is melted.
Mix macaroni and tuna fish in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Blend in cheese sauce and bake in oven 20 minutes at 325°.
Serves six.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt chocolate with paraffin in double boiler.
Mix all other ingredients and roll into small balls.
Roll balls in chocolate with a spoon and put on waxed paper to dry.
(Chill dough for a little while before dipping.)

title: stewart's beef burgundy
directions: Cook bacon in a large skillet.
Remove and drain and add beef cubes and brown well in bacon grease.
Remove beef and put in crock-pot or large pot.
Brown carrots and sliced onion.
Season with salt and pepper.
Stir in flour; add broth and mix well.
Add to pot.
Put in remaining ingredients and bring to a boil, then simmer over low heat for 3 hours or on low in crock-pot for 8 hours.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix and pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: mint-chip ice cream
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over boiling water, stirring to dissolve. Add peppermint flavoring and salt; stir well.
Let mixture cool. Combine topping mix, cold water and vanilla in bowl and whip mixture until stiff.
Fold in peppermint mixture and chocolate chips.
Pour into freezer tray and freeze until firm.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: peppery mini-bites
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Spray 10-inch nonstick skillet with nonstick cooking spray.
Cook bell peppers and onions in skillet. Beat eggs and egg whites slightly.
Stir in bell pepper mixture and remaining ingredients.
Spray muffin cup pan with
nonstick cooking spray.
Spoon 1 tablespoon mixture into each muffin cups. Bake 8 to 10 minutes until centers are set.
Let cool 1 minute. Loosen edges with knife and remove from pan.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend all ingredients together with a mixer.
Form into a ball and chill; serve with crackers.

title: easy chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onion in butter until clear.
Add chicken, soup and Ro-Tel; simmer 15 minutes.
Crumble tortilla chips and place in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour chicken mixture on top.
Cover with cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: stroganoff pork chops
directions: Combine flour, seasoned salt and paprika.
Coat pork chops. Brown chops in a lightly greased skillet; drain.
Combine gravy mix and water as called for on package.
Pour over chops.
Add onions.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Uncover and simmer 15 minutes longer.
Remove pork chops to serving platter.
Add mushrooms and sour cream to gravy.
Combine thoroughly.
Heat through; pour over chops.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: glitter paint
directions: Mix ingredients well and dispense through squeeze-top bottles.

title: angel-pineapple cake
directions: Make angel food cake according to directions.
Whip cream and mix with drained pineapple and instant pudding.
Slice the cake in half and make a tunnel in the middle.
Fill the tunnel with mixture and spread remaining mixture covering entire cake. Garnish top with orange slices.
Delicious and easy.

title: easy pasta alfredo
directions: In Dutch oven, toss hot noodles, cheese, salad dressing and parsley.
Warm noodle mixture over medium heat until cheese melts. Sprinkle individual servings with additional cheese and black pepper.
Makes 4 servings.

title: canned green beans
directions: Open can of cut green beans.
Place in boiler pot (3-quart size).
Add about 3 inch square salt pork or piece of ham.
Add about a can of water.
Cook about 1 hour.
When ready to serve, add about 1/2 cup milk and let come to boil, then remove immediately, otherwise the milk will curdle.
Serve with corn bread.
If no meat, then add about 2 tablespoons butter.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Cook the celery and onions in butter.
Blend in flour.
Butter toast and cut into 1/2-inch squares.
Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Bake for 30 minutes and top with buttered bread.
Bake 20 minutes longer.

title: manicotti and meat balls
directions: Cook lasagna noodles by package directions; each stick makes two.
Cut in half.

title: grandma's fat pancakes
directions: Dissolve the sugar and salt in water, then add the yeast and let stand until it dissolves and bubbles, then add the shortening and the egg.
Mix well.
Add flour and dry milk.
Beat well until thoroughly mixed.
Let stand covered until mixture doubles in size.
Fry slowly over medium heat, one spoonful at a time, until golden brown.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apple bread
directions: Stir together apples, nuts and sugar.
Let stand, stirring often until juicy, about 1 hour.
Stir together flour, soda, salt and spices.
Add apple mixture and stir well.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Add eggs.
Turn into 2 loaf pans that have been well-greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes or until test is done.
Cool on pan 10 minutes and turn out onto rack.

title: grandma's sugar cream pie(1937 recipe)
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and salt well.
Add milk, vanilla and cinnamon.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour into an 8 or 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake 35 minutes.

title: lunch box pizzas
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Flatten each biscuit into a 3-inch circle and press into a greased muffin cup.
Combine tomato sauce and Italian seasoning; spoon 1 teaspoon into each cup.
Top each with 1 pepperoni slice and 1 tablespoon cheese.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve immediately or store in refrigerator.
Makes 10 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; fold in Stove Top mix.
Pour into 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.
Do not overcook.
tags: Stove Top stuffing with seasoning mix

title: ribbon fudge
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups sugar, 6 tablespoons margarine and 1/3 cup milk in heavy saucepan.
Bring to a full boil, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Boil for 4 minutes; remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate pieces until melted.
Add 1 cup marshmallow cream and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Repeat, using rest of ingredients and using peanut butter for chocolate pieces.
Spread over chocolate layer.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares.
Makes about 3 pounds.

title: sloppy jo turnovers
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Add salt, garlic powder, catsup and sour cream.
Mix.
Separate dough. Press each biscuit to a 4 x 4-inch square.
Put 1/4 cup mixture on
center of each square and fold over to make triangle and seal edges with fork.
Cut 3 slits on top and bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: layer salad
directions: Layer all ingredients (except last 3) in an oblong pan and frost with mayonnaise mixed with sugar.
Top with shredded cheese. Vary ingredients.
Superb for taking to parties!

title: paia mango bread
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar gradually and beat until fluffy. Add eggs one at a time and beat well.
Add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and mix into egg mixture alternately with the mango. Add nuts.
Bake in 5 medium pans for 40 to 45 minutes or in 4 large loaf pans for about an hour at 350°.

title: old-time pancakes
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and sugar.
In a deep medium size bowl, beat egg until thickened and lemon color; add buttermilk and butter and beat to blend.
Add flour mixture; stir only until it is moistened.
Drop batter, by scant 1/4 cupfuls, onto a lightly greased electric griddle heated to 375°.
Bake until bubbles break on top and bottoms are brown; turn and brown top sides.
Serve hot with butter and syrup.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Put together in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Brush on chicken every time you turn it.
Makes enough sauce to grill 10 chickens.

title: stuffed acorn squash
directions: Cut squash in half.
Bake upside down with 1/4 cup of water in pan for 15 to 20 minutes.
Scoop out centers.
Saute onion in margarine.
Mix all ingredients and place in squash shells.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Place eggs in cold water.
Add salt; bring to full boil.
Turn burner to simmer for 30 minutes.
Place cooked eggs in cold water and crack eggs.
Shell eggs.
Cut in half.
Put egg whites aside. Put egg yolks in small bowl and smash with fork.
Add pepper, mustard and salad dressing.
Cream eggs by hand.
Fill egg whites with yolk mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: grated broccoli with parmesan
directions: Peel and grate broccoli stems.
Shred the cheese.
Heat oil in a large frying pan over medium heat.
Add grated broccoli stems and 3/4 teaspoon salt.
Toss to coat.
Cover, reduce heat and cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, about 10 to 15 minutes. Stir in red pepper flakes and cook 1 minute.
Stir in Parmesan cheese and serve.

title: strawberry cake dessert
directions: Cut cake into squares and layer in pan.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Mix in strawberries and Cool Whip.
Beat with beater until pink.
Pour over cake pieces and mix.
Refrigerate until solid.

title: parsley sauce(for baked ham)
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender.
Pour over baked ham (already baked).
Let stand 15 minutes before carving.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix everything but ginger ale with mixer until smooth.
Freeze in containers.
When ready to use, place partially thawed mixture in punch bowl.
Add ginger ale.

title: turtle cake
directions: In double boiler, melt caramels, milk and butter.
Set aside. Mix cake as directed on pkg.
Pour 1/2 of batter in 9 x 13 greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.

title: black walnut pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and butter.
Add eggs and walnuts.
Fill unbaked pie shell with mixture and bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: grilled flank steak
directions: Sprinkle steak lightly on both sides with garlic powder. Combine soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce and oil.
Prick both sides of meat and marinate and cover 8 hours or overnight. Grill over medium coals; slice across grain.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Coat a medium-size nonstick skillet with Pam.
Dissolve bouillon in boiling water.
Add to sauteed vegetables.
Stir in remaining seasonings and bring to a boil.
Add cooked rice to skillet, stirring well.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes and serve.

title: savory crescent chicken squares
directions: Mix the
ingredients
together except crescent rolls, 1 tablespoon melted
margarine
and
crushed croutons.
Separate rolls into 4 triangles.
Seal the perforations.
Spoon 1/2 cup of the chicken mixture
onto
the
center
of	each rectangle. Pull the 4 corners of the
dough to the center of the mixture. Seal and brush the
tops
with
1 tablespoon melted margarine. Sprinkle the tops with crushed croutons.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.

title: ann's texas cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients together at the same time and it is best mixed by hand.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and butter in a heavy saucepan. Bring ingredients to a rolling boil.
Let boil 1 minute.
Remove pan from heat.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Add oatmeal and peanut butter.
Stir rapidly.
Using tablespoon, drop cookies onto wax paper and let cool.
Yields approximately 24 cookies.

title: baked fish
directions: Spray baking dish with Pam or lightly grease with oil.
Place fish in dish.
Alternate slices of tomato and onion on fish at a slant.
Pour Italian dressing over fish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until fish is lightly flaky.

title: squash muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Mix squash, milk and oil and combine with dry mixture.
Bake in a 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Bake pie shell and let cool.
Melt Hershey bar or bars in a double boiler.
Mix in Cool Whip as soon as chocolate is melted. Mix well and spoon into cool pie shell.
Refrigerate for 3 or 4 hours before eating.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook Rice-A-Roni as directed on box; add mashed up tomatoes. Cook and brown hamburger and onion.
Mash up as it cooks.
Add salt and pepper.
Put hamburger mix in rice and add cheese to thicken.

title: pasta salad
directions: Saute oleo and seasoning package together.
Boil pasta and drain.
Add shrimp, pasta and seasoning.
Sprinkle with garlic powder and Parmesan.

title: cocoa crunch bars
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan; remove from heat and blend in cocoa.
Add brown sugar, corn syrup or honey, vanilla and salt; blend well.
Combine oats and nuts in large mixing bowl.
Pour chocolate mixture over dry ingredients.
Stir to blend well.
Line a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan with aluminum foil. Generously grease foil.
Press mixture into pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool; peel off foil.
Cut into bars.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes about 3 dozen bars.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients
except
stuffing
mix
and
butter. Pour in greased casserole dish.
Top
with stuffing mix and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until browned.

title: chicken a l'orange
directions: Sprinkle chicken pieces with salt, pepper and paprika.
Roll pieces in flour.
Line a shallow casserole with foil.
Put chicken in lined pan.
Sprinkle onion, green pepper and mushrooms over chicken.
In saucepan, mix orange juice, sherry, brown sugar and salt.
Add water and cornstarch.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in 1 1/2 quart casserole and put in oven.
Bake at 375° about 1 hour or until set and lightly browned.

title: hot cocoa
directions: Bring cocoa, sugar and water to a boil. Add milk and heat. (Don't boil the milk.)
Makes 8 servings.

title: citric acid punch
directions: Dissolve citric acid in boiling water.
This must be prepared in an enamel or heatproof glass container as it will taste bitter if prepared in a metal container.
Dissolve sugar in cold water. Add frozen orange juice and pineapple juice to the citric acid and sugar solution.
You may freeze or serve over attractive ice ring. Serves 75.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.

title: lima beans and sausage
directions: Brown sausage.
Cook green onions with garlic in butter in a large saucepan until tender.
Blend in soup, water, bay leaf, cayenne and lima beans; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and cook over low heat for 15 minutes.
Add tomatoes and cook 5 minutes longer or until done, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaf.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add soy sauce and 1 cup water.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Add celery and onion.
Blend in water and cornstarch mixture into pan.
Add water chestnuts, sprouts and mushrooms. Heat thoroughly and season with salt and pepper.
Put in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream sugar, oleo, oil and egg yolks, one at a time, mixing well.
Combine milk, soda and add flour alternately to sugar and oil.
Beat egg whites stiff; add, mixing well.
Add vanilla, nuts and coconut.
Bake in 325° oven for 40 minutes in 3 (9-inch) cake pans.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Mix flour and butter together.
Press down into long Pyrex dish, then pat pecans down into mixture.
Bake at 350° until brown (12 to 14 minutes).
Make up Dream Whip as directions on box.
Mix confectioners sugar and cream cheese together, then fold into Dream Whip.
Add this mixture over crust.
Top with cherry pie filling and chill.
Cut into squares.
This should make about 10 to 12 servings.

title: barbecued frankfurters
directions: Cook onions in hot fat until tender.
Combine remaining ingredients (except frankfurters).
Add to onions.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Prick frankfurters.
Add to sauce.
Cover. Simmer 15 minutes.

title: baked lemon pepper chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken and any excess fat.
Liberally sprinkle lemon-pepper over each piece.
Wrap individually in aluminum foil.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
This is lo-fat, lo-calorie.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli per package directions.
Drain broccoli. Blend together soup and flour; add sour cream, carrots, onion, salt and pepper.
Stir in broccoli.
Turn into 2-quart baking dish.
Combine together stuffing mix and melted butter.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: orange punch
directions: Prepare Kool-Aid as directed.
Mix in ginger ale.
Stir in the sherbet just before serving.

title: broccoli-cheese-rice casserole
directions: Put broccoli in a micro-dish and put in microwave on defrost for 5 minutes. Then add rice and soup. Put back in for 5 minutes on High. Then put cheese in and stir. Put back in for 5 to 6 minutes. Stir and serve.

title: rice krispies bars
directions: Bring sugar and cornstarch to boil.
Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon of vanilla and peanut butter. Mix well and add the Rice Krispies.
Mix well and pat into a buttered pan.
Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips, spreading on top.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: pancakes by jake
directions: Stir until moistened, all lumps do not have to be gone.
Cook in lightly greased skillet.

title: egg casserole
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Layer: bread, butter (pats), sprinkle of ham or sausage and grated cheese.
Repeat.
Mix milk and eggs well.
Pour over layers.
Let set overnight or several hours in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Servings: 6.

title: muffins basic and variations
directions: Grease 12 (2 1/2-inch) muffin cups.
Heat oven to 400°.
Sift flour, baking powder, sugar and salt into a medium-sized bowl. Stir to mix well.
In a small bowl beat egg with a fork.
Add milk and oil.
Add all at once to dry ingredients.
Stir mixture only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Batter will be lumpy.
Drop batter from a tablespoon into prepared muffin pans, filling each cup half to two-thirds full.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from pan and serve hot with butter, jam or marmalade.

title: tortilla stack-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly butter two 8-inch round layer cake pans, pie pans, souffle dishes or casseroles.
Place 1 tortilla in each pan.
Combine cheeses in bowl.
Sprinkle 2/3 cup combined cheeses over each tortilla.
Top with generous tablespoon each of green onion and chilies.
Top with another tortilla. Repeat until there are 4 layers in each pan.
Top with fifth tortilla.
Brush tops with melted butter.
(The stacks can be prepared several days in advance or even a day ahead, refrigerated, and then baked just before serving.)
Bake stacks, uncovered, in preheated hot ovens (400°) for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted and tops are lightly browned.
Let cool 5 minutes.
Invert serving platter over cake pan, then carefully flip and turn stack-up out onto platter.
Repeat with second pan.
Cut each stack into 16 wedges.
Garnish each platter with salsa and fresh chilies and sour cream if you wish.
Makes 16 appetizers.

title: baked ham
directions: Heat soup, vinegar, water, mustard, sugar, and cloves in large saucepan.
Heat to a low boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Thicken with corn starch to desired consistency.
Add ham and simmer for 30 minutes.
Can be transfer to a slow cooker to cook on low all day.
Place ham slices on your favorite bread or bun.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix the oleo, white sugar, cocoa and milk together.
Boil for 1 minute.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoons on wax paper.

title: chicken casserole
directions: This recipe is easily halved.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix oil, eggs and sugar together.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla; mix well.	Fold in apples.
Add pecans.
Makes 2 loaves baked at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or 21 muffins (fill muffin tins 2/3 full and bake at 325° for 20 minutes).
Both loaves and muffins freeze well.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Wash and skin breasts; salt and pepper to taste.
Place in baking dish.
Pour soups over breasts.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Peel fresh shrimp.
Make light incision along outer back and remove black vein.
Wash; place in colander and season generously with salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Melt oleo.
Add onions, celery and bell pepper, if desired, and parsley.
Wilt.

Add tomato sauce and cook slowly in uncovered heavy iron pot about 45 minutes. Dissolve cornstarch in the cup of water and add to mixture. Simmer another 5 minutes, then add seasoned shrimp and green onions and cook until shrimp are done, usually about 20 to 30 minutes.
Salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and especially Tabasco are used generously in this dish.

(If a little more sauce is desired, an additional teaspoon of cornstarch in 1/2 cup of water may be added, but remember that as the shrimp begin to cook, they will create quite a bit of liquid themselves.)
Serve over mounds of steamed white long grain rice.
Serves 6.

title: christmas bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add flour, eggs, salt, chocolate, vanilla and nuts and mix.
Spread dough into 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Mix 10x sugar, butter and creme de menthe.
Spread over cooled cake.
Chill. Melt remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Let cool slightly and spread over second layer.
Chill and cut into squares.

title: lime pickles
directions: Place cucumbers in 2 gallons water and lime.
Let set for 24 hours. Drain and rinse off cover.
Cover with cold water and let stand 3 hours.
Cover with vinegar and spices and let stand over night.
Heat cucumbers, vinegar and spices to boiling.
Simmer for 35 minutes.
Place in clean jars and seal.

title: 2 minute supper in throop
directions: Put 2 hot dogs, beans and frozen French fries on a paper plate; stick it in a microwave oven.
Cook 2 minutes.
Wa la!
Eat well.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: Cook and stir ground beef, onion and celery until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water; stir bouillon and remaining ingredients into meat mixture in a large pot.
Cover and bake at 350° about 1 hour and 15 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Crumble bacon and sprinkle over beans. Serves a lot!!

title: granola-breakfast cereal
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients as you would pie crust. Toast in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown. Stir often so it doesn't get lumpy.
Add chocolate chips or raisins after slightly cooled.

title: garden cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well. Chill. Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Heat corn and milk.
Add egg.
Stir, then add cracker crumbs, onion and salt.
Pour into greased 8-inch baking dish.
Top with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat egg whites; add sugar;
beat egg yolks until light in color and fluffy.
Fold egg
yolks	into egg white mixture. Fold in bourbon.
Beat whipping	cream; fold into egg mixture. Serve immediately with nutmeg on top of each glass.

title: cheddar baked potato slices
directions: Using small bowl, combine soup, paprika and pepper.
Grease a 2-quart oblong baking dish, arranging potatoes in overlapping rows.
Sprinkle cheese and then spoon soup mixture over cheese. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: mars krispies
directions: Melt margarine and Mars bars until creamy.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Put into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cool before cutting.

title: baked egg mornay
directions: Slice
eggs
in half lengthwise, scoop out yolks.
Mash well. Add Miracle Whip, horseradish and pickle juice.
Return yolks
to egg
halves.
Place
deviled
eggs in buttered 13 x 9-inch casserole.	Blend 5 tablespoons butter in saucepan over low
heat. Blend
in	flour, stir in milk slowly.
Cook until thickened. Add salt, pepper, cream, Parmesan and Swiss cheese and 2 1/2 tablespoons butter.
Stir until cheese melts.
Pour over deviled eggs.
Top	with
buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat and put in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle with onion flakes or powder.
Place layer of cheese over meat, then layer of Tater Tots.
Mix soup and milk; pour over Tater Tots.
Bake.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook hamburger until brown, stirring to crumble.
Drain off grease.
Lightly grease 8-inch square pan.
Spoon meat into pan. Top with pizza sauce and add cheese.
Combine Bisquick, milk and eggs, beating until smooth.
Pour mixture over casserole.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: easy tropical punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: taco-mac
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package; drain and rinse with cold water.
Brown meat and drain off fat.
Add taco seasoning and mix well.
Let cool.

title: christmas salad
directions: Melt candy in 1 cup boiling water over low heat.
Add jello and dissolve.
Add applesauce.
Pour half in rectangular pan; chill until "wiggly."
In separate container, combine remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls and spread on set jello.
Cover with remaining jello to make 3 layers.
Refrigerate until set.

title: pie crust
directions: Beat eggs and put in cup with vinegar.
Add enough water to make 1 cup.
Mix all ingredients together.
Roll as usual.

title: very good cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar, then blend in remaining ingredients.
Bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cream of celery soup
directions: Chop celery and onion through blender; melt bouillon cubes in hot celery juice.
Make white sauce with butter, flour and milk and mix with celery; serve with crackers.
(Also good with casseroles.)

title: simmered chinese chicken
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven or large skillet with lid. Brown chicken on all sides; remove fat from pan.
(I use a "turkey baster.")
In a medium bowl, mix together the soy sauce, brown sugar, catsup, sherry or apple juice, red pepper flakes, garlic and green onion.
Pour mixture over chicken in Dutch oven.
Cover tightly and simmer 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove chicken to platter. Keep warm in 250° oven.

title: coconut pecan pie
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour 1/2 of the cheese mixture into each pie shell. Drizzle 1/4 of the caramel sauce on each.
Sprinkle 1/4 of coconut mixture on each.
Repeat the layers.
Freeze 5 to 6 hours.
Thaw 10 minutes before serving.

title: salsa chili with beans
directions: Gently saute hamburger; drain.
Pour chili beans with juice into 4-quart cooker.
Chop onion and tomato.
Add to beans.
Add chili sauce to pot.
Chop whole chilies.
Add to mixture.
Add seasonings and salt to taste.
After chili has simmered 1 hour, cook, covered, to retain flavor.

title: moist 'n creamy coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed, baking in 13 x 9 inch pan. Cool 15 minutes then poke holes in cake with utility fork. Meanwhile, combine milk, sugar and 1/2 c. coconut in saucepan. Bring to a boil and reduce heat, and simmer for one minute. Carefully spoon over warm cake, allowing liquid to seep down through holes. Cool completely. Fold 1/2 c. coconut into whipped topping and spread over cake. Sprinkle with remaining coconut. Chill overnight. Store leftover in refrigerator.

title: quick dessert
directions: Slice angel food cake in 3 layers. Spread with Cool Whip and strawberries between layers.

title: mary's chili pork roast
directions: Brown roast on all sides in frypan. Place meat in 2-quart covered pan. Add rest of ingredients. Place in 325° oven for 2 1/2 to 3 hours. Remove. Slice and serve with rice and refried beans and tortillas. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: lake charles dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and use with fresh vegetables.

title: chicken alfredo with asparagus
directions: Cook chicken breast and cut into pieces. Add to alfredo sauce. Add garlic. Boil asparagus in separate pot and cook about 15 to 20 minutes. Cut asparagus into 1/2-inch pieces and add to sauce. Add mushrooms (optional). Let simmer for about 15 to 20 minutes. Pour over angel hair pasta.

title: sugar biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients and drop on cookie sheet. Bake in oven at 475°.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine crumbs, Parmesan cheese and seasonings.
Dip chicken in butter (or milk), then coat with crumb mixture.
Sprinkle with lemon.
Refrigerate 1/2 hour.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
(If boneless, bakes in 20 to 30 minutes.)

title: stuffed double burgers
directions: Combine beef, Worcestershire sauce and salt; mix lightly. Shape into 12 patties.
Top 6 patties with cheese and pickle slices.
Place remaining patties over filling; seal edges.
Place on rack over hot charcoal.
Grill 5 minutes on each side.
Yields 6 burgers.

title: peanut butter coffee cake wreath
directions: Heat sour cream over low heat until lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Beat in sour cream, sugar, salt, margarine, egg and 1 1/2 cups flour until smooth.
Stir in enough remaining flour to form a soft dough.
Turn onto well floured surface; knead until smooth, 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl; turn greased side up.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double, 1 hour.
Prepare filling.
Punch down dough.
Roll into rectangle, 25 x 6-inches.
Make 1 1/2-inch cuts on 25-inch sides at 1/2 inch intervals.
Spread Peanut Butter Filling down center. Crisscross strips over filling.
Shape into ring on greased cookie sheet.
Pinch ends together.
Cover and let rise until almost double, 1 hour.
Heat oven to 375°.
Bake until golden brown, 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool slightly; top with Cocoa Glaze.
Makes 1 coffee cake.

title: nine layer baked chicken
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with bread.
Layer other ingredients as written.
Cover with foil and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Last 15 minutes, cover with buttered crumbs made from crusts of bread.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli as package directs; drain.
Add margarine and onion and simmer a few minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes or until done.
Top with grated cheese.

title: scalloped oysters supreme
directions: Combine crumbs and melted butter.

Put layer of crumbs in bottom of baking dish, then put a layer of oysters and seasoning. Alternate crumbs and oysters until there are two layers of each. Pour can of mushroom soup over and top with crumbs and drained button mushrooms.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: mama's cranberry salad
directions: Grind strawberries and orange.
Mix this with sugar.
Let stand for one hour, then add nuts, apple and celery.
Mix jello with 1 cup water.
Bring to boil to dissolve jello and add 1 1/2 cups cold water, then add to other ingredients and congeal.
This is a family favorite at Christmas dinner.

title: coconut crowned caramel delights
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Combine pie crust mix, brown sugar, and baking soda in bowl of food processor (or use electric mixer). Pulse 2 or 3 times just to mix. Add eggs and process until mixture begins to form a ball. Drop by heaping teaspoonsful onto ungreased cookie sheet, spacing cookies about 2 inches apart. Bake for about 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from cookie sheet onto rack to cool. Melt the chocolate and when the cookies are completely cooled, brush the bottom of each with a thin layer of chocolate.
Place with chocolate side up until cooled.
If using the German chocolate, you might want to place the cookies in the freezer for a few minutes after the chocolate has been brushed on. The coating chocolate will harden much quicker.
Combine the caramels and water in a microwavable bowl and microwave for 1 minute and stir. Then microwave for about 15 seconds and stir, continuing until caramels are melted.
Spread caramel mixture over tops of the cookies and then press into toasted coconut. Allow caramel mixture to firm up before serving.

title: apple salad
directions: Peel apples before chopping.
Dissolve gelatin in hot water. Add cinnamon candies to boiling water.
Stir until dissolved. Add to gelatin.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Add apples, celery and walnuts.
Chill until firm.

title: individual pizzas
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place hamburger in skillet.
Stir hamburger with fork to break up large pieces.
Cook on medium heat until hamburger is browned; drain.
Add tomato sauce, oregano, salt and garlic salt.
Pat out each biscuit on cookie sheet to form pizza crust.
Spread each biscuit with hamburger mixture. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Yields 10 servings.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add sauces to beef.
Simmer 1 hour. Add 1 tomato paste can of water.
Add sour cream and green onions. Set aside.
Cook and drain 8 ounce package noodles.
Layer noodles, sour cream and meat sauce in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Heat olive oil in pot until hot.
Brown ground beef.
Add seasonings and cook about 10 minutes.
Add Ro-Tel and cook five minutes.
Add boiled eggplant and about 1 1/2 cups of water.
Cook on low fire for about 1 hour.

title: martha pafford's fried sweet potatoes
directions: Bake sweet potatoes in oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool overnight; slice lengthwise in 1/2-inch thick slices.
Fry in cooking oil on medium-high heat.
Brown; turn once.
Drain on paper towel or brown paper bag.
Serve hot.
May sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Try both ways; they are really tasty.

title: meatballs (rouladen)
directions: Beat steak with pounder or mallet.
Fill steak with diced bacon and pickle slices.
Salt and pepper.
Roll each steak and hold together with toothpicks.
In pan add oil, tomato and onion. Lay meat on top; brown on both sides.
Fill pan with water until rolls are covered; salt to taste.
Cook until done, about 1 hour (depending on size of pan) until fork feels it is done.
Remove meat rolls from pan and add flour; make gravy.
Return meat rolls to pan and warm.
Serve with mashed potatoes and red cabbage.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together, blending well.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° in 9-inch square pan.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Scald rhubarb in boiling water to cover.
Keep tightly covered and allow to stand several minutes before draining. Prepare mixture of eggs, flour, sugar and lemon juice.
Add drained rhubarb to this mixture, stirring gently to mix well. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake as for any custard pie.

title: chocolate fudge candy
directions: Cook sugar and milk; bring to boil.
Boil for 6 minutes.
Put butter and chocolate bits in bowl.
Pour milk mixture over chocolate and butter.
Beat.
Put in vanilla and nuts.
Pour in pan and cool.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use 3 to 4 heaping teaspoons per mug of hot water.
Store in a large tightly covered container. This mix makes a great gift during the cold wintery days or even the holidays for teachers, shut-ins, children, etc.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, soup, about 3/4 can milk and peppers in a bowl; put 1/2 in bottom of baking dish.
Crush Doritos; put over mixture in dish.
Put remaining mixture on top of Doritos.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with cheese and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: hot spinach dip
directions: Mix all together, except for tomato and onions. Spoon into a 9-inch pie plate or quiche dish. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned. Sprinkle with tomato and onion. Serve with crackers.

title: grandma's cake frosting
directions: Add sugar and cocoa.
Mix.
Add other ingredients.
Mix.
In pot, cook until forms a soft ball.

title: travis' favorite chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour, soda, salt, sugar and cocoa in mixing bowl (low speed).
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: caramel dip for fruit
directions: Melt butter. Add brown sugar. Add sour cream and vanilla. Serve with apple wedges and banana slices that have been dipped in lemon juice.

title: creamy swiss steak
directions: Place onion in bottom of a 4-quart crock-pot.
Dredge steaks in flour.
Layer and season as you go.
Spread cream of mushroom soup over meat.
Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours (high 3 to 5 hours).

title: ambrosia - my way(according to daughter terry)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except whole walnuts.
Refrigerate. Garnish with remaining walnuts.
Delicious!

title: lemon salad
directions: Combine cream cheese and Eagle Brand until smooth. Add pie filling and pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip and chill.

title: lemon supreme special
directions: Mix cake mix, sugar, oil and nectar together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour (when brown).
Cool, right side up, for 15 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: spoon bread
directions: Stir corn meal gradually into boiling water. Let cool. Beat egg yolks and stir into cornmeal with fat and buttermilk in which the soda has been dissolved. Beat egg whites until stiff and add to mixture. Pour into a greased baking dish. Bake at 425° for 40 minutes.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Brown ground beef.
Chop onion very fine and add to beef. Drain.
Add ketchup and chili powder.
Cook on medium-low heat for about 15 minutes.
Add water, if too thick.

title: autumn fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add rest of ingredients.
Make sure nuts go in last.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 1 large or 2 small casseroles.

title: sweet potato company casserole
directions: Mash potatoes; stir in butter.
Add remaining ingredients except marshmallows; mix well.
Turn into lightly greased 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with marshmallows; bake 10 minutes or until marshmallows are lightly browned.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: miracle whip cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in oven at 375°.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cake
directions: Combine boiling water, oatmeal and butter; let stand 10 minutes.
Add sugars and mix well.
Add eggs and mix well.
Sift together flour, soda and cocoa; mix.
Fold in 1/2 bag of chocolate chips.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix oleo, sugar and eggs.
Sift remaining ingredients and add. Chill and roll in small balls.
Roll in 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 tablespoons cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: spaghetti with clam sauce(quick, delicious and low-fat)
directions: Drain clams, reserving liquid.
Heat oil in a 1-quart saucepan over medium heat.
Add garlic; cook until lightly brown.
Add basil, oregano, parsley, crushed red pepper and reserved clam liquid; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; simmer 10 minutes to blend flavors.
Add clams.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until heated through.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: crockpot chili
directions: Brown meat.
Saute onions and bell peppers til soft.
Add all ingredients into crockpot and mix well.
Cook on high for 4 hours. Serve with fritos and grated cheese.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Cut oysters in pieces. Put layer of oysters in bottom of 2 quart baking dish. Add layer of crumbled saltines, slices of butter and shake of salt and pepper. Repeat 4 times, ending with saltines. Pour milk till soaked through.
Seperate mixture with knife and add more milk until all is moist. Bake at 350° for 30-35 min.

title: potato casserole #2
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Cover and bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Crumble 1 stack Ritz crackers and stir into 3/4 stick melted oleo.
Put this on potato casserole and return to oven about 20 minutes.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions in 2 layer pans or a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Blend milk gradually into cream cheese and prepare pudding using this mixture.
Spread on top of cake layers. Top with pineapple.
Frost with whipped topping.
Sprinkle with coconut and garnish with maraschino cherries.
Keeps well and gets even better after a couple of days in the refrigerator.

title: skillet chili
directions: In 12-inch skillet, heat oil and stir in diced onion; cook until tender.
Brown hamburger and drain off grease.
Add canned diced tomatoes, kidney beans, salt and chili powder.
Cook about 30 minutes on medium heat.

title: creamy tacos
directions: Brown ground beef.
Slowly melt cheese with evaporated milk. Add all ingredients together; simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Do not boil (cheese will curdle).
Serve over corn chips.

title: coconut-pineapple pie
directions: Pour ingredients which have been well mixed, into a 9-inch uncooked pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken tortilla soup
directions: Cook onion and garlic in 2 Tbsp. oil until tender.
Stir in broth, bell pepper, chilies, basil, salt, pepper, and puree.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat and summer, uncovered, for 30 min.
Heat 1/2 c. oil in skillet and cook tortilla squares and chicken into 6 bowls and pour soup over.
Top with shredded cheese, if desired.

title: lemon bites
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, egg and topping (batter will be very stiff).
Drop teaspoonful of dough into confectioners sugar.
Roll into 1 inch balls, using sugar to keep dough from sticking to hands.
Place balls of dough 2 inches apart on a greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown.
Transfer to wire rack to cool completely. Store in airtight container.

title: upstate minestrone soup
directions: Slice sausage crosswise (1/2-inch thick).
Brown in oil in deep saucepan or Dutch oven.
Add onion, garlic, carrots and basil. Cook for 5 minutes.
Add zucchini, tomatoes, water, bouillon, cabbage, salt and pepper.
Bring soup to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered for 1 hour.
Add beans, cook another 20 minutes. Garnish with parsley.

title: pumpkin parfait surprise
directions: Mix gelatin with boiling water.
Stir to dissolve.
Add ice water and set aside.
Mix pudding, milk and yogurt.
Add pumpkin, spice and gelatin.
Beat well.
Pour 3/4 of mixture into 2-quart dish.
Fold whipped topping into remaining mixture and pour on top.

title: lola hexom's chicken hot dish
directions: Simmer celery in broth 10 minutes.
Add butter.
Add mushrooms and dressing mix.
Place in greased baking dish.
Top with chicken or turkey.
Pour soup mixture over all.
Bake 1/2 to 3/4 hour at 350°.
Cover while baking.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: In medium saucepan, cook sugar and water until syrupy (about 10 to 15 minutes).
Set aside and cool.
Add remaining ingredients to cooked syrup.
Freeze until firm.

title: impossible pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased pie pans or 1 (10-inch) pie pan.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: honey "n" spice barbecue chicken
directions: Combine Heinz 57 sauce and honey.
Place chicken on grill or broiler pan.
Brush with melted butter, then 57 sauce-honey mixture.
Grill or broil until chicken is tender.
Turn and baste frequently.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: simmering potpourri
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bring to a hard boil; simmer.
Makes your house smell wonderful!!

title: low-fat mock boiled "peanuts"
directions: Soak beans overnight; parboil and pour off water.
Place in a slow cooker.
Cover beans with water; add oil and salt.
Cook approximately 2 to 3 hours.
Beans will be firm, not tender.
Take out and salt for taste.
If beans are tender, then you have yourself a pot of beans.

title: beef and cabbage casserole
directions: Chop cabbage into medium pieces and spread in bottom of a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Brown meat and onions in large skillet, breaking up meat with large spoon as it cooks. Stir in rice, salt and pepper.
Spoon mixture over cabbage.
In small saucepan heat tomato soup and water to boiling.
Pour over ingredients.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover casserole with foil tightly and bake for 1 1/2 hours in preheated 350° oven.
Fluff lightly with fork before serving.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Pour popped corn into a large brown grocery bag.
Combine sugar, butter, corn syrup and salt in 2 quart Ultra-21 dish. Bring to a boil in microwave (takes approximately 2 minutes). Reset microwave and boil for 2 minutes more.

title: easy refrigerator hot rolls
directions: In mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, salt and 1/2 cup flour.
Beat thoroughly.
Add oil and egg.
Mix in remaining flour with spoon until dough is easy to handle.
Place greased side up in greased bowl.
Cover bowl with aluminum foil; place in refrigerator.
Punch down occasionally as dough rises.

title: english toffee bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine peanut butter, sugar, egg and vanilla to thoroughly blend.
Drop by teaspoon, 2 inches apart, onto cookie sheet.
Flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sugar. Bake for 14 to 16 minutes, until lightly browned.
Cool on a rack. Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: sour cream cornmeal muffins
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Grease muffin pan and spoon each tin about half full.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: low-fat new england turkey chowder
directions: In a 5-quart pan, over medium-high heat, saute celery and onions in margarine for 2 to 3 minutes, or until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Add broth, potatoes, salt, white pepper and cayenne pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Once mixture is at a simmer, cover and cook 8 to 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in the turkey.

title: home canned apple pie filling
directions: Blend dry ingredients in large saucepan.
Stir in water.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add lemon juice and food coloring.
Pack in jars, leaving 1 inch of space at top of jars. Process 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cavatini
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef with onions and bell pepper.
Drain grease.
Cook noodles as directed on package and drain.
Mix ground beef mixture with Ragu sauce and noodles.
Pour into a large casserole dish.
Top with pepperoni and cheese.
Cook until cheese melts or about 20 minutes.

title: the world's best cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, cream butter and sugars until fluffy.
Add egg and mix well.
Add oil and vanilla, blending well.
Add oats, corn flakes, coconut and nuts, stirring well. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in water.
Bake for 12 minutes.
Remove from oven. Cool on cookie sheet for a few minutes before removing.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: glazed ham
directions: Blend honey, molasses, oil and cloves.
Place ham on spit/skewer and brush with glaze mixture.
Barbecue at medium heat for 15 minutes.
Baste; cook on high heat for 30 minutes.
Baste; lower heat back to medium for an additional 15 minutes.
Meat thermometer should read 150°.

title: crepes
directions: Stir the milk and water together. Set aside. Put the flour and salt in a bowl. Add the eggs and some of the milk and water mixture and whisk in the flour. Gradually pour the remaining milk and water into the mixture. Add half of the melted butter and whisk until smooth and creamy. Brush a skillet with butter and heat until it sizzles. Pour in 2 tablespoons of batter. Quickly tilt the pan from side to side until a thin layer of batter spreads across the bottom of the skillet. Cook the crepe for about a minute, then flip it over. Cook it for 10 seconds and slide it onto a warm plate. Spread with jam or honey; roll the crepes or fold into triangles.

title: nancy's chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken with seasoning of your choice.
(I use garlic salt and pepper or Lawry's seasoned salt and seasoned pepper.) Save broth; cool.
Debone chicken and cut into bite size pieces. Line bottom of Pam sprayed 9 x 13-inch baking dish with chicken pieces.
Combine broth, soup and drained vegetables and pour over chicken.
Combine remaining ingredients for "drop" biscuit topping.
Spoon over chicken and vegetable mixtures.
Do not stir. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes until golden brown.

title: mexican black bean salad
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil over medium-high heat.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve at room temperature or refrigerate.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift together meal, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add butter, onion, beaten egg and enough milk to make dough soft. Drop one teaspoon in deep fat (375° to 400°).
Cook about 4 or 5 minutes.

title: chinese noodle salad
directions: Combine cabbage, scallions and Ramen noodles in bowl.
Then brown in skillet, almonds, sesame seed, oil and butter.
Add to mixture combined in bowl previously, then add remaining ingredients.
Toss well.
Allow to sit a few hours in refrigerator before serving.
Serves 6 to 10.
Enjoy!!

title: baked onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter until limp.
Mix in undiluted beef broth, wine, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt.
Heat thoroughly.
Ladle in
4 to 6 ovenproof bowls
Sprinkle 1/2 of shredded Swiss cheese over soup.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: In casserole, put 1 layer of asparagus, 1 layer of eggs, 1 layer of soup, 1 layer of cheese and 1 layer of peas; repeat. Melt oleo and crumble crackers into oleo.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Cook until cheese melts and is bubbly, about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: asparagus salad
directions: Drain asparagus.
Arrange spears in a medium size salad bowl. Layer onion and bell pepper rings over top.
Pour Ranch dressing or mayonnaise over all.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and egg; add vanilla.
Add flour, 1/2 cup at a time.
Spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until desired browning.

title: finger paint
directions: Mix cornstarch with 3/4 cup water to make a smooth paste in a saucepan.
Soak gelatine in 1/4 cup cold water; set aside.
Pour boiling water slowly into cornstarch mixture, stirring as you pour.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and is clear.
Remove from heat; stir in gelatine.
Add tempera paint to color desired.
Cool.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Combine brown sugar, butter, syrup and salt in 2-quart glass bowl.
Microwave on High 3 or 4 minutes, stirring after each minute, until mixture comes to a boil.
Microwave 3 minutes more. Place popcorn and peanuts (and coconut, if desired) in a large brown paper bag.
Add baking soda to syrup mixture and stir well (it will foam!)
Pour over the popcorn and peanuts.
Close bag, shake well and microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes. Shake well and microwave for 1 1/2 minutes more. Shake well and pour into a large roasting pan. Cool and stir to separate.
(This is the best caramel corn I've ever had!)

title: easy holiday cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix half of cake mix (dry), shortening, butter, vanilla and egg in large bowl until well mixed.
Stir in remaining cake mix.
Fill cookie press with dough.
Form desired shapes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with colored sugar. Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until light brown around edges.
Cool 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: waffles(servings:  4)
directions: Combine well beaten egg yolks, milk and butter and add flour, beating until smooth.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in hot waffle iron.

title: tiger butter candy
directions: Melt white chocolate and peanut butter in double boiler.* Pour onto cookie sheet.
Melt Hershey's in double boiler, drop by spoonfuls into white chocolate and swirl.
Freeze 30 minutes. Remove to a board and hit with a hammer to get splinter effect.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Combine cake mix, 1 stick butter and egg.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan and up the sides (skimpy on the sides).
Combine the cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar; pour on the top of the cake.
Spread evenly.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Add enough water to pineapple and cherry juices to make 2 cups liquid.
Bring
liquids to a boil and pour over gelatin to dissolve.
Add
Cokes
and refrigerate until mixture begins to congeal.
Add
fruits and nuts; stir in cream cheese.
Pour in mold and chill until set.

title: tortilla stack
directions: Melt butter; add beef, onion and garlic.
Cook to brown the meat; drain fat.
Add tomato sauce, olives, chili powder, salt and pepper to meat mixture and stir well.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, alternate layers of buttered tortillas with meat sauce mixture and 1 1/2 cups of cheese.
Sprinkle the remaining 1/2 cup of cheese over top.
Pour water at edge of casserole into bottom of dish.
Cover and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Uncover and let stand for 5 minutes, then cut into 4 wedges and serve.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Put some oil on bottom of baking pan to cover.
Heat in oven until hot, 10 minutes.
Lay chicken pieces in bottom of pan. Sprinkle with paprika and oregano.
Put in oven for 15 minutes. Turn pieces over and sprinkle with paprika and oregano.
Cook 30 more minutes.
Put canned mushrooms and juice on top.
Cook 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and cook another 5 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Steam the broccoli.
Saute onions lightly in margarine.
Add soup and cheese.
Heat gently until cheese melts. Add remaining ingredients except bread crumbs.
Pour sauce over broccoli in medium baking dish.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and continue baking, about 30 minutes.

title: venison meat pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix ground venison, allspice, lemon juice, onion, salt and pepper together and set aside.
Flatten and expand individual dough segments with a rolling pin so that they have a round shape.
Place some ground venison mixture on each dough segment and pinch shut, forming a small half-circle pie. Put the small pie on a baking sheet sprayed with Pam.
Bake for 15 minutes or until done.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Make 2 holes in flour. Put egg in one and margarine in other.
Add vanilla and mix. Combine apples, 1/2 cup sugar and tapioca.
Grease a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan with margarine.
Put apple mixture in.
On wax paper, pat out batter.
Place on top of apples.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serve warm or cold.

title: chili for church troop
directions: Brown and drain ground beef; saute onions.
Mix tomato juice, chili beans and red beans. Heat until hot.
Add meat and onions. Mix well.
Add spaghetti.
When spaghetti is done add mushroom soup and cheese; simmer.
Add salt, pepper and chili powder to taste.
May add water to thin soup.

title: chicken puffs
directions: Cream the cheese and 2 tablespoons of the margarine together until smooth.
Add milk, salt, pepper, onion and chicken.
Mix well.
Separate crescent dough into 4 rectangles, firmly pressing perforations to seal.
Spoon meat mixture evenly over dough.
Pull corners of dough to center and press edges and all seams together. Brush tops with reserved margarine.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet for 20 to 25 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 4.

title: apple streusel coffee cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Add beaten egg, milk and melted shortening.
Add raw apples and nuts and mix well.
Pour into an 8-inch buttered pan or an angel cake pan.
Sprinkle with topping.

title: oven pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet.
Put rice in bottom of baking pan.
Sprinkle with 3/4 envelope dry onion soup mix.
Cover with 1/2 can mushrooms and 3 cups water.
Place chops in pan and rest of mushrooms, pimentos and rest of onion soup mix.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: layered spinach supreme
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk, eggs and onion.
Spread in greased 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking pan.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Spoon evenly over batter.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: a happy home recipe
directions: Take Love and Loyalty and mix thoroughly with Faith.
Blend with Tenderness and Forgiveness.
Add Hope, Friendship and Abundant Laughter.
Top freely with Smiles and Consideration for others.
Bake with bright sunshine.
Serve daily in generous helpings.

title: pear jello salad
directions: Drain pears.
Use juice and water to make 1 cup.
Boil and add to jello.
Set aside until thickened.
In blender, blend cream cheese and pears.
Add the jello and blend.
Fold in Cool Whip. Sets in about 2 hours.

title: turkey breast in the crock
directions: Wash and clean out turkey breast.
Place in crock-pot on low setting.
Add can of chicken broth, water and salt and pepper. Cook all day, turning once or twice if possible (but not necessary) until done.

title: cheesecake cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar, nuts and flour.
Stir in butter.
Blend until light and crumbly. Remove 1 cup mixture for topping.
Place remainder in an 8-inch square pan and press firmly.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Beat cheese with sugar.
Beat in egg, lemon juice, milk and vanilla.
Pour onto baked crust.
Top with reserved 1 cup topping mix.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes. Cool before cutting.
Makes about 24.

title: st. clair pudding
directions: Melt the chocolate and oleo. Add the milk, Karo, vanilla and powdered sugar. Stir well and spread over crackers.
Refrigerate at least 1 or 2 days before serving.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook onion in butter. Blend in flour and salt. Gradually stir in broth.
Cook and stir until thick.
Add chicken and vegetables. Heat until bubbling.
Pour into a large casserole, 2 1/2 to 3-quart.
Top with pie crust; vent.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: ma kaylor's angel food cake
directions: Measure and sift flour and sugar together three times.
Measure egg whites and remaining ingredients into a large bowl.
Beat until frothy.
Add gradually 2 tablespoons at a time, 3/4 cup sugar. Beat about 10 seconds after each addition.
Continue beating until stiff peaks are formed.
Sift about 3 tablespoons flour over meringue and fold in.
Repeat until all flour is folded in. Mixture will be thick.
Place ungreased tube pan.
Cut batter with a knife to remove air and level top until even.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Immediately turn pan upside-down over a bottle and cool.
Loosen with spatula.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cut corn from cob.
Cut celery, peppers and onion in small pieces, add salt, mustard, sugar and vinegar.
Let come to a boil, then add turmeric powder and boil 1/2 hour.

title: potato pudding
directions: Combine ingredients in casserole.

title: fresh cranberry apple salad
directions: Dissolve jell-o in boiling water, cool, add orange juice. Grind cranberries, add chopped apple, nuts and sugar.
When jell-o begins to thicken slightly, add cranberry apple/nut mixture.
Put in mold.

title: feather-light banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and gradually add sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add buttermilk to which baking soda has been added, alternately with dry ingredients.
Add mashed bananas and mix well.
Dredge nuts with flour and add to the mixture.
Pour into a prepared loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: "lime lift"
directions: Slice limes thinly.
Place in bowl with sugar.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Pour boiling water into bowl.
Cool, then chill.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Cover bottom of flat pan with nuts and coconut.
Mix cake mix according to directions.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and vanilla.
Dot on top of cake mix and twirl into mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix everything together except biscuits.
Heat in microwave for 3 minutes.
Pour in baking dish and top with biscuits.
Bake in oven at 300° until biscuits are done.

title: pumpkin-cranberry cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease (or Pam) baking sheets.
Chop cranberries and combine with 3 tablespoons sugar.
Combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda and salt in bowl.
With mixer set on medium-high, beat butter and remaining 1 cup sugar until creamy.
Beat in pumpkin, honey, vanilla and zest.
Reduce speed to low and gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in nuts and cranberries.

title: pizza fruit platter
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two round pizza pans. Combine first 6 ingredients and divide batter between 2 pans. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool on rack.
(You may freeze one pizza base for future use.)

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add mushrooms; blend in soup.
Add cooked, cubed chicken breasts.
Add cream or milk.
Separately cook broken spaghetti.
Grease casserole dish.
Layer chicken mixture and spaghetti.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, milk, sugar and eggs. In separate bowl, mix cinnamon and brown sugar. Add to batter and mix with wooden spoon. Pour in greased Bundt cake pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Melt
butter or margarine.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour
in a 9-inch pie shell (unbaked).
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix rice and the three cans of soup.
Place in buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish.
