Lay chicken on top of rice mixture. Butter the chicken parts, then sprinkle the Lipton onion soup on top of the chicken and rice mixture.

title: creamy cauliflower salad
directions: Mix yogurt, mayo and Ranch dressing.
Combine with other vegetables and ingredients.
Chill.
Add radishes when ready to serve.
Makes 25 servings.

title: pork chops and apples
directions: Trim fat from chops; rub sage onto both sides of chops.
Spray skillet; cook chops for 5 to 7 minutes, until pink.
Make sauce of onion, apple wedges, cider or juice and brown sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 3 to 5 minutes until apples are crisp, tender and onions are done.
Combine water and cornstarch; add to skillet.
Mix, cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Serve on cooked brown rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: onion ring batter
directions: Beat all ingredients together, adding enough water to make a medium thick batter.
Cut onions in rings 1/4-inch thick.
Dip each ring in batter and fry in hot oil.
Also good for fish.

title: white fruit cake
directions: First simmer raisins for about 30 minutes.
Drain and cool. Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Combine flour and whipped cream alternately.
Add fruits, raisins and nuts.
Place in tube pan, greased, and cook for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Cool, wrap and store.

title: mom's sour cream potato salad
directions: Bath potatoes in Italian dressing.
Refrigerate overnight or a couple of hours.
Combine potatoes, onions, celery seed, salt and pepper; toss lightly.
Add celery and eggs.
Mix sour cream, mayo, vinegar and mustard; mix well.
Pour over potatoes and toss lightly.
Chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: prime ribs of beef
directions: Have roast at refrigerator or room temperature.
Make small cuts in meat beside fat with small, sharp paring knife.
Insert garlic cloves.
Stir together salt, pepper, mustard and paprika. Rub over cut surface and fat of meat.

title: chili
directions: Saute beef until brown.
Pour of fat.
Add onions, pepper, garlic and spices.
Mix well.
When onion and pepper are tender, stir in tomatoes, sauce and paste.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil. Break up tomatoes with a fork.
Cover and simmer slowly until thick and flavors blend, about 40 minutes.
Add beans.
Simmer 10 minutes or until hot.

title: beef paprika
directions: Melt shortening in large skillet.
Add meat, onion and garlic; cook and stir until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Stir in catsup, Worcestershire sauce, sugar, salt, paprika, mustard, cayenne and 1 1/2 cups water.
Cover and simmer 2 to 2 1/2 hours. Blend flour and 1/4 cup water; stir gradually into meat mixture. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute. Serve over noodles.

title: foundation sweet dough
directions: Dissolve yeast and 1 tablespoon sugar in lukewarm water.
Scald milk, add shortening, sugar and salt; cool to lukewarm.
Add 2 cups flour to make a batter.
Add yeast and beaten eggs.
Knead lightly and place in greased bowl.
Cover and set in warm place, free from draft.
Let rise until doubled in bulk, about 2 hours.
When light, punch down and shape into dinner rolls, buns or coffee cake.
Place on tray and let rise.
Bake at 400° to 425°, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: Mix well and pour into a greased casserole dish.
Cover with topping.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Cook zucchini on low heat for one hour.
Add sugar, pineapple, lemon juice and Sure-Jell.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Take off burner. Add apricot Jell-O.
Stir well to blend.
Pour into sterilized jelly jars.
Seal and cool.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter; add eggs, then bananas, flour, soda, baking powder, salt and pecans.
Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cover few minutes; remove from pan.
Put in Tupperware container and seal overnight.

title: microwave brown bread
directions: Shake the raisins with a tablespoon of the flour to coat. Combine all ingredients and pour into a 4 cup microwaveable measuring cup or bowl of similar size.

Container should be well greased and there should be enough room at the top for expansion. Cover with plastic wrap, held in place with an elastic band. Microwave at 50 percent power for 12 minutes, then allow to sit for 10 minutes. Run knife around inside of bowl and invert to remove bread. Slice and serve warm with baked beans.

title: angel hash(salad)
directions: Combine well beaten egg yolks with 1 cup syrup drained from fruits.
Blend well.
Add to cornstarch and sugar; mix well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil and thickens.
Cool thoroughly at room temperature.
Fold in whipped topping, nuts, marshmallows and fruits.
Chill overnight in refrigerator.

title: fluffy peanut butter pie
directions: Whip the cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat peanut butter and sugar into cheese.
Slowly add milk, blending thoroughly.
Fold topping into mixture.
Pour into prepared pie crust.
Sprinkle with chopped peanuts (optional).
Freeze until firm and serve.

title: sand tart cookies
directions: Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Use foil or cookie sheet, if not greased.

title: millionaire salad
directions: Cook eggs, sugar, lemon juice and marshmallows in top of double boiler until partly melted.
Add 1 tablespoon butter and cool.
Add whipped cream, pineapple, bananas and walnuts.
Place in 9 x 15 x 2-inch pan or a bowl.
Chill.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: In
large
bowl
stir
eggs,
syrup,
chocolate, sugar, butter and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted
comes
out clean.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 8 servings.

title: grilled mushroom burgers
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Stir well.
Shape into 6 patties.
Coat grill with cooking spray.
Place on grill over medium-hot coals.
Place patties on rack and cool 5 to 7 minutes on each side.
Spread 1 tablespoon catsup on bottom half of bun.
Top with patty.
Top with lettuce and tomato slices and onion slice.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Fold mixture through potatoes, place in large casserole.
Pour 1/2 pint half and half cream over potatoes.
Bake slowly 1 hour.

title: stars and stripes
directions: Slice 1 cup strawberries; halve remaining strawberries.
Set aside.
Line bottom of 12 x 8-inch baking dish with cake slices (8 slices of the pound cake).
Top with 1 cup sliced strawberries, 1 cup blueberries and Cool Whip.
Arrange strawberry halves and remaining blueberries over Cool Whip to create a flag design. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 15 servings.

title: baked pepper-cheese squash
directions: Boil squash.
Fry bacon until crisp and remove from pan. Brown onion rings in some of the bacon drippings.
Crumble bacon. Layer one half of squash, bacon, onion rings and cheese in a 9 x 9-inch shallow baking dish.
Repeat until ingredients are used up. Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake in a 325° oven for 40 minutes. Serves 10.

title: creamy potluck potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water for 10 minutes or until tender; drain, rinse in cold water, drain again.
In large mixing bowl, stir together soup, sour cream, cream cheese and the dry butter flavored mix.
Add 1/4 cup Cheddar cheese (shredded), 3 tablespoons green onion, milk, parsley, garlic, salt and pepper; stir mixture to combine.
Stir in the cooked potatoes.
Transfer mixture to 2-quart shallow casserole or 12 x 7 x 2-inch dish. Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until heated through.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 5 minutes more or until cheese melts.
Sprinkle with remaining green onions. Serves 4 to 5.
This recipe can be doubled.

title: queso chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken pieces and roll in flour; dip in beaten egg and water mixture and then back in flour. Fry uncovered in hot oil until done; drain on paper towel. Cook rice. Cube Velveeta in a large microwave safe bowl and add Ro-Tel to top; cover loosely and microwave on high for 5 minutes; stir well and continue cooking until melted. Place cooked rice in a Pam sprayed casserole dish. Stir in just enough cheese sauce to moisten rice. Arrange cooked chicken pieces over rice and add more cheese sauce on top.

title: cheesy grits casserole(breakfast casserole)
directions: Cook grits in water, add butter and cheddar cheese and seasoning salt.
In a separate bowl, stir 2 eggs.
Mix in slowly to the grits mixture.
Put in 9 x 13 casserole and cook for 1 hour at 350.
Can be made the night before and bake the following morning.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and marinate at least overnight in Italian dressing.
Add vegetables and cheese.
Mix with sour cream and seasonings to taste. Refrigerate.
Keeps well up to a week or ten days.
Flavor improves with age.

title: barbecued beans
directions: Mix all together.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Great for picnic or barbecue.
Best baked day ahead.

title: scallops in cheese sauce
directions: Saute celery, green pepper
and onion in butter; do not brown. Add flour, mustard, salt and pepper;
blend.
Add milk and
cook until thickened.
Stir in cheese and let melt.
Add drained scallops
and
sherry.
Cover
and	cook for about 10 minutes. Serve with noodles.

title: peanut butter dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in a small mixing bowl and beat until smooth with hand electric mixer.
This is delicious on canned fruits or fresh bananas or apples.

title: citrus salad
directions: In bowl, mix fruit, sour cream, marshmallows and coconut. Cover and refrigerate for several hours.
If desired, serve in lettuce-lined plates.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread cherry pie filling in square baking dish. Top with pineapple. Sprinkle cake mix over pineapple. Pour melted butter over cake mix. Sprinkle with coconut and nuts. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: potato crust cheese pie
directions: Scrub, but do not peel, potatoes.
Shred potatoes and onion coarsely; lightly press and drain off liquid.
Add the beaten egg, the onion soup mix and black pepper to taste.
Toss.
Grease bottom and sides of a 10-inch pie plate with nonstick cooking spray.
Press potato mixture over bottom and sides of pan to form crust.
Cover crust with drained, cooked vegetables, if desired. Sprinkle cheese over vegetables or crust.
Beat eggs with milk, parsley, paprika, dry mustard, onion soup mix, black pepper and cayenne.
Gently pour over cheese.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until knife inserted in center comes out clean (and crust is golden).
Serves 8.

title: monkey bread
directions: Dissolve the yeast in the lukewarm water.
Combine in a large mixing bowl the milk, potatoes, Crisco, sugar and salt and let stand until the mixture cools to lukewarm.
Then add the yeast, eggs and 1 1/2 cups flour.
Mix thoroughly and continue to add flour until you have a stiff dough.
Turn out on a board and knead thoroughly.
Return to a greased bowl and grease the top of the dough.
Cover with a damp cloth and let stand to rise 2 hours in a warm place.
Punch down and put in the refrigerator to chill. About 1 1/2 hours before serving time, roll dough about 1/2 inch thick.
Cut in 2-inch squares and pull to elongate to diamond shape.
Dip in melted butter; lay alternately around a well buttered ring mold or tube pan.
Then repeat for a second layer, alternating so the diamonds will not fall on each other.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve in a ring and let your guests pull apart.
You can also use a diamond shaped cutter.

title: nancy's stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef with the onion.
Drain off excess fat.
Add consomme, lemon juice and garlic.
Simmer while cooking noodles. Drain noodles and add to meat sauce.
Stir in sour cream 5 minutes before serving.
Pour into serving dish.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: sir thomas
directions: Fry or broil Canadian bacon or ham.
Place on bottom muffin half.
Top with egg, cheese and remaining muffin half.
Enjoy immediately.

title: caramel peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk, vanilla and butter in large pot.
Bring slowly to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 3 minutes. Remove from heat and add peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme. Cream together and pour into a buttered square container.

title: beef and tomato in soy sauce
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons oil and stir-fry onion until fragrant.
Add tomato; stir briefly.
Add beef and carrot.
Add wine, soy, ketchup, sugar, pepper and 1 cup water.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat to low and cook 1 hour or until meat is tender and liquid is reduced to about 2/3 cup.
Mix cornstarch with 2 tablespoons water. Add to meat to thicken.
Serve over cooked noodles.
(Dried noodles are available in Asian markets and many supermarkets.
To cook, add to boiling water; cook for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Add a little oil.)

title: fruit cocktail torte
directions: Sift flour, sugar and soda into a bowl.
Into this dry mixture, pour the can of fruit cocktail and mix well.
Add the beaten egg and vanilla.
Pour mixture into greased baking dish. Over the top, sprinkle the chopped nuts and brown sugar.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes in a 350° oven.
This may be fairly brown, but does not hurt the torte.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Soften bread in milk.
Mix hamburger, egg and bread together. Make patties and fry in pan.
Do not brown.
Mash out grease.
Set in glass dish.
Put cream of chicken and water into a bowl and whip to get out lumps.
Pour over patties.
Place can of biscuits, one at a time, around the side of pan.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat shortening until fluffy.
Add sugar a little at a time. Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flavoring.
Add flour 3 or 4 tablespoons at a time.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all together and put in flat, greased casserole.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in a well-greased cake pan.
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: orange chiffon cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Make a well and add in order:
oil, egg yolks, water and orange peel.
Stir until smooth.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs together well.
(I use a fork for this.)
Add remaining ingredients, except for pecans.
Mix well.
Add pecans and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: sausage twirls
directions: Combine biscuit mix, milk and butter in a large bowl until well blended and refrigerate dough for 30 minutes. Divide refrigerated dough into 2 portions and roll out each portion on waxed paper to 1/8-inch thick rectangles, each about 10 x 7-inch. Spread half uncooked sausage over dough; top sausage with peppers and onions. Roll lengthwise into a log. Repeat process with remaining ingredients. Place both logs wrapped in freezer until hard enough to cut easily, about 1 hour.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Mix together flour, oleo and pecans.
Bake until brown and cool.
Mix powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Add 1 large Cool Whip.
Put on top of mixture.
Spread fruit on top.
Add sugar and cornstarch to blueberries when cooking.

title: hello dollies
directions: Layer ingredients in a rectangular pan in order given.
Bake at 300° until coconut is toasted, about 15 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: creamed cheese crescents
directions: Mix ingredients until smooth and creamy.
Place dough in refrigerator overnight.
Divide dough and roll in powdered sugar. Cut into 2-inch squares.
Fill with prune, walnut or apricot butter.
Roll into crescents.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until brown.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool.
Makes 10 dozen.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift dry ingredients together and cut in shortening.
Add yeast mixture to buttermilk and mix with dry ingredients.
Knead, then roll out and cut into biscuits. Brush with butter and bake at 400° until brown.
Yields 30 to 36.

title: kurt's mom's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl, using a wooden spoon, rice spatula, or hands.
Place in ungreased loaf pan.
Form and round out mixture to fit pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until done.

title: banana-orange surprise(for the weight watchers group.  low-fat.  good breakfast drink.)
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender.
Blend on high for 30 seconds.
Enjoy!

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill overnight.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Keep refrigerated up to 6 weeks. Bake muffins at 400° about 20 minutes.

title: homemade sausage
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Wash the casing in water then put end onto
faucet and run water through.
Store remaining casing in salt. Push casing onto funnel.
Make a knot at the end and push meat through funnel with your thumb.
Twist into links.
Use immediately or freeze some and refrigerate the rest, as these are perishable.
Can also be used in bulk.
Shape into patties and pan fry.
Can also use turkey meat.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Blend well the first 8 ingredients; stir in the remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheets.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes at 375°.
Makes about four dozen.

title: sweet party mix
directions: Melt margarine in microwave for 30 to 45 seconds, stir in sugar and extract.
Gradually add cereals and nuts, stir well. Micro 4 to 5 minutes, stirring every 1 1/2 minutes.
Spread on waxed paper to cool.

title: gourmet wild rice
directions: Combine currants and brandy and set aside.
Cook rice according to moisture level on package, using the chicken broth. Bring to a boil, cover and reduce heat.
Cook for 45 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Stir in currant mixture, olive oil and pine nuts.
Serves 6.

title: overnight lettuce salad
directions: Drain vegetables well.
Layer in order.
Cover.
Keep in refrigerator overnight.
Do not stir until ready to serve.

title: egg pancakes(thin)
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk, salt and baking powder to flour to make a thin batter.
Pancakes will be thin.
Sprinkle with sugar and roll up.

title: ricotta cheese cake
directions: Mix dry pudding in with cake mix and prepare according to cake box directions.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix Ricotta cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla together.
Pour mixture over cake mix.

title: irish bread(2 loaves)
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large pan or bowl (spaghetti pot).
Knead with hands or mixer on low. Grease and flour 2 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, then at 325° for 40 minutes (or until baked through).

title: stir-fry
directions: Cut all vegetables in small, but not tiny, pieces.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in skillet.
Stir by frying onion, carrots and broccoli until 1/2 done.
Add celery, mushrooms, zucchini, green pepper and snow peas.
Fry and stir until cooked, but still crunchy.
Season with black pepper and soy sauce.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt in ungreased 9 x 9-inch pan.
In bowl, mix oil, milk and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients and mix with a fork until most of the lumps are gone (a few minutes).
Sprinkle with the mixture of brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Pour very hot water over batter.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Mix Yoshida's gourmet sauce, rum and a generous amount of rosemary (more or less to your desire).
Place flank steak in the marinade for at least an hour (can marinate longer), turning occasionally.
Grill until desired doneness.

title: broccoli with bacon salad
directions: In a bowl mix sugar, vinegar and salad dressing.
Add all ingredients.
Add bacon before serving.

title: ruth's sweetheart salad
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Meanwhile, in a saucepan, bring sugar and pineapple juice to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Add lemon and cherry juices.
Cool to lukewarm.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients well in 5-quart freezer and freeze it.

title: rich and easy chocolate nut cupcakes
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine.
Place in a large bowl and add sugar, salt and flour.
Stir in eggs, one at a time, and add vanilla and pecans.
Pour into paper baking cups in muffin tins. Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Makes 20 to 24 cupcakes.

title: creole black-eyed peas
directions: Cook bacon in large skillet until crispy. Remove bacon, reserving drippings in skillet. Crumble bacon and set aside.

title: hummus
directions: Mince parsley in food processor; set aside.
Drop garlic through feeding tube while machine is running.
Process until well minced.
Add chickpeas, 2/3 cup olive oil, tahini, lemon juice, salt, cumin and pepper.
Process until smooth.
Spoon into serving bowl; drizzle with remaining olive oil and sprinkle with parsley. Garnish with olives.

title: chicken divan quiche
directions: Combine rice, water and 1/4 teaspoon salt in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap; microwave at High 5 minutes.
Cook, covered, at Medium-high (70% power) for 12 minutes, or until rice is tender.
Cool.

title: super all-day beef stew
directions: Mix together soup, water or wine and flour until smooth. Combine with remaining ingredients in covered roasting pan.
Bake at 275° for 4 to 5 hours.
(It is not necessary to brown meat or dissolve beef cubes; just combine everything, tossing well.) Serve over noodles. Makes 8 servings.

title: never fail fudge frosting
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a saucepan.
Add sugar and cocoa. Add milk.
Let come to a boil and boil for 1 minute at a rolling boil.
Remove from heat.
Add almond flavoring.
Cool a few minutes; then stir well.
Spread on cake.

title: seven layer dip
directions: Combine bean dip and green chilies. Spread in large serving plate or cookie sheet. Combine sour cream and taco seasoning. Spread over bean mixture. Spread guacamole dip over sour cream mixture. Cover and chill several hours. Just before serving, garnish with cheese, tomatoes, green onions and olives. Serve with chips.

title: carol's spinach bread
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions; drain.
Press between layers of paper towels to remove excess moisture.
Set aside; saute onion and garlic in butter in a small skillet over medium heat until tender.
Combine onion mixture, spinach, Cheddar cheese and Mozzarella cheese; stir well.
Slice bread in half horizontally.
Spread spinach mixture evenly on cut sides of bread; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Place on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until cheese melts. Yield: 8 servings.

title: pie crust(great grandma gums)
directions: Mix all together.
It turns out for me every time.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes, if the skins are tough, or just scrub and rinse them.
Cut potatoes into thin slices but not all the way through. Put potatoes in baking dish.
Fan them slightly.
Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with herbs.
Bake potatoes at 425° for 50 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake for another 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Combine caramels and 1/2 cup evaporated milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly to melt caramels.
Set aside.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cake mix, melted margarine, 1/3 cup milk and nuts.
Press half of dough in cake pan and bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Sprinkle caramel mixture over chips.
Crumble remainder of dough on top.
Return to oven and bake for 18 minutes. Cool completely before cutting.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Scrub cucumbers; don't peel.
Put in a large bowl all the ingredients.
Stir to dissolve sugar.
Cover and refrigerate. Next day, mix thoroughly.
Pack in jars with some liquid.
Will keep up to 6 months refrigerated.
Makes approximately 5 pints.

title: filipino strip steak
directions: Mix soy, lemon and pepper.
Place sirloin strips in marinade and let set 2 to 3 hours.
Remove strips and drain, saving all liquid.
In hot pan or wok brown sirloin in oil and cook until done.
Remove and keep warm.
Saute onions until soft.
Return half the liquid to pan.
Take the other half and put in a jar.
Add cornstarch and vigorously shake until smooth.
Return to pan and simmer while stirring until thick.
Add meat to mixture.
Serve over rice.

title: mint or plain wafers
directions: Can use several drops of peppermint, if desired, or any other flavoring such as orange, lemon, etc.

title: world's best cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream the butter and sugars until fluffy.
Add egg; mix well.
Add salad oil and vanilla, mixing well.
Add oats, cornflakes, coconut and nuts, stirring well.
Add flour, soda and salt; mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork dipped in water. Bake 12 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheet for a few minutes before removing.
They stay moist and keep beautifully.
Yields 5 to 6 dozen.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Grease dish with margarine.
Add the 1 cup washed raw rice and 2 cans beef consomme.
Saute onion in the 4 tablespoons margarine and pour on top of rice, soup mixture.
Drain can of mushrooms and put on top.
Bake 1 hour, uncovered, at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: crissey's waffles
directions: Measure dry ingredients into mixing bowl.
Blend.
Combine egg yolks and milk.
Stir into dry ingredients.
Stir in cooking oil. Carefully fold in egg whites.
Do not overmix.
Pour 1 cup batter onto preheated griddle.
Close and bake.
Serve hot with butter and maple syrup or try strawberries and whipped cream. Makes 5 to 6 waffles.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: oatmeal crisps
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and sugars with mixer.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well.
Sift together flour, salt and baking soda and add to creamed mixture; beat.
With a wooden spoon, stir in oatmeal and nuts.
Form dough into a roll on waxed paper.
Wrap and chill thoroughly.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer ingredients in order.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip and sweetened condensed milk thoroughly.
Add lemonade mix that has been thawed completely.
This will thicken when lemonade is added.
Be sure to mix well.
Pour into graham cracker pie crusts and refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.

title: vigorous veggie soup
directions: Put all ingredients into a 2 to 4-quart pot.
Fill with water. Bring to boil, then lower flame and simmer for 1 hour.
(Avoid seasoning, if possible.)
Remove all ingredients.
(Cooked vegetables may be eaten as okazu with seasoning added as desired.) Store broth in refrigerator.
Drink 1 cup of broth once in the morning and again at night.
(Consume broth twice daily.)
Continue drinking twice a day for a minimum 2-month period.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease pie plate.
Place all ingredients in blender.
Cover and blend on high for 15 seconds. Pour into pie plate.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted in middle comes out clean, about 50 to 55 minutes.

title: secret hot fudge sauce
directions: Place chocolate, sugar and milk in a heavy saucepan over low heat.
Let melt, stirring occasionally.
When completely melted, remove from heat and stir in butter, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Add vanilla.
Serve warm.

title: pecan pie filling
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in uncooked pie crust.

title: buttered beans
directions: Wash beans; add to large pot of water.
Cook 3 hours.
Add spices and ham chunks.
Serve with cornbread!

title: tuna sunflower casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Spoon into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients. Stir thoroughly. Add oil slowly, beating constantly and continue to beat until thick.
Add poppy seeds. Store in refrigerator.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix peas, cooked macaroni, salt and pepper to taste, tuna, soup and water.
Top with cheese.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
I oftentimes double the recipe.

title: frosty strawberry squares
directions: Stir flour, butter, brown sugar and nuts together and spread evenly in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Leave 2/3 of mixture in pan.
Remove other and save.
Combine whites, sugar, strawberries and lemon juice in a large bowl and beat to stiff peaks (10 minutes).
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon over crumbs and top with saved crumbs.
Freeze 6 hours or overnight.
Cut in squares.
Serves 12.
May use 10 ounce frozen strawberries, partially thawed.

title: cole slaw salad
directions: Shred cabbage; dice pepper and onion and mix sugar, vinegar, salad oil and salt.
Bring to boil and pour over cabbage mixture. Do not stir for at least 1 hour.
Chill and serve.
Makes 1 gallon. Keeps up to 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp, chop and cool.
Combine mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar, salt, lemon juice.
Add to broccoli, onions and raisins.
Add bacon just before serving.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together the flour, salt and baking soda, set aside.
Cream together the shortening and peanut butter, add the sugars and mix well.
Add the eggs, one at a time, mixing well between additions. Stir in the flour.
Bake at 325°f. 160°c. gas mark 3 for 15-20 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix sour cream and cream cheese together.
Stir in dressing mix.
Fold in shrimp.
Chill and serve.

title: strawberry topping
directions: Rinse, hull and cut strawberries in half.

In medium saucepan over medium heat, cook 2 cups strawberry halves, sugar, 2 tablespoons orange juice and lemon juice, stirring constantly, 3 to 5 minutes until sugar dissolves and strawberries begin to soften.
In food processor or blender puree mixture until almost smooth.
In same saucepan, stir remaining orange juice and cornstarch until smooth; add strawberry puree.
Cook over medium-high, stirring constantly, 5 minutes until slightly thickened.
Remove from heat; stir in remaining strawberries. Serve over pancakes, ice cream or cake.

title: greek spinach pie(from mom's friend, jenny)
directions: In
large bowl combine the tomatoes, olives, scallions, garlic,
salt,
pepper
and
basil.
Toss gently and add olive oil.
Stir and let stand, covered, for at least 3 hours.
This developes
the
flavors.
Cook
pasta
according
to
package directions
and toss the cooked pasta into the prepared sauce. Serve immediately or at room temperature.

title: ambrosia pie
directions: Mix whipped topping with condensed milk.
Stir well; add pineapple, oranges, coconut, pie filling, and marshmallows.
Stir all ingredients well and spoon mixture into pie crust.
Chill for 2 or 3 hours before serving.
Pies will keep 3 weeks in refrigerator or may be frozen for later use.

title: peanut butter roll
directions: Mix butter and powdered sugar.
Add cream and vanilla.
Keep adding sugar until you have a dough which could be rolled.
Roll into one large sheet, then spread with peanut butter and roll up. Put in icebox and allow to harden.
Cut into slices.
Serve.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish; set aside.
Mix all ingredients except fruit.
Pour on top of margarine, but do not mix.
Pour fruit in middle of batter.	Do not mix.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: peachy pork picante
directions: Cut pork into cubes and coat with taco seasoning; brown in a little oil.
Add salsa and preserves to skillet, stirring to mix well.
Cover skillet and lower heat, simmering gently for 15 minutes or a little longer.
Serve over rice.

title: pork sausage gravy and biscuits
directions: Cook sausage in medium saucepan until browned.
Drain off fat, leaving about 2 tablespoons. Stir in flour.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Gradually whisk in milk, salt and pepper, stirring constantly, about 5 minutes.
Serve over hot biscuits.

title: karen baxter's sweet-n-sour sauce
directions: Mix together until it boils.

title: beef and cheese enchiladas
directions: Mix Velveeta cheese, pimentos, green chilies, cream of chicken soup, milk and enchilada sauce.
Heat slowly until cheese has melted.
Brown meat while soup mixture is cooking.

title: oriental chicken wings
directions: Marinate chicken wings with other ingredients for 30 minutes. Preheat oven to 400°.
Place wings on a cookie sheet or a baking pan with rack, lightly coated with cooking spray.
Bake for 1 hour. Serve with plenty of napkins!

title: glossy chocolate frosting
directions: Mix together in saucepan the sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in boiling water, cocoa and salt.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat.
Stir in margarine and vanilla.
Spread on cake while hot.

title: granny's peanut brittle
directions: Cook water, syrup and sugar about 20 minutes. Add peanuts. Cook until peanuts start to pop. Take off heat. Add baking soda and vanilla. Pour into a greased pizza pan or cookie sheet. Let cool. Break up and eat.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Layer vegetables in casserole dish.
Heat soup, milk and butter.
Pour over vegetables.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.

title: grandma's scratch cake
directions: Mix cake ingredients and bake in glass baking dish at 350° until done.

title: simpler chicken casserole *
directions: Cook and debone chicken. Mix together all ingredients and pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour or until liquid is absorbed.
(This was called "Delicious Chicken Casserole" in the previous FBC cookbook.)

title: *banana split cake
directions: Bake 1/2 box of cake mix in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.
Cool cake.
For pudding layer, mix the softened cream cheese, dry pudding mix and 1 1/2 cups milk together and pour over cooled cake.
On top of the pudding layer, place a layer of the drained pineapple, sliced bananas and Cool Whip.
Drizzle on chocolate syrup; top with cherries and sprinkle pecans over all.
Chill.

title: crispy potato pancake
directions: To shred potatoes:
Peel and rinse.
Run potatoes lengthwise through the coarse blades of a vegetable shredder.
Immerse shredded potato in cold water to prevent darkening until ready to cook.
Drain well.

title: risotto with shrimp
directions: In a 10-inch frying pan melt 3 tablespoons butter, add onion. Cook stirring often until onion is lightly golden, about 6 minutes.
Add rice and mandarin peel, stir often until most of rice is opaque, about 4 minutes.
Add mandarin juice, wine and chicken stock. Bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered, stirring occasionally at first and then
more often to prevent scorching as liquid is absorbed.
Cook about 40 minutes, until all liquid is absorbed and rice is tender to bite. Spoon rice onto a warm platter, keep warm.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Cook for 30 minutes and put in jars and seal.
Makes 8 pints.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Brown ribs.
Pour sauce on ribs and bake at 350° for 1 and 3/4 hours.
Bake, uncovered, another 15 minutes.
(Can also be made with meat balls.)

title: potato and kale soup
directions: In large pot, combine potatoes, chicken and broth or water. Boil, skimming as necessary.
Cook at slow boil for 13 to 15 minutes or until tender.
Add olive oil, carrots, scallions, kale, beans, bay leaf, basil and parsley.
Add dash or two of Tabasco sauce if desired.
Boil, stirring occasionally, 5 to 6 minutes or until flavorful.
Remove bay leaf before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: potatoes and ham
directions: Layer in casserole dish potatoes, onion and ham.
Blend together milk, flour, salt and pepper.
Pour over potato mixture. Dot with butter and bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: italian pasta sauce #2
directions: If adding meat, brown first, and then add onion, carrots, celery, (peas and/or mushrooms, if desired) and garlic in oil until soft, but not brown (about 10 minutes). Add tomatoes and basil, dry or fresh, and simmer for about 45 minutes. Serve over cooked pasta. Approximately 4 servings.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender; drain. Salt and pepper to taste. Mix other ingredients and melt in microwave. Pour over potatoes. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: golden lemon chicken
directions: Dip chicken in egg, then flour.
In a 12-inch skillet, melt butter and brown chicken over medium heat for 4 minutes, turning once.
Mix soup mix with water and stir in skillet.
Arrange lemon slices on chicken, bring to a boil and simmer for 10 minutes, covered, or until sauce is thickened and chicken is done.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pastichio(baked macaroni)
directions: Cook beef and drain.
Saute beef and onions in 3 tablespoons margarine.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic.
Add grape juice and tomato paste; simmer until moisture is absorbed, 20 minutes. Cook macaroni in salt until almost done.
Rinse and drain.
Mix hot macaroni with melted butter.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: In a large casserole baking dish, layer broccoli, chicken and rice.
Mix and add the chicken soup, sour cream and chicken broth. Top with crackers and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Top with grated cheese and bake 10 minutes.

title: cranberry jello
directions: Cool jello not set, then beat very well with electric mixer or blender.
Pour into a mold to set.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Heat until melted the soup, cheese, tomatoes and milk.
Layer in a large dish:
Doritos chips, hamburger, mixture and cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: frosty freeze pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and marshmallow cream.
Mix at medium speed until blended.
Add sherbet and mix well.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into crust.
Freeze until firm.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: oatmeal-cheesecake-cranberry bars
directions: In a large mixing bowl, stir together flour, oatmeal and brown sugar. Using a pastry blender or 2 knives, cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Reserve 1 1/2 cups of the crumbs. Press remaining crumbs into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef; drain and rinse with hot water.
Add to Ragu and water to simmer.
Cook 9 lasagna noodles according to directions on the box.
Mix cottage cheese and Egg Beaters.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Pat 2 packages of crescent rolls onto a cookie sheet.
Bake crescent rolls at 375° for 10 to 13 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, Ranch dressing and mayo together.
Add 1/2 of chopped vegetables to mixture.
Spread onto cooled crust.
Sprinkle remaining vegetables on top and pat down.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine 1/2 cup melted butter with next 5 ingredients in mixing bowl.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Combine brown sugar, flour, 2 1/2 tablespoons melted butter and nuts in small mixing bowl; mix well.
Sprinkle topping over sweet potato mixture.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: snicker doodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Mix flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Mix all ingredients.
Shape into balls.
Combine cinnamon and sugar in a shallow dish.
Roll dough in sugar and cinnamon, coating well. Bake 8 to 10 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel and seed cukes. Cube cukes. Mix with sugar, vinegar and scallion. Let sit a few minutes. Stir occasionally. Put yogurt into a bowl. Pour juice off cukes and into yogurt. Combine well and add cukes. Toss.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Blend all and beat for 2 minutes.
Bake in greased and floured cake pans in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until done.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: spinach and ham lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles as directed.
Drain, rinse and set aside. Meanwhile, cook spinach as directed and set aside.

title: sour cream sugared nuts
directions: To toast nuts: Sprinkle nuts into ungreased skillet, stirring. Cook on medium heat 5 to 7 minutes until golden brown.
Mix sour cream and brown sugar in saucepan.
Heat to 223° with candy thermometer, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir rapidly until mixture has coated the nuts.
Spread on wax paper and separate nuts.
Cool and store in airtight container.
Lasts 3 to 4 months.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
May add chocolate chips and pecans to this mixture.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and mix well.	Reserve 1 cup of	flour.	Sift
remainder of flour with baking powder and salt. Add

alternately with milk to first mixture. Sprinkle

pans, filled 2/3 full, at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: dolly parton's corn pone
directions: Mix all ingredients together, using enough milk to make a stiff batter.
Form pones by hand and put on greased baking sheet. Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 425°.
Makes about 18.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Stir oleo and sugar into boiling water, let cool.
Add eggs and vanilla; stir.
Add flour, cinnamon, soda and salt. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: tom's spaghetti salad(for men only)
directions: Cook spaghetti as per directions on box.
Cool with cold water and drain.
Add diced mango, tomato, cucumber and dressing.
Chill overnight.
Stir before serving.

title: rum raisin ring cake
directions: Drain pineapple, pressing out 1 1/4 cups pineapple syrup or juice; reserve 1/4 cup for cake and 3 tablespoons for icing.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Put first five ingredients in saucepan and boil one minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add one teaspoon vanilla, 1/2 cup nuts.
Mix in powdered sugar.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: moon's green chili casserole
directions: You will need 1 (7 x 11-inch) casserole dish.

title: easy chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place rice in a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Pour the chicken broth over the rice and place your chicken on top. Pour your melted margarine over the chicken and bake in oven at 450° for 1 hour.
You can debone your chicken and mix the chicken into the rice.

title: classic lasagna
directions: Cook beef until browned, stirring to crumble; drain.
Add garlic to next 4 ingredients; simmer 15 minutes or until thick, stirring occasionally.

title: citron custard pie
directions: Mix all together with egg beater.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell and bake at 325° until golden brown on top.

title: hot crabmeat appetizer
directions: Soften cream cheese with milk.
Blend all ingredients together.
Bake covered at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot while spread on party rye or crackers.
Serves 6.

title: black magic cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add salad oil, eggs and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Add coffee, then vanilla.
Bake for about 35 minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut meat into serving pieces. Season with salt and pepper. Roll in flour.
Heat slow cooker.
Add vegetable oil. When hot, put in meat and cook until done.
Add onion, celery, pepper, tomato soup and water. Cover and cook for 45 minutes.
If desired, thicken gravy by adding cornstarch.

title: steamed fish
directions: Scale and clean the fish.
Sprinkle salt over the fish and let stand for 10 minutes.
Place fish in shallow pan.
Combine sugar, oil and shoyu.
Pour over fish.
Garnish with Chinese parsley and lemon wedges.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Add 1/4 cup water to carrots and celery.
Microwave 2 to 3 minutes until softened.
Saute onions and garlic in oil.
Set aside.
Brown sausage in large saucepan.
Drain.
Add all ingredients.
Cook until bubbly, stirring occasionally.
If too thick add additional water.

title: hareesah(wheat stew)
directions: In a 12-quart saucepan, place the chuck roast, wheat, salt and enough water to cover.
Bring to a boil on high heat.
Reduce heat to medium and let cook with frequent stirring until all the water is absorbed and the meat comes off the bones.
(Be careful not to overdry it for it may char.)
Remove wheat to a large plate and let cool.
Remove bones from meat and set aside.
In a blender, puree the wheat with the addition of a little water.
Place the pureed wheat back into the large plate.
In the same blender, chop the meat.
Mix the meat and wheat and return to the saucepan.
Add about 2 cups water.

title: cheese rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine hot milk, margarine, sugar and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Let cool.
Add egg and yeast.
Gradually add flour to form a stiff dough.
Let rise in warm place until double in size (about 2 hours).
Mash down and make into rolls with a cube of cheese in center of roll.
Be sure dough is sealed around cheese.
Place on greased baking pan and let rise again to about double in size.
Bake in 400° oven until golden brown.

title: yankee pot roast
directions: Rub garlic on roast, then coat with flour. In a large Dutch oven, brown roast in oil. Add tomato juice, carrots, onions, celery, bay leaves, seasoning blend, thyme and pepper; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 3-1/2 hours, turning meat occasionally. Add potatoes; simmer for 30 minutes or until tender. Discard bay leaves. Remove roast and slice; serve with vegetables and gravy.

title: grammy-fannie chapman's chocolate boiled frosting
directions: Bring ingredients to a boil on medium heat.
Let boil until thickens.
Remove from heat and set pan in cold water, stirring constantly, until thick enough to put on cake.
Great frosting for Bundt cake.

title: cola cake
directions: Sift together flour and sugar.
Stir in marshmallows; set aside.
In saucepan, put cola, margarine, shortening and cocoa. Bring to a boil.
Pour over flour mixture.
Stir in buttermilk, soda and eggs.
Pour in greased tube pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve with nacho chips or crackers.

title: ann's mother's barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Put sauce on roasting chicken, pork or beef roast or pork chops.
Makes excellent barbecue sandwiches with roast pork or beef.
Can be doubled or tripled easily.
Freezes well.

title: easy shrimp creole
directions: Cook bacon. Drain some off. Saute veggies and shrimp. Add tomato soup and other ingredients. When ready to serve, add crumbled up bacon. Serve over rice. Serves 4 to 6.

title: fresh apple chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: monkey bread #3
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Combine 3/4 cup sugar and the cinnamon into a paper bag and shake a few pieces of the biscuits at a time.
Pile up pieces into a well-greased Bundt or cake pan. Boil together brown sugar and butter.
When sugar is dissolved, pour hot syrup over the biscuits in the pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Very sweet and fattening!

title: easy deep dish pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Lightly grease jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch or cookie sheet.
Mix baking mix and water until soft dough forms.
Pat dough in bottom and up sides of pan with well floured hands or roll into rectangle 13 x 10-inches and place on cookie sheet; pinch edges of rectangle, forming 3/4-inch rim.
Cook and stir beef, onion, bouillon and garlic until beef is brown and bouillon is dissolved.
Mix tomato sauce and oregano; spread evenly over dough.
Spoon beef mixture evenly over sauce.
Top with mushrooms, green pepper and cheese.
Bake until crust is golden brown, about 20 minutes.

title: baked ziti with homemade sauce
directions: Cook ziti according to package directions.
In large bowl, combine Ricotta, Mozzarella, Romano, egg, salt and pepper.
Place layers of ziti, filling and meat sauce, beginning and ending with the sauce.
Bake in a 350° oven about 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Add all other ingredients; mix well. Pour into glass baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Combine butter and stuffing mix.
Spread half in bottom of baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over butter and stuffing.
Cover with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot cranberry drink
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large pot.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Can brew in large coffee pot.
Put cinnamon and cloves at basket.

title: grilled cheese muffins
directions: Slice muffins in half and spread each half with margarine. Brown the buttered side in a frying pan making a grilled cheese sandwich.
Enjoy!

title: taco salad
directions: Wash and break up lettuce into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients together and toss into a large bowl.
(Crush Doritos in bag before opening.)

title: quick breakfast doughnuts
directions: Heat shortening in deep fat fryer or electric skillet.
Open tube of biscuits and make hole in center of each with fingers. Fry in hot fat, turning to brown on each side.
Drain on paper towel.

title: old-fashioned butter cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream the butter, adding sugar.
Stir in egg, cream and vanilla; mix well. Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Roll out to 1/8 inch thick and cut into shapes.
Bake at 400° for 4 to 8 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Crush enough Doritos to spread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Brown hamburger meat (pour off grease).
Mix. Brown hamburger meat, green chopped chillies, taco sauce or picante sauce, 1 can mushroom soup, milk (measure in soup can) and Ranch Style beans.
Heat together until simmer.
Pour over crushed Doritos.
Sprinkle chips on top and cover with grated cheese.
Bake about 20 minutes until bubbly.

title: egg pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Then add milk, margarine and flour.
Add nutmeg and cinnamon.
Pour into pie crust and bake in a 325° oven until firm.

title: lime cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve lime jello in water and let cool; add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and pour into a mold.
Chill.

title: imperial chicken
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Dip each breast in milk and dredge in bread crumb mixture.
Arrange in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine butter, garlic and lemon juice; drizzle over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until tender.
Yields 6 servings.

title: homemade shake and bake
directions: Mix, then shake and bake.

title: curried seafood chowder
directions: Peel shrimp and devein, if desired.
Melt margarine in large Dutch oven over medium heat.
Add flour and curry powder.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add chicken broth, stirring until smooth.
Stir in clam juice, milk and chopped potatoes.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes until potatoes are tender.
Add fish and shrimp, cook 5 to 10 minutes until shrimp are pink and serve.
Yield:
3 1/2 quarts.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken breasts parmesan
directions: Dip salted and peppered chicken (I cut mine into bite size pieces) into flour and then egg (I add a little milk to the egg mixture).
Roll in mixed bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Fry over low heat about 10 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Cut biscuits into quarters and roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Layer in a Bundt pan.
Pour any remaining sugar mixture into an 8 ounce measuring cup and add 1 teaspoon of cinnamon and enough sugar to fill the cup.
Melt margarine.
Stir nut and sugar mixture into it.
Spoon over the top of biscuits.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs. Stir in baking powder, salt, soda and flour. Mix well. Add oats and coconut.
Mix in corn flakes. Mix in chocolate chips. Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: yummy potatoes on the outdoor grill
directions: Take margarine and spread around on heavy-duty foil.
Cut up potatoes in small chunks.
Add cut up ham or bacon and onions. Season according to taste.
Mix all together and add extra margarine on top.
Bring foil up around the potatoes and seal on top and sides.
Put on the grill for 1 to 1 1/2 hours on low.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix together and pour in hot skillet.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: butter cookies
directions: Combine
ingredients.
Roll
into balls; flatten with a fork. Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Mix eggs and milk well, then add dry ingredients.
Pour 1/3 cup onto hot griddle.
Cook for 2 minutes, then flip.
Cook for 2 more minutes.
Serve.
Top with fresh fruit.

title: raspberry vinaigrette
directions: Place berries in bowl and mash with fork.
Gradually wisk in oil.
Stir in the vinegars, wine and mustard. Season to taste with salt, pepper and sugar.
Makes 1/4 cup dressing.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix in order listed.
Roll into walnut size balls.
Roll in white sugar.
Place on greased sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.
For a crisper cookie, press flat before baking.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits in the water for 5 minutes.
Add the melted garlic cheese, melted margarine and eggs.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° until set, approximately 45 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Dice lettuce and place on bottom of tray. Pour drained salsa on top of lettuce.
Mix together softened cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning mix, until blended together. Pour mixture over salsa.
Top with shredded cheese. Chill.
Serve with taco or tortilla chips.

title: fannie may fudge
directions: Combine butter, sugar and milk in large pan on medium-high heat.
Stir until melted. Add marshmallows and stir until boiling. Turn off heat.
Add chocolate chips, Hershey bars and unsweetened chocolate.
Stir well until mixed. Pour into well-greased jelly roll pan or 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Cool and cut into bite size squares.

title: slush punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in 2 cups hot water.
Dissolve Kool-Aid or Jell-O in 1 cup hot water.
Add remaining ingredients, except ginger ale.
Freeze.
Thaw to a slush before serving and add ginger ale.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars. Blend in oil, eggs and vanilla. Mix dry ingredients together and add to butter-sugar mixture, mixing thoroughly. Roll into small balls and press with cookie press or bottom of glass dipped in sugar. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: debra's fudge patties
directions: Mix together the sugar, syrup, margarine, cocoa, milk, and vanilla extract.
Bring to a boil and boil 2 minutes.
Take off heat and stir in pecans.
Mix with a wooden spoon until thick. This might take 25 to 30 minutes.
Drop from a spoon onto wax paper.

title: pfeffernuss
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Stir in grated orange rind and chopped nuts.
In a separate bowl cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs and molasses.
Stir egg mixture into first mixture to make a smooth dough.
Roll into balls in size of walnuts.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar upon taking from oven.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat sugar, oil and eggs until well mixed.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: chow chow
directions: Sprinkle
green tomatoes and bell peppers with salt and let set
overnight.
Drain
well.
If
too
salty, rinse with water. Mix vinegar, dry mustard, celery seed, turmeric, onion and	sugar together.
Combine	all
ingredients in large pan. Bring to
a slow boil.	Simmer over very low heat for about 20 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: pumpkin drop cookies
directions: Mix egg, sugar, ginger and nutmeg.
Add pumpkin and mix well. Sift together baking powder, salt and flour; add to pumpkin mix alternately with shortening and vanilla.
Add raisins or nuts, if necessary.
Combine all ingredients, mix well and drop by teaspoon onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Frost if you would like.

title: yummy cottage cheese
directions: Spread cottage cheese on diet bread; sprinkle with cinnamon, nutmeg and diet sweetener. Place under broiler.

title: robie's vegetable lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare noodles by package instructions. While noodles are cooking, clean and slice vegetables in small, bite size pieces and stem until slightly tender.
Saute onion and garlic in oil.
Drain excess oil off.
Combine vegetables, onions, garlic and sauce.
Mix tofu in a bowl, should look somewhat like cottage cheese when mixed with fork.
Layer noodles (3 in a row), tofu and then sauce mixture until all ingredients are used.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Cut in the shortening. Add water and make into dough.
Let rest for 15 minutes.
Eggs may be omitted if you so desire.
Roll out dough about 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into 3-inch trapezoid shape.
Fry in grease at 375° until golden brown, then turn them over.
They puff up quite a bit. Serve with honey.
Makes 24.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Place fruit in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over peaches.
Pour margarine over cake mix.
Sprinkle top with nuts and cinnamon. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients 2 minutes, then add egg whites and strawberries.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) pans or 3 (8-inch) pans for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: (dreamy) pecan pie
directions: Melt first 4 ingredients.
Mix milk, sour cream and pudding mix.
Bake pie shell.
Spread on bottom of baked pie shell and bake 10 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with pecans.

title: microwave lemon chicken and rice
directions: Mix all ingredients in 2-quart microwavable casserole; cover. Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Stir; cover.
Cook 3 minutes or until chicken is cooked through.
Stir; cover.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Garnish with chopped parsley.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine rice and milk.
Add salt, sugar and raisins in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring often.
Simmer 1/2 hour, until rice is soft.
Beat eggs; add to hot mixture.
Stir, then remove from heat.
Add vanilla; stir.
May be served warm or cool. Excellent topped with cream and a dash of cinnamon and sugar.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Melt butter in large, hot skillet.
Mix all ingredients and pour half into skillet.
Bake at 425° until lightly browned.

title: spinach and rice
directions: Wash spinach; trim stems and discard.
Chop spinach into small pieces.
Saute onion in olive oil until transparent.
Add spinach to olive oil and onion; cook until spinach softens.
Add tomato sauce, dill, salt, pepper and rice.
Add the water.
After it boils, lower heat to simmer.
Check to see that water is not absorbed too quickly.
If so, add another can until rice cooks.

title: diabetic fruit cookies
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients together for 3 minutes (will thicken).
Let cool.
Cream oleo.
Add the next 3 ingredients; add to fruit mixture.
Sift together the flour, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Blend together and mix well.
Chill dough.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: cream puff hors d'oeuvres
directions: Boil butter and water; add flour and beat well.
Remove from stove and add 1 egg at a time; beat well.
Drop by small teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes after turning oven to 400° for the first 5 minutes.
Let cool and slice each part way through.
Fill with shrimp, chicken or ham salad spread.

title: vbs pizzas
directions: Put pizza sauce on each cracker. Place meat on sauce. Top with shredded cheese. Microwave until cheese melts.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Cook pasta; rinse and cool.
Chop vegetables.
Mix grated Parmesan cheese.
Marinate with Wish-Bone Robusto Italian dressing.

title: hot wings
directions: Cut wing tips off at joint and discard; cut each wing in half at joint.
Arrange wings on rack in broiler pan.
Broil 6 inches from heat for 25 minutes or until browned; stirring occasionally. Transfer to serving dish.
Heat hot pepper sauce, butter and vinegar; drizzle evenly over wings.
Serve with celery sticks and desired choice of dressing.

title: faye's egg custard pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, nutmeg, vanilla and salt well. Stir in milk until blended. Bake at 350° until set (doesn't move when jiggled). Don't overbake.

title: frosted zucchini squares
directions: Mix together until crumbly.
Pat 1/2 of mixture onto 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: double delicious cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over margarine.
Pour condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with chips and press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool and garnish as desired.
(Melt 1 cup semi-sweet chocolate chips with 1 1/2 teaspoons shortening. Drizzle over bars.)
Cut into bars.
Makes 24 to 36 bars.
Time: 10 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients (except 1/4 cup pecans) and refrigerate overnight.
Form into one large ball or 2 small ones and roll balls in chopped pecans.
Serve with crackers or Triscuits.

title: rice malange
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir well.
Pour into slightly greased 2 quart baking dish.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mexican taco dip
directions: Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan. 1st layer - Refried Beans 2nd layer - Avocado (smashed with fork) 3rd layer - Sour Cream mixed with Taco Seasoning 4th layer - Shredded Cheese 5th layer - Diced Tomato 6th layer - Black Olives (optional).
Serve cold with Tortilla Chips.

title: camarones burciaga
directions: Heat olive oil and butter in large skillet over medium heat. Saute scallions and garlic for one minute.
Add shrimp, white wine, Rose's lime juice and red pepper.
Cook over medium heat until shrimp are done (approximately 5 minutes).
Add cilantro 1 minute before cooking is completed.
Serve over cooked pasta with Parmesan cheese.
Serves four hungry people.

title: tomato preserves
directions: Combine
tomatoes,
lemon
and	pectin.
Bring	to full boil. Add sugar and return to full boil.	Stir constantly for 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and continue to stir 1 to 2 minutes. Skim
off
foam.
Should
make
ounce)
jelly glasses. Seal.
(You may use paraffin over these preserves or a tablespoon of boiling water.)

title: baked bananas
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Peel and cut bananas into bite size chunks.
Place bananas in shallow baking dish.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix one cup flour and one heaping tablespoonful Crisco. Cut shortening	into
flour
until
you have a coarse mixture. Add just enough ice water to moisten.
Knead well.
Roll thin.

title: rindfleisch-eintopf(beef stew)
directions: Melt shortening in a Dutch oven.
Add the meat and brown on all sides.
Place the onions on top of the meat.
Mix the flour and seasonings with 1/4 cup water.
Blend with the tomatoes and add the mixture to the Dutch oven.
Bake at 325° about 2 hours, until the meat is fork-tender.
Serve with oven-browned potatoes.

title: walnut bread
directions: In saucepan, melt butter.
Add water and buttermilk.
Heat over low heat to boiling.
In a large bowl, pour liquid over yeast to dissolve.
Add salt, molasses and walnuts.
Add flours, a little at a time, stirring to blend.
On floured counter, knead dough until satiny and smooth.
Let rise in warm place 30 minutes.
Split in half.
Shape into 2 loaves.
Place in 2 loaf pans or on floured baking sheet.
Brush with egg white and place walnut halves on top. Let rise, covered, for 40 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pecan puffs(wedding)
directions: Mix ingredients.
Cut out, or shape into balls and press. Roll in powdered sugar when hot and again when cold.

title: hash brown - ham casserole
directions: Combine sour cream and soup.
Stir in potatoes, ham, American cheese and onion.
Turn into 9 x 13-inch pan; spread evenly. Combine corn flakes and butter.
Sprinkle over potato mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and bake 20 to 25 minutes more.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: dip for fruit
directions: Blend together.
Good with kiwi, cantaloupe, strawberries, etc.

title: chicken divan
directions: Arrange broccoli in a shallow baking pan.
Top with chicken. Combine soup and milk and pour over all.
Top with cheese.
Put onion rings on about 10 minutes before finished baking.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a medium bowl.
Mix well. Place in a greased casserole.
Combine remaining ingredients in a medium bowl.
Mix well.
Place topping evenly over apples.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes or until topping is slightly browned.
Serves 8.

title: chilled vegetable salad
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil in small saucepan over medium heat; cook, stirring often, 5 minutes or until sugar dissolves. Remove dressing from heat and cool 30 minutes. Stir together rest of ingredients in a large bowl; gently stir in dressing. Cover and chill salad for 8 hours. Serve with a slotted spoon. Makes 8 cups. Salad may be stored in an airtight container in the refrigerator for several days.

title: creamy broccoli soup
directions: Saute broccoli, onion and carrots in butter in large saucepan until vegetables are tender.
Stir in milk and soup.
Cook mixture until completely heated.
Sprinkle with pepper and paprika.

title: uncle ken's beer batter
directions: Combine and beat well.
Mixture will thicken as it sets.
Add beer or more finely rolled crackers for correct consistency. Should coat finger when testing.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a well greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: mushroom quiche
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms in oil.
Add salt and lemon juice. Boil out liquid.
Mix eggs and milk.
Stir in mushroom mix.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 30-40 min. at 375°.

title: a doodle dandy
directions: Cook fresh vegetables in oil until tender.
Combine all ingredients and pour into an oiled casserole dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: one meal dish
directions: Use one ramekin and grease with butter.
Layer macaroni, salt, pepper and pieces of butter and then Cheddar cheese.
Make another layer of the same.
Pour milk over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chili st. andrew's
directions: Brown and drain beef and onion.
Add all ingredients except beans.
Cook on low, simmering at least an hour.
Add beans last and heat through.

title: sourdough bread
directions: In large mixer bowl, soften yeast in warm water.
Blend in Sourdough Starter, salt and sugar.
Add 2 1/2 cups flour.
Beat 4 minutes with electric mixer.
Cover; let rise until light and bubbly, about 1 1/2 hours.
Combine soda and 2 1/2 cups flour; stir in dough.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Turn out on floured board and knead 5 to 7 minutes.
Divide dough in half. Cover and let rise 10 minutes.
Shape into 2 round loaves.
Place on slightly greased baking sheet.
With sharp knife, cut slashes across top.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Place pie crust in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place sausage, cheese and onions in pie crust first; then beat eggs and milk well and pour over top.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°, then 30 minutes at 300°.

title: hunt's burgers
directions: Make hamburger into patties.
Put in heated frying pan (with a little water).
Slowly let fry until lightly browned on both sides.
Now simmer with onion rings, Hunt's sauce, water, salt and pepper.
Put lid on and slowly simmer until onions get soft and sauce thickens.
When done, let cool about 5 to 8 minutes.
Put on hamburger buns with some onions and sauce.

title: chili soup
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.

title: baked chicken-amish style
directions: Grind up cornflakes and crackers and mix together (I use a blender).
Mix in the seasonings.
Set aside amount you feel you will need for the amount of chicken you are cooking; store the rest for later use.
Dip chicken in egg/milk mixture and roll in the seasoned crumbs until completely coated.
Bake chicken on cookie sheet for 1 hour at 350°.
Put chicken in covered roaster and bake for an additional hour.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each.
Add chiles, corn, cheeses and seasoning. Blend well. Sift together flour, cornmeal and baking powder.
Add to corn mixture and blend well.
Pour into a greased and floured 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish or 18 muffin cups.
Place in preheated 350° oven and immediately reduce heat to 300°.
Bake bread for 1 hour, muffins for 45 minutes.
Makes 18 muffins or bread.

title: very low-fat eight layer casserole
directions: In a large skillet, cook turkey until brown.
Drain off fat. Stir in tomato sauce, basil, sugar, salt, garlic salt and pepper. Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.

title: nut bread
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 1 hour in greased pans. Makes 2 loaves.

title: cherry almond cake filling
directions: Soften the gelatin in the cold water for 5 minutes.
Place in top of a double boiler over water; stir until completely dissolved.
Add chopped cherries with juice, sugar and salt. Chill until slightly thickened.
Whip cream.
Add almonds, vanilla and almond extract.
Fold into gelatin mixture.
Frost white layer cake or angel food cake.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Grease two 9 x 1 1/2-inch layer pans.
Line bottom with waxed paper. Sift dry ingredients together into a large bowl.
Stir in mayonnaise, then gradually stir in water and vanilla until smooth and blended.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until cake springs back when touched. Cool completely. Remove from pans.

title: dump cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Take 1/2 chopped onion; spread in bottom of electric skillet. Add chicken; take other 1/2 of chopped onion to top of chicken. Spread mushrooms soup over chicken; take onion soup mix and sprinkle over mushroom soup. Add 2 soup cans water. Start out on 300° for 15 minutes. Turn down to simmer to finish cooking about 30 minutes to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice; add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: jalapeno potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes into 1/4-inch slices. Cook potatoes in boiling water about 20 minutes or until tender. Drain and cool slightly.

title: fun cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Combine flour, baking soda and salt. Set aside.
Cream together butter and sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla. Blend in flour mixture. Stir in M&M's and nuts. Drop with teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 11 minutes. Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Peel, slice and boil eggplant until tender.
Drain in colander 10 minutes.
Put in bowl.
Add eggs, milk, seasoning and half of crumbs, cheese and margarine.
Pour into baking dish having mix about 1 inch thick.
Sprinkle top with remaining crumbs and margarine.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until firm.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: cavatini
directions: Fry ground beef, onions and pepper.
Drain off fat.
Add mushrooms, garlic powder, Italian seasoning, spaghetti sauce and sugar.
Heat thoroughly.
Cook shells and add to sauce.
Put in baking dish 9 x 13-inch.
Top with Mozzarella.
Place in oven under broiler until cheese melts and browns a little.
Serve with salad and garlic bread.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased oblong pan.
Mix all ingredients and spread in pan.
Bake in preheated oven until golden brown for 25 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into 2 x 1-inch pieces.
Makes 4 dozen appetizers.

title: sod cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nuts and chips, until well blended.
Add nuts and chips.
Bake on sheet cake pan.
Cool completely before cutting.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pittsburgh potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skins.
When cool, peel and shred coarsely. Shred cheese.
Heat 1/2 cup butter and cheese until almost melted. Remove from heat, stir in sour cream, onion, salt and pepper. Fold in potatoes.
Put into 2-quart casserole and dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cornmeal cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar in a large bowl.
Add egg and beat well. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop dough by teaspoon onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes until lightly brown.
Yields about 3 dozen cookies.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: Mix sweetened condensed milk and water with blender.
Add vanilla pudding and beat until well blended.
Chill for 5 minutes. Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon 1 cup of pudding mixture in a large, glass bowl.
Top with 1/3 of wafers and 1 banana. Repeat layering twice.
Chill thoroughly.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar well, then add other ingredients.

title: cookie raisin puffs
directions: Cream shortening, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Add flour, soda and salt to creamed mixture.
Add cooked raisins. Shape dough into small balls.
Roll each in sugar and place on greased sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 dozen.

title: baked country ham
directions: Step 1:
Soak in cold water with 1 cup sugar and 1 cup vinegar for 8 to 24 hours.
Make sure ham is covered.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Heat in large skillet the oil.
Add and cook until brown, cloves.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook rapidly, uncovered, about 15 minutes or until thickened.
Stir occasionally.
If sauce becomes too thick, add 1/4 to 1/2 cup water.
Serve hot on cooked spaghetti or linguine.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Use greased glass dish.
Place bread as a liner in bottom, then cheese, then sausage.
Sprinkle these evenly over the bread. Mix eggs, milk, salt, mustard and pepper.
Pour egg mixture over bread and sausage.
Chill overnight, then bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 5 to 6 people.

title: chocolate chunk cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, beat brown sugar, sugar, margarine and shortening until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and egg.
Blend well.

title: ham bone soup
directions: Place ham bone in a 2 gallon kettle; add water, tomatoes, parsley, celery, peppercorns, barley, carrots and salt to taste. Boil for 2 hours.
Add cabbage and potatoes.
Cook 30 minutes.

title: crab meat casserole
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix milk and bread crumbs.
Gently stir in crab meat and egg whites.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Place in greased (Pam) 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or 1 1/2-quart dish. Sprinkle with buttered crumbs.
Bake 15 minutes.
Serves 2 generously.

title: deviled crab
directions: Combine lemon juice, eggs and seasonings. Add to crabmeat. Mix lightly. Add mustard. Combine sauce and crab mixture. Mix lightly. Fill individual casseroles or shells. Sprinkle with buttered crumbs. Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: raclette-style cheese
directions: In a small mixing bowl or food processor bowl combine cheeses; let stand to soften.
Add snipped oregano, mustard, white wine, Worcestershire sauce and hot pepper sauce.
Beat with an electric mixer on low speed or cover food processor bowl and process until well combined.
(Mixture will be crumbly.)
Form mixture into a ball.
Shape into a 4 1/2-inch round about 1 inch high.
Wrap in clear plastic wrap and chill several hours or overnight

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Mix cottage cheese, 1/2 cup of the Parmesan cheese and egg. Spread 3/4 cup of the sauce in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Top with 3 lasagna noodles, 1/2 of the cottage cheese mixture, 1/2 of the spinach, 1 cup sauce and 1 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 c. Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 10 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: I use a food processor to grind fresh cranberries.
Mix with the marshmallows and sugar and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Next day before serving, add the remaining ingredients, adding the Cool Whip just before serving.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix well with the next 4 ingredients. Pour into the pie shells.
Freeze.
Serve either frozen or allow to thaw slightly.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Make batter with egg, flour, salt and 4 Tbsp. water. Salt and pepper the pork and coat with batter. Fry until brown on all sides. Simmer with a little water, covered, for about 1 hour.

title: christmas pie
directions: Mix nuts, baking powder and crackers and fold into beaten egg whites.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool well.
Cover with whipped cream.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: christmas fudge
directions: Put all ingredients, except nuts, in a bowl.
Microwave at 50% power until chips are melted (3 to 5 minutes).
Stir once or twice to mix, then stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan and refrigerate until set.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in casserole dish.
Mix other ingredients; pour over oleo.
Add sliced can of peaches.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes.
If apples or peaches are used, you may sprinkle sugar and cinnamon on top.
Serve hot or cold with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: cheese grits
directions: Put water in heavy saucepan and bring to a boil.
Add grits and return to boil, stirring frequently until grits thicken.
Add butter and cheese, stirring until cheese melts.

title: plain sweet roll dough
directions: Soften yeast in the warm water.
Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt; cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast and egg.
Gradually stir in flour to form a soft dough.
Beat vigorously.
Cover and let rise until double (about 2 hours); turn on floured surface and use in any variation.
Either shortening or sugar or both increased to 1/4 cup will make a richer dough.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: In 6-quart pot, saute diced bacon until crisp.
Add onion, celery and green pepper; cook over low heat, 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add tomatoes to veggie mixture.
Drain clams, reserve liquid; set clams aside.
Add water to clam liquid to equal 1-quart.
Pour into pot.
Add salt, pepper, bay leaf and thyme. Bring to boil, reduce heat; simmer covered 45 minutes.
