Add potatoes (more or less to your liking); cover and cook 25 minutes. Add clams; simmer 15 minutes, uncovered.
Add parsley; serve hot with crackers.

title: potato-cheese casserole
directions: Cover potatoes with salted water and bring to a boil; reduce heat and cook about 30 minutes or until tender.
Peel and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Set aside.

title: fish chowder
directions: In kettle brown onion in oleo. Add water and bring to boil. Add potatoes; cook 10 minutes.
Add fish and lemon juice.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Add milk, salt, pepper and parsley.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes at 425° until tender.
Cut in half and scoop out insides into mixing bowl.
Place skins on flat pan.

title: fiesta biscuit bake
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons margarine in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Cut each biscuit into eighths.
Mix with jar of salsa.
Arrange in butter coated pan. Top with onion, green pepper, black olives and cheese. Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes until brown. Cut into squares.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Blend Crisco and sugar; add eggs and remaining ingredients. Do not grease cookie sheets.
Drop by tablespoon on cookie sheet (several inches apart).
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Frost cookie while still hot.

title: vegetable fritters
directions: Saute vegetables in 1 tablespoon butter.
Remove from heat. Mix together sour cream, mustard and eggs.
Gradually beat in cornstarch.
Stir in vegetables.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter in skillet.
Spoon 2 tablespoons fritter batter in skillet.
Cook until lightly browned on one side.
Turn and brown on the other side.
Any combination of vegetables can be substituted.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: orange cake
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add to cake mix. Add oil and eggs, one at a time. Mix well; add coconut. Pour into 9
x 13-inch cake pan and bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Form into balls.
Brown. Drain fat.
Add soup over meat.
Stir.
Simmer 25 to 30 minutes. Serves 6.
May double.
Serve over rice or pasta.

title: fruit pizza(agency winner for best dessert and specialty category)
directions: Cut cookie dough into slices 1/8-inch thick.
Line an ungreased 14-inch pizza pan with slices, overlapping slightly. Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Cool.
Combine softened cream cheese, sugar and vanilla, mixing until well blended.
Spread mixture over crust.
Arrange fruit over cream cheese layer.

title: strawberry preserves from frozen strawberries
directions: Combine berries, sugar and lemon juice in 2-quart glass casserole.
Microwave for about 7 minutes on Roast.
Stir and continue cooking for 15 to 16 minutes more.
Stir in pectin. Cool; put in jars and cover with paraffin.
Do not attempt to melt paraffin in microwave.
Use a double boiler instead.

title: m&m's cookies
directions: Mix sugars and butter until fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add combined flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups of candies.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Press remaining candies into cookies.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: judy's ham rolls
directions: Slice through center of rolls as one piece.
Spread butter and mustard, sprinkle with minced onion and then place slices of ham. Cover with Swiss cheese.
Place top of rolls back into place. Wrap in Reynolds aluminum wrap.
Warm in oven at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Place artichoke hearts (with some of the juice) along with remaining ingredients into blender or food processor.
Blend until smooth.
Place in a baking dish.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: eggs in paper bags
directions: Loop bacon around green stick.
Broil over the fire until almost done.
Shorten bag to about 6 inches.
Place bacon in bag. See that bacon grease saturates bag.
Carefully break egg into bag and on the bacon.

title: zucchini curry soup
directions: Saute onion in 1/2 stick margarine.
Combine with zucchini, curry powder, garlic, and broth.
Simmer 45 to 60 minutes.
Puree in blender or food processor.
Cool and add remaining ingredients, adding milk to get consistency you like.
Chill at least 6 hours. Delicious!

title: the marinated flank steak
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in Ziploc bag.
Score and fold flank steak; add to marinade in bag.
Allow to marinate several hours at room temperature or overnight in refrigerator.
(If marinated in refrigerator, allow to come to room temperature before cooking.)
Marinade can be reused.

title: coffee bars
directions: Mix together and spread on cookie sheet.
Top with nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
No frosting needed.

title: tasty eggplant
directions: In a large frying pan, heat olive oil and saute eggplant and onions until cooked through.
Add tomatoes, garlic and ginger and cook another 2 to 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for another 5 minutes.

title: jalapeno hush puppies
directions: Combine cornmeal, salt and pepper.
Stir in the onion, jalapeno pepper and buttermilk just until combined.
Let stand for a few minutes to thicken.
Drop hush puppies, using two spoons, a few at a time, into the hot (365°) oil.
Fry for 3 to 4 minutes or until golden, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hush puppies warm with catfish.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer beans in dish or pan.
Layer onion.
Layer tomatoes. Mash avocados and season to taste for next layer.
Mix sour cream, taco seasoning and salad dressing together for next layer.
Top with cheese and olives.
Refrigerate overnight or at least several hours.
Serve with chips or eat by itself; it's good either way.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Add enough mayonnaise or sour cream to mix.
Let stand 1 to 2 hours before stuffing celery.

title: french canadian split pea soup
directions: Combine peas, ham, onion, bouillon, 8 cups water, 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper in kettle.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring often.
If using ham bone, remove meat, dice and return to kettle along with the carrots and celery.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Cook bacon until crisp, drain and crumble (I use the microwave).
Stir in the bacon, cream and butter to the soup and heat through.

title: colossal cookie
directions: In a small bowl, mix flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.

title: brownies
directions: Mix well and spread to 1/2-inch thickness.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: beef stew
directions: Mix together and pour over meat in ungreased casserole.
Bake 2 hours at 300°.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: tater tots casserole
directions: Press fresh hamburger into 7 x 12-inch baking dish.
Add 1 can of chicken soup as it comes from can; spread over meat.
Scatter onion over evenly.
Add can of corn, undrained.
Cover with Tater Tots.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Be sure dish is covered with foil.

title: irish stew
directions: In a large saucepan, brown meat and onion in oil.
Add boiling water and tomato sauce to meat and simmer 1 hour.
Add carrots, potatoes, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Cook until carrots and potatoes are done.

title: betty amick's cheddar cheese soup
directions: Mix cornstarch with cheese.
In 4 to 6-quart saucepan bring water to a boil.
Add cheese mixture, stirring constantly until cheese melts and mixture becomes smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and garlic.
In skillet, saute vegetables and ham individually in butter.
Add to cheese mixture. Reheat, stirring, and add half and half.

title: old fashioned chicken noodle soup
directions: Combine all ingredients, except noodles, in large pot and cook about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Skim off the foam that develops when hen comes to a boil.
Remove chicken and strain broth.
Remove grease from top of broth, using a ladle, or chill broth until fat congeals, then remove. (I like to use one of those pitchers which allows you to pour off the broth and discard the grease.)

title: cauliflower broccoli medley
directions: Combine vegetables in large bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients except bacon; add to vegetables, tossing gently. Chill several hours or overnight.
Garnish with bacon.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Arrange sliced apples into unbaked pie shell.
Mix the remaining 6 ingredients together and pour over apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: speedy squashickles
directions: Combine squash, onions and green peppers in a large bowl. Sprinkle with salt.
Let stand for 1 hour; drain.
Combine sugar, vinegar, mustard seed and celery seed in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Remove from heat.
Add vegetables; mix gently.
Ladle into hot sterilized 1 pint jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Seal with 2-piece lids.
Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.
Makes 5 pints.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, 1/2 cup butter, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese; stir well.
Spoon into a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole. Crush cereal and stir in remaining butter.
Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.
Garnish with lemon twists and parsley, if desired.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: date pudding
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour 1 cup brown sugar, flour, dates, nuts, milk and baking powder into pan after mixing well.
Boil syrup (boiling water, 3 cups brown sugar and oleo) 5 minutes. Pour syrup mixture over batter in pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: orange-honey dressing
directions: Combine dry ingredients in 1-quart mixer bowl.
Add honey, lemon juice, vinegar and orange concentrate; blend well.
Beating constantly, slowly add oil; beat 5 minutes longer at medium speed or blend all ingredients in blender for 20 seconds at high speed. Chill.
Shake before serving.
Makes 1 pint.

title: florentine turkey or chicken
directions: Early In The Day:
Cook spinach as label directs. Drain well. Arrange in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: italian cookies
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, orange juice and vanilla.
Gradually add flour, baking powder and juice.
Bake at 375°.

title: "aunt sara's pickles"
directions: Cut pickles in chunks or use sliced dills.
Drain them and place in a large glass jar or crock.
Add the sugar and seasonings.
They make their own juice.
Refrigerate for a few days, stirring occasionally to dissolve sugar.
Then they may be put in smaller jars for ease in handling.
They turn out good and crisp.

title: country baked beans
directions: Brown bacon, ground beef, chopped onion and garlic to taste in skillet.
Put in crock-pot with remaining ingredients.
Cook on high 4 hours or on low all day.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Warm water to lukewarm.
Add yeast to soften.
Scald the milk and add sugar, salt and shortening and add 1/2 of the flour and beat well.
Add the softened yeast and egg and mix carefully. Add remaining flour and mix until a soft dough forms.
Turn out on a lightly floured bread board and knead until it becomes satiny in appearance.
Oil a large bowl and place dough in bowl. Cover well with waxed paper.
Bring to room temperature.
Shape into rolls and cover with waxed paper.
Allow to rise until double in size.
Cook in preheated oven at 425° for 15 to 25 minutes.

title: carameled marshmallows
directions: Melt butter; add milk and caramels and melt.
Dip frozen marshmallows in caramel mix with toothpicks and roll in Rice Krispies.
Place on wax paper to set.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados in a medium-sized bowl with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix in bowl.

title: chicken, special
directions: Mix together and pour over the chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Tastes like barbecue chicken.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix
all
ingredients,
except
soup.
Make into balls; pour into
baking dish.
Pour diluted soup over meatballs and bake 1 1/2
hours
in
a 350° oven.
May substitute 1 package Lipton's onion soup for onion and salt.

title: spirited punch
directions: Brew tea for 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags.
Add cider, lemon juice, sugar and spices.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Remove spices.
Add wine.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Prepare chicken tenders according to package directions. Place tenders in large skillet. Add sweet and sour sauce, pineapple and vegetables. Heat, covered, and simmer 25 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Serve over rice.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Warm soup; add other ingredients.
Place in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
The next day, add crushed potato chips on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
(Freezes well.)

title: turkey stuffing
directions: Slowly fry sausage and onion. Bring to a boil the soup mix and water. Cool. Break up bread and mix with sausage, soup mix and sage.
Stuff into turkey.
Put remaining in a pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix and put in greased casserole.
Cook 45 minutes at 400°.

title: old time egg pie
directions: Beat eggs real well.
Add sugar; stir in well.
Add flour and vanilla flavoring, stirring well.
Add milk and pour into uncooked pie crust.
Bake at 300° to 325° for about 30 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Use a 10 x 15-inch pan.
Spray pan with Pam or other nonstick spray.
Spread the can of cherry pie filling in pan.
Spread can of pineapple on top of cherries.
Spread that with the dry cake mix.
Pour on the melted butter.
Top with nuts and then coconut. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rum sausages
directions: Bake or fry sausage until well done; drain and cool.
Cut each sausage into 3 pieces; set aside.
Place sugar, teriyaki and rum into saucepan.
Cook until sugar has dissolved and syrup comes to boil.
Remove from heat.
Place sausage and syrup into ovenproof dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 25 minutes.
Drain and serve hot with toothpicks or serve with syrup in a chafing dish. Reserve syrup to store any leftovers.
These keep in refrigerator 2 weeks.
Reheat to serve.
May be frozen.
Makes 48 pieces.

title: holiday french toast
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl.
Add orange juice and all ingredients, except bread and powdered sugar.
Dip bread in egg mixture and place in baking dish.
Pour any remaining egg mixture on top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight, turning once.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Place pecans in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle coconut over pecans.
Mix cake according to package directions.
Pour over coconut and pecans. Melt oleo and mix with cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Spread on cake.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: bryan's cheesecake
directions: Mix envelope of Dream Whip according to directions.
Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in Dream Whip.
Pour into crust.
Refrigerate.

title: mulled wine
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a Dutch oven over medium heat; bring to a boil, reduce heat, and simmer 5 minutes.
Add wine; simmer 10 minutes.
Pour mixture through a wire-mesh strainer into a container; discard solids.
Makes 10 servings.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: In an electric skillet, place a small amount of oil; place on medium heat.
While the skillet is heating, slice the chicken, the pepper and the onion and drain the juice off of the mushrooms. When the skillet is hot, place the green pepper, onion and mushrooms in.
Let these cook for about 2 to 3 minutes and then add the chicken and 1 teaspoon garlic powder.
Cover and let cook about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Next, grate the Cheddar cheese. When the 10 minutes are up, turn the electric skillet to low to keep warm.
Place some of the chicken mixture and some of the Cheddar cheese in a tortilla; roll it up and serve.
Makes 10 fajitas.

title: tenderizing marinade
directions: Combine oil, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, vinegar, lemon juice, garlic, sugar, salt and pepper in a glass jar.
Shake and mix well.
Pour over meat and let marinate in refrigerator for 4 hours or overnight.

title: campfire stew
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add soup.
Do not dilute and mix.
Serve with a green salad.
Makes a quick, nutritious meal.

title: cherry devilicious cake
directions: Cream Crisco and 1 cup sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks 1 at a time, beating after each.
Stir in vanilla.
Sift together flour, cocoa, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with water; beat well after each addition.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form; gradually add 3/4 cup sugar; beat to stiff peaks.
Fold into batter.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Top each serving with dollop of Cream Cheese Topper and warm Cherry Sauce.

title: fried apples
directions: *Any kind except the green apples.
Amount of apples depends upon the amount of people.

title: pecan chew
directions: In a large heavy pot, add all the ingredients.
Cook to a hard boil stage (260°) on top of stove.
Quickly add pecans and beat one minute.
Pour onto a buttered cookie sheet 2/3 full.
Let cool and cut into bite size pieces.
Great at Christmastime!

title: crab soup
directions: Melt 1 stick butter and saute onion.
Set aside.
In a large pan melt 1 tablespoon butter; add flour.
Gradually add half and half to make white sauce.
Add milk.
Add sherry, crabmeat and onions.
Cook all day until thick on low heat.
Add Old Bay seasoning to taste just before serving.

title: roquefort cheese ball
directions: Beat together the cheese until very smooth.
Stir in the onion, Worcestershire sauce and pepper sauce.
Mix well.
Chill for about an hour.
Shape into 1 large ball or 2 small ones and roll in the nuts.
Cover well and refrigerate until serving time. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix well and put in a pie shell. Bake in oven until brown and knife inserted near center comes out clean.

title: cherry cherry punch
directions: Dissolve the gelatin and sugar in boiling water.
Add pineapple juice, concentrates and cold water.
Add ginger ale and mix well. Yields 60 (4 ounce) servings.

title: quick jell-o salad
directions: Chop cucumber, onion, and pecans very fine. Add cottage cheese and salad dressing. Dissolve Jell-O in 1/2 c. hot water. Pour immediately over other ingredients. It will set in a very short time. * One of my favorites from my childhood days.

title: sure-jell easy 3-step strawberry jam
directions: Mix strawberries and sugar thoroughly.

Set aside 10 minutes. Stir Sure-Jell fruit pectin with water in saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat. Stir mixtures together until sugar is completely dissolved and no longer grainy, about 3 minutes.
Pour into plastic containers; cover.
Let stand at room temperature for 24 hours.
Jam is now ready to use.
Store in refrigerator or freeze extra containers. Thaw in refrigerator.
Makes about 4 (1 cup) containers.

title: pasty pie
directions: Make pie crust following a 3 crust recipe.
Roll out and line both dishes; fill.
Mix all ingredients together.
Makes 1 (11 x 15-inch) Pyrex dish and one large pie plate.
Line bottom of both and fill with mixture; top with crust, sealing edges well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour for pie plate and 1 hour and 15 minutes for large Pyrex dish.

title: st. patrick's day dessert
directions: Mix cookie crumbs and oleo.
Set aside 2/3 cup for topping. Press rest into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.

title: hot pickled okra
directions: Have jars hot.
Put 1/2 teaspoonful of dill seed in each jar. Put okra in jar.
Cut up 1 red hot pepper and 1 green hot pepper. Add another half teaspoon of dill seed.
Pour vinegar over and seal.
Turn upside-down.
Wait 3 weeks before eating.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Stir rice and water together first, so they cook properly.
Layer ingredients in the order listed.
Cover dish with foil and bake at 350° for 1 3/4 hours.
Remove foil for the last 15 minutes of baking time to lightly brown cheese.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients. Mix eggs and oil. Add to dry ingredients, then add zucchini. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10-inch pie plate.
Cook and stir ground beef and onion in a 10-inch skillet over medium heat until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread in plate. Beat milk, eggs and baking mix until smooth (15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand mixer).
Pour into plate.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until knife is clean after being inserted in the middle, 5 to 8 minutes. Cool 5 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: heavenly jello
directions: Mix jello and water.
Add other ingredients, except Cool Whip and nuts.
Let set.
After cooled, stir in the Cool Whip and nuts.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar; beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold in vanilla and coconut. Drop by teaspoonfuls, 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 325°.
Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet.

title: dinner rolls
directions: In a separate bowl combine yeast and warm water.
Now in a large bowl place sugar, salt and warm milk.
Stir in yeast and water mixture.
Mix in shortening and eggs.
Sift in 2 cups of flour and keep adding until a ball is formed and you can easily knead the dough with hands.
Cover with towel and let rise until double in size, about 2 1/2 to 3 hours).
Punch down dough when doubled in size; break off in roll size pieces and let rise again on a greased baking sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven until brown.

title: jennie's fresh apple cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil, vanilla, eggs, lemon juice. salt and cinnamon in mixing bowl and mix well.
Mix flour and soda and fold in.
Beat well.
Add apples and pecans and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: easy beef or pork roast
directions: Mix soup mix, mushroom soup and cola together.
Place roast in pan and pour liquid mixture over roast.
Cover and bake in 300° oven for 3 to 4 hours.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Prepare jello with 2 cups water.
Refrigerate until it begins to jell.
Add remaining ingredients and pour in pan, bowl or mold. Refrigerate.

title: easy elegant chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups, butter and sherry.
Pour about 1 cup over the rice and blend to moisten.
Put rice on bottom of a large shallow casserole (large enough so that breasts can be placed side by side.)
Place chicken on top of rice.
Pour remaining soup mixture over chicken.
Put cheese and almonds on top and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 2 1/2 hours at 275°.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: frieda's potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Peel while warm.
Slice and add vinegar.
Let sit for 1 hour.
Add celery, onion, eggs, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Makes 12 servings.

title: blueberry pancakes
directions: Combine milk, corn syrup, corn oil and egg in mixing bowl. Add pancake mix; stir until dry ingredients are moistened. Batter will be lumpy.
Stir in blueberries and cottage cheese carefully.
Pour 1/4 cup batter onto griddle; cook until brown, turning once.
Repeat cooking until all batter is used.
Yields 8 pancakes.

title: 3 bean baked beans
directions: Saute beef, bacon and onion.
Drain beans except pork and beans and add to meat mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well and pour into large bean pot or baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Beat 2 whole eggs; add jello, sugar and pineapple and bring to a boil.
Let boil about 1 minute.
Let cool.
Whip chilled milk and add to other mixture; put in pie shells.

title: pizza spread
directions: Mix together. Put in a 9 x 13 dish. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. You can also put in crock-pot on low. Serve with Tostitos.

title: christmas morning strata
directions: Night before serving, grease a 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish. Cook pork sausage meat, stirring frequently to break up sausage until thoroughly cooked and no longer pink.
Using slotted spoon, remove sausage to paper towel to drain.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add vinegar and water; boil 5 minutes.
Add beets and let stand over low heat 30 minutes.
Just before serving, bring to boiling point and add butter.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate shake
directions: Pour the first 3 ingredients into a blender and blend.
Pour into a glass and top with the whipped cream.

title: rice-chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook Rice-A-Roni and broccoli according to directions.
Layer rice, chicken, broccoli and cheese.
Mix soup and milk. Pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: carrot-cucumber relish
directions: Grind all vegetables.
Sprinkle with salt and let stand 3 hours.
Drain.
Bring vinegar, water and sugar to a boil.
Add vegetables and spices.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Seal while hot in sterilized jars.

title: biscuits(from the parsonage kitchen)
directions: Note:
Use enough milk to make a very soft, tacky dough, about one cup.
Butter or margarine is used as needed for brushing tops of biscuits as they come from the oven.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put cake mix into mixing bowl.
Add 2 eggs and vegetable oil; mix well.
(Optional:
Nuts, raisins or chocolate chips, may be added.)
Drop by teaspoonfuls of dough onto an ungreased cookie sheet. Space about 2-inches apart.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain well. In a 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole dish, mix spinach, sour cream and onion soup mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove.
Crumble onion rings and sprinkle over top.
Bake again for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: creamy pralines
directions: Cook together sugar, milk and cream of tartar, stirring constantly until it forms a soft ball.
Add pecans and heat.
Drop onto wax paper.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Place strawberries in your favorite cooked crust.
Cook sugar, jello, flour, water and red food color until thick and transparent.
Cool completely and pour over strawberries in cooked pie crust and top with your favorite topping.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Pour oil in 9 x 13-inch baking pan, cover bottom.
Add cake mix, eggs and water. Stir in pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, take cake from oven and let sit for 5 to 10 minutes.
Punch holes in cake with end of wooden spoon and pour fudge topping over cake into holes.
Cool cake.
Frost with Cool Whip.

title: pecan crunch fudge
directions: Combine brown sugar, butter and evaporated milk in a 3-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches soft ball stage (238°).
Remove from heat; stir in butterscotch morsels and Marshmallow Creme.
Beat vigorously with a wooden spoon until mixture is smooth and just begins to cool. Stir in chopped pecans, brickle chips and vanilla.
Spread mixture evenly into 2 buttered 8-inch square pans.
Cool completely and cut into squares.
Gently press a pecan half on each square of fudge, if desired.
Store in an airtight container.

title: rich pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling, salted water according to package directions.
Drain; rinse and drain again.
Cool.
Place lettuce in bottom of a 2-quart casserole; sprinkle with salt and pepper. Top with macaroni.
Sprinkle egg slices with salt; layer atop macaroni.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add flour and water and bring to a boil.
Add cheese, eggs and broccoli.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Crumble Ritz crackers on top and dab with butter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rhubarb shortcake
directions: Put rhubarb in bottom of 8 x 9-inch pan.
Cream 3/4 cup sugar with butter.
Add flour, milk, baking powder and salt.
Pour this mixture over rhubarb.
Mix 1 cup sugar with cornstarch and cinnamon.
Sprinkle this over mixture in pan.
Pour 1 cup boiling water over all.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, onions, soup and sour cream in a bowl.
Mix melted butter with not quite a package of stuffing mix.
Cover long baking dish with part of the stuffing mixture.
Spread squash mixture, then the rest of the stuffing mixture. Bake at 300° until bubbles in center.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix pie ingredients well before pouring into pie crust.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes, then lower temperature to 325° and bake for 40 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix pork and beans with all ingredients and bake in 250° oven until hot throughout.
Brown meat and onions; drain well and add to bean mixture.

title: mexican rice
directions: In a frying pan with a little oil, just enough to cover the bottom of the pan, place rice.
Brown (actually more like "tan") the rice.
In a blender place the onion, cloves, bouillon cube, celery salt, seasoned salt, black pepper and can of tomato sauce. Blend until smooth.
Add to browned rice, then add enough water to cover rice.
Remember 1 cup rice to two cups liquids.
Bring to a boil, cover then simmer until all the liquid is evaporated.
Fluff with fork and serve.

title: scalloped carrots
directions: Boil carrots until tender and drain.
Saute onion in 3 tablespoons oleo and add to carrots.
Add soup, grated cheese, salt and pepper; mix well.
Place in baking dish and top with the dressing mix which has been tossed with 1/3 cup melted oleo.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: veal and peppers
directions: In a large frying pan, melt 2 teaspoons shortening and lightly brown veal cubes.
Add whole tomatoes and juice, sliced red peppers, green peppers, mushrooms, onion and basil.
Add the seasonings, the salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Simmer for approximately 1 1/2 hours or until veal is tender.
Just before serving, add shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Serve and enjoy!
Serves 4 people.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix in a small saucepan over medium heat.
Melt margarine; add onions and garlic.
Cook 5 minutes or until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat to low; simmer 10 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cherry nut ice cream
directions: Scald evaporated milk, water and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs. (A small amount of hot mixture added to eggs will keep them from curdling when added to hot mixture.)
Add 1/2 gallon milk or milk and whipping cream.
Add chopped cherries and pecans and pour in freezer and freeze.
Add additional milk to freezer container if the mixture does not fill to full line.
Freeze according to freezer directions.

title: italian cookies(grandma's recipe)
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Then add dry ingredients. Shape into loaves with well down the center.
Roll in seeds and put jam in center of well.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.
Remove from oven, cut in slices and separate.
Return to oven for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: nut & honey crunch o's brittle
directions: Foil line 17 x 14-inch cookie sheet.
Lightly coat with vegetable spray; set aside.
In heavy 12-inch frypan over medium heat, cook peanuts, margarine, sugar, corn syrup and water, stirring constantly, until mixture starts to boil.
Cook and stir about 12 minutes longer or until peanuts just start to brown. Remove from heat.
Carefully stir vanilla and almond flavoring into hot mixture.
Add Nut & Honey cereal and gently prepared cookie sheet.
Cool completely; break into pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: cheeseburger loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Line loaf pan with waxed paper and place 1/2 cup grated cheese on bottom of pan. Place half of meat loaf mixture over cheese; top with another 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Cover with remaining meat.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.
Allow to stand 10 minutes before removing from pan. Serves 4 to 6.

title: rainy day barbecue franks
directions: In saucepan melt margarine.
Add onion; slowly cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients except franks, cooking slowly, uncovered, about 30 minutes.

title: honey dressing for fruit
directions: Blend all ingredients except cream in top of double boiler; cook over hot (not boiling) water for 15 minutes until thickened. Cover, cool in refrigerator until chilled and fold in whipped cream.

title: easy liver pate
directions: Mash liverwurst.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Mix well!
Turn pate out onto waxed paper.
Form into a 5 x 3-inch rectangle.
Chill 30 minutes.
Spread sides and top of pate with the softened cream cheese.
Chill 30 minutes longer.
Serve with crackers.
Yields about 12 ounces.
Try at your next cocktail party!

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a large bowl and refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: pink champagne
directions: Blend together softened cream cheese and sugar.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch dish and freeze. Cut into squares when ready to serve.
Can be used as a side dish or dessert.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix coconut and milk.
Set aside.
Mix eggs and sugar.
Add melted butter and mix well.
Add coconut and milk mixture.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Use deep dish for pie crust.
Pour mixture into pie crust and bake at 350° until firm.

title: pecan caramel thumbprints
directions: In food processor chop 1 1/4 cups of pecans and place in a small bowl.
Put remaining 1/2 cup pecans and sugar in processor and pulse until nuts are finely ground.
Add butter and eggs, process until smooth.
Add flour, baking powder and salt; pulse just until blended.
Scrape dough into a bowl.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Butter a pizza pan and spread cookie dough onto the pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not overbake!
Cool.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Spread over cooled cookie crust.
Top with assorted fresh fruits.
Dot with Cool Whip, if desired.
Be certain to keep refrigerated.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Cook and stir hamburger and onion in margarine until light brown; stir in flour, salt, garlic powder, pepper and mushrooms. Cook, stirring constantly for 5 minutes.
Stir in soup; heat to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and heat for about 15 minutes on low.
Simmering boil noodles according to directions on package. Serve mixture over cooked noodles.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown bacon, ground meat and onion.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: microwave chocolate crackles
directions: Microwave butter on High 45 to 60 seconds until melted.
Add cocoa, blend well; beat in sugar, baking powder, salt, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Refrigerate at least 8 hours until firm.

title: buster bar dessert
directions: Crush Oreos and mix with butter.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Pat down
firmly.
Spread softened ice cream over cookie layer. Freeze
until
firm.
Spread
fudge
topping
over ice cream layer.
Sprinkle
peanuts over topping.
Cover with Cool Whip. Freeze; set out 20 to 30 minutes before serving.

title: pear salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cream cheese, softened so it will mix well.
Add mayonnaise and let cool.
Add pears and pineapple.
Whip the Dream Whip according to package and fold in. Chill at least 6 hours.

title: seasoned okra snack
directions: Combine cumin, chili powder, garlic powder and salt in a bowl. Mix well.
Cook okra according to package directions.
Pour into a big bowl.
Evenly sprinkle seasoning blend over okra.
Toss gently.
Serve immediately.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix and chill until ready for use.

title: tropical strawberry filling(kid's sandwiches; prep. time: 5 minutes)
directions: In a small bowl, combine the cream cheese and pineapple.
Stir until well mixed.
Stir in banana and coconut.
Makes 2 sandwiches. Your choice of bread.
Yields 2 servings.

title: lee's spiced tea
directions: Boil 10 minutes and drop in tea bags.

title: poor man's dish
directions: Peel tomatoes.
Combine sugar, salt and water; add to tomatoes.
Stew until tomatoes are tender; let cool.
Add broken biscuits to cooked, warm tomatoes.

title: ye ole dump cake
directions: Dump pineapple and juice into a (9 x 11 or 13-inch) baking dish.
Add cherry pie filling, spreading evenly over pineapple. Sprinkle dry cake mix over fruit.
Top with nuts and butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until brown.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: caramel icing
directions: Melt butter and
brown	sugar.	Bring
to a boil.
Stir for 2 minutes constantly.
Add
milk and bring back to a boil; cool. Beat in powder sugar until smooth.

title: mother's potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on until done, but firm.
When cool, remove skins and slice thin.
In one bowl, mix vinegar, oil, water, sugar, salt and pepper.
In another bowl, put onions and parsley.
Add cut potatoes alternately with onions, parsley and vinegar mix.
Toss from pan to pan to mix.
Stirring well, mush potatoes.
Let set at least 24 hours in refrigerator before serving.

title: bar b. q. sprinkle
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Sprinkle over meat as it bakes or is grilled.
Delicious over
pork
chops and chicken.	Prepare ahead; double recipe for later use.

title: oatmeal and pecan cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add vanilla and beat eggs.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add oats and nuts to other ingredients and mix.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly brown.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: caramel cornflake ring
directions: Stir, melt and cook brown sugar, corn syrup, milk and butter to the soft-ball stage at 238 degrees.
Place 4 c. of cornflakes in a large buttered mixing bowl.
Stir in the hot syrup mixture until blended.
Pack the flakes in a buttered 8-inch ring mold. Cool. Invert and serve with sugared or stewed fruit.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: In a bowl, cream together the brown sugar, shortening and peanut butter, beating until the mixture is light and fluffy. Beat in the egg and stir in the flour, baking soda and salt.
Form tablespoons of the dough into balls.
Transfer balls to baking sheets.
Flatten with the tines of a fork, making a crosshatch pattern.
Bake in batches in the middle of a preheated 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden.
Cool on racks.

title: grandma's hot water bread
directions: Pour boiling water over cornmeal to make a thick mush.
Add butter and mix well.
Form into patties while hot and fry in hot oil.

title: cheesy vegetable soup
directions: In medium pan, cook onion in oleo until tender.
Add corn, broccoli, carrots and water.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat. Cover and simmer 10 minutes, until vegetables are tender.
Stir in soup, milk, cheeses and dash of pepper.
Cook and stir over medium heat until cheeses are melted.

title: copper pennies
directions: Peel and slice carrots 1/4-inch thick.
Cook until tender (10 minutes).
Slice onion thin, same with pepper.
Divide onion in rings.
Drain carrots; mix with onion and pepper.
Boil sugar, oil, soup, salt and pepper for 1 minute.
Pour over carrots. Store in refrigerator.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks one at a time.
Add soda and salt to flour and sift 2 more times.
Then add flour mixture and sour cream alternately to the butter and sugar mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan or Bundt pan at 350° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours or until toothpick comes out clean.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar if desired.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: creme puffs
directions: Boil water and add Crisco. Add flour and salt; stir vigorously until paste. Cool. Add 1 egg at a time; beat until smooth. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: brown mountain cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Sift flour and add. Dissolve soda in 1/2 cup water.
Add buttermilk, cocoa, dissolved soda water and vanilla.
Makes 3 layers.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: crock pot navy beans
directions: Soak beans in 4 cups water in refrigerator 8 - 24 hours. Drain, rinse, and put into crock pot.
Mix next 6 ingredients with 1 cup water.
Pour over beans, and stir to coat beans.
Press ham hock down into beans.
Cover and cook 10 - 12 hours on low until beans are tender.

title: flounder in lemon-dill sauce(serves 4)
directions: *Purchase fresh or frozen flounder fillets.
Thaw frozen flounder fillets.

title: fudge pies
directions: Melt butter, then mix all by stirring well.
Do not beat.
Put in 2 pie shells.
Cook like chess or custard pie.

title: guadalupe potatoes
directions: Mix potatoes, onions, bell peppers and margarine together. Season with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Wrap in tinfoil and bake on the grill until done or place in a large buttered casserole dish and bake in oven at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: fiesta salad in tortilla cups
directions: Spray 10-inch skillet with Pam cooking spray.
Heat over medium heat for 1 minute.
Add beef, onion, chili powder and garlic powder.
Cook until beef is browned and onion tender.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup, water, rice and vinegar; heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low.
Cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order given in dishpan.
Drop by tablespoon or ice cream scoop on greased cookie sheet; flatten with a spoon. Bake at 350° for 9 to 10 minutes.

title: toffee bars
directions: Preheat over 350 degrees.
On a 13 x 9 x 2 pan break graham crackers into 4's.
Arrange one flat layer.
Sprinkle pecans over top.

title: peanut butter krispie bonbons
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and roll into balls (a small cookie scoop is good).
While rolling balls, in a glass double boiler (it holds the heat better), melt chips and chocolate bar with the lecithin.
Coat balls in chocolate mixture.
Place on wax paper on a cookie sheet.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet and store in covered container.
Leftover chocolate mix with Krispies, nuts or raisins.
Put into a dish and refrigerate overnight; remove and cut.

title: sausage and noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Brown sausage and onions together. Add cheese, soup and milk.
Simmer until cheese melts.
Mix with noodles and serve.

title: spiced peaches
directions: Simmer together for 10 minutes 3/4 cup water, vinegar, sugar and spices.
Remove from heat.
Strain and discard cloves.
Mix with Jell-O.
Add remaining water; chill until very thick.
Fold in peaches.
Pour into a 1-quart mold.
Chill until firm.
Makes 4 servings.

title: surprise pancake and syrup
directions: Mix pancake mix according to directions on box, but add a few drops of food coloring.
Cook as usual.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except for butter and 1/4 cup Parmesan.
Place in 2 1/2-quart casserole dish and dot with butter and Parmesan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Pour over chicken mixture and bake.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Last 15 minutes, dot with butter and sprinkle with bread crumbs.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, pecans and oleo; pat out in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cook for 20 minutes at 375°.
Cream the cream cheese and sugar; blend in 1 cup of Cool Whip.
Spread over the cool first layer.
Mix pudding with milk; beat until it begins to thicken. Pour over second layer.
Spread Cool Whip on top of this (sometimes it takes part of another carton).
Sprinkle chopped pecans on top, if you like.

title: potato surprise
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix with sour cream, onion, pepper and soup. Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread frozen potatoes in pan; pour margarine mixture over top of potatoes.
Layer the cheese over that, then cover with crushed corn flakes.
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes at 350°, until cheese bubbles.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough on pizza pan.
Bake using directions on package.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese and whipped cream together. Spread desired amount on cooled cookie dough.
Place fruit on top of cream cheese and whipped cream.
Serve immediately.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together, then alternate flour and milk until gone.
Make sure mixture is creamy.
Add all 5 flavors, then mix well.
Pour into cake pan, all but about 5 or 6 muffins.
Bake at 350° for about 40 to 45 minutes, or until middle is done.

title: holiday party egg nog
directions: Be sure you have a large enough container for mixing and storing in ice.

title: dirt
directions: Chop cookies in a blender 3 or 4 at a time and set aside.
Mix butter, powdered sugar and cream cheese and set aside.
Mix pudding and milk and Cool Whip.
Combine butter mixture with pudding mixture.
Layer 1/3 of the cookies and 1/2 pie filling, then 1/3 cookies and 1/2 filling.
Top with rest of the cookies. Put into freezer overnight.
Add silk flowers or gummie worms.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut cauliflower in bite size pieces; slice radishes and chop onions.
Combine all vegetables and add dressing.

title: blueberry nut crunch cake
directions: Grease pan.
Mix pineapple, blueberries, sugar (3/4 cup), cake mix, margarine and pecans.
Cook in 350° oven for 45 minutes. Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar on top of cake.

title: impossible vegetable pie
directions: Grease pie plate and bake at 400°.
The Bisquick makes the crust.

title: moist muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl.
In a small bowl, beat egg, milk, oil and vanilla.
Add carrots, zucchini, pecans and raisins to liquid mixture.
Mix.
Then, add all to dry ingredients.
Blend together until all ingredients evenly moistened.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Combine all ingredients except sauce in large bowl and mix well.
Shape into 1 inch balls; cover and refrigerate or freeze until ready to bake.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Set balls on ungreased baking sheet and bake until golden brown, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with Mustard Sauce.
Makes 70 appetizers.

title: diced apple cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add remainder and mix well. Bake in greased loaf pan 1 hour at 325°.

title: french toast
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together in medium mixing bowl. Dip bread in the mixture.
Preheat skillet with small amount of butter at a time.
Makes about 8 to 10 slices.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: Cream oleo and shortening; add brown sugar, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Sift and add flour; add oatmeal, chocolate chips, pecans, Rice Krispies and coconut.
Using 1/4 cup per cookie or ice cream scoop, put on ungreased cookie sheet, 6 to a sheet.
For crunchy and hard cookies, cook 15 minutes at 450°.
For soft and chewy cookies, cook 6 to 7 minutes at 425° and let cool 5 minutes before removing from sheet.
Makes 30 to 40 cookies.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Very easy to prepare and very good!

title: carrot cake
directions: Bake at 350° in layers for 25 to 30 minutes or maybe a little longer (three 9-inch layer pans) or at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes for a tube pan.
The time for a 9 x 13-inch pan is 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken and spaghetti.
Mix all ingredients together in crock-pot for 2 or 3 hours to warm.

title: fancy carrots
directions: In medium saucepan, cook carrots in boiling water until tender (7 to 9 minutes).
Add scallions; cook 2 minutes.
Drain well. Stir in margarine, honey and salt; heat thoroughly.
Makes 8 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: ma's peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine peanut butter and granulated sugar in a large bowl. Stir in brown sugar until creamy with no lumps.
Add eggs, then margarine, to the peanut butter mixture.
In another bowl, combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Gradually add flour mixture to the peanut butter mixture, stirring until dough is thick.
Drop dough onto greased cookie sheet.
Cook for 10 minutes at 375°.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: granny cake
directions: Mix together. Pour into a pan and sprinkle with brown sugar and chopped nuts if desired. Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13 pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder and salt. Cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir buttermilk and yeast mixture into dry ingredients.
Form into walnut-size balls.
Bake at 400 degrees for 12 minutes.

title: crab supreme
directions: Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, mushrooms, garlic, onion and parsley.
Add crab.
Place in a buttered baking dish.
Melt oleo and toss with corn flakes. Sprinkle over crab mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: demon cake
directions: Melt the baking chocolate over simmering water, and add to the butter and sugar, creamed well.
Add buttermilk and flour which has been sifted with the baking soda, baking powder and salt alternately, then add the well beaten egg yolks and the egg white, stiffly whipped, and lastly the vanilla.
Pour into three well-greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 to 35 minutes.
Put together with Chocolate Butter Filling.

title: sweet roll dough
directions: Measure
1 3/4 cups flour into large mixing bowl.
Stir in sugar,
salt
and
yeast.
Heat milk, water and shortening until warm (120° to 130°).
Pour in flour mixture and add eggs and beat with
electric
mixer
at
low speed for 1/2 minute. Continue beating for
3 minutes more at high speed and stir in remainder of flour.
Dough
will
be
soft and rather sticky. Knead about
3 minutes.
Let
rest
20 minutes, then shape as desired.
Let rise in	warm
place
from 40 to 60 minutes and bake until
golden brown.
Time
and
temperature
will
vary according to
the
roll made.
Remove
from
pans and cool on racks.

title: green chili enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook ground beef with garlic and salt until brown.
Stir soups into meat.

title: deb's roast
directions: Put roast in roasting pan that 1/2 covers roast.
Bake at 425° for 1 hour.
Mix soup on stove top until smooth.
Add soup to roast and carrots.
Reduce to 375°.
Bake about 30 minutes and then add potatoes and onions.

title: microwave honey-barbecue drumsticks
directions: In a 1-cup glass measuring cup combine barbecue sauce, honey and orange juice; stir to mix.
Rinse drumsticks; pat dry with paper towel.
Place in microwave dish (12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch).
Brush chicken with sauce; cover with waxed paper.
Microcook on High for 5 minutes.
Turn dish; brush with sauce.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes longer or until no longer pink.
Cook any remaining sauce on High for 30 seconds to 1 minute.
Carefully spoon over chicken.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Pour soup into buttered oblong baking dish.
Arrange boned chicken and soup; place biscuits on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together well the first 5 ingredients. Sift together white flour, baking powder, cinnamon, ginger, cloves, salt and soda. Add to sifted ingredients the wheat flour, wheat germ, bran and pecans. Add the flour mixture to zucchini mixture. Bake in 2 loaf pans for 1 hour at 325°.

title: crab meat appetizer
directions: Spread softened cream cheese on round plate with a rim.
Cover with 3/4 bottle of chili sauce.
Sprinkle with crab meat.
Serve with Triscuits crackers.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in boiler and slowly bring just to a boil.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Have ready in large bowl the oatmeal, chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour the hot mixture over it and stir well.
Drop from teaspoon onto wax paper and allow to cool.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: cinnamon hard candy
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; bring to boil and keep boiling until temperature on candy thermometer reaches 300°. Remove from heat and add oil and food coloring. Pour onto cookie sheet; let set until hard and cool. Break into pieces with knife and dip into powdered sugar.

title: meat balls
directions: Shape into size of marbles and cook in microwave 7 or 8 minutes.
Place meat balls in sauce made of 1 bottle chili sauce and 1 can jellied cranberry sauce.
Serve hot on toothpicks.

title: swedish rice pudding
directions: Cook the Minute rice and water in saucepan as directed on the Minute rice box.
Beat eggs until foamy, add sugar, fruit cocktail and juice to vanilla and evaporated milk.
Mix in the Minute rice. Put in large greased casserole dish.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 30 minutes.
Then bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: baked squash
directions: Wash and cut up squash.
Boil until tender; drain thoroughly and then mash.
Add all ingredients except 1/2 of butter to squash.
Melt remaining butter.

title: carrots parmesan
directions: Boil carrots in salted water, to which sugar has been added, until tender.
Drain and put through a food mill or grate in a fairly fine grater.
Stir in cream cheese and grated onion and season to taste.
Pour into large greased casserole.
Arrange pecan halves on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: vegetable and oatmeal goulash(3 to 4 persons)
directions: Soak 2 breakfastcupfuls small white beans in cold water for 24 hours.
Put into a stew-jar with 3 ounces of diced fat bacon and 1 pound sliced carrots.
Mix thoroughly 1 level teaspoonful dry mustard and 1 tablespoonful golden syrup with enough hot water to make 1/2 pint.
Pour over beans and add enough water to cover. Put on lid and bake in moderate oven for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
For the last half hour, remove the lid and bring some of the bits of bacon to the top to brown off.
Delicious!
(GR)

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken breasts until done; cool and cut into bite size pieces.
Mix remaining ingredients together in a large bowl. Layer cut up chicken in a large Pyrex dish; pour soup mixture and drained Veg-All over chicken.

title: kentucky pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in a 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling salt water until tender.
Turn off heat and let stand 1 minute; then drain.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Cook onion in bacon grease until tender.
Mix all ingredients, reserving 4 slices of bacon.
Pour into baking dish.
Crumble and sprinkle remaining bacon on top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, heat corn oil over medium heat.
Add onion, garlic and parsley.
Cook, stirring 1 minute.

title: butterhorn rolls
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar and salt.
Add butter to milk.
Add this to the first mixture, then add yeast liquid also.
Beat in the flour, one cup at a time, until stiff enough to handle.
Put on board, adding flour to make a dough that will knead well.

title: rigatoni alla buttera
directions: Peel casings off sausage; cook in skillet over medium heat. When cooked, drain and crumble into small pieces.
Add tomatoes to skillet with sausage; mix well.
Add cream; cook over medium heat until sauce thickens.

title: easy lemon pies
directions: Mix together milk and Cool Whip.
Add lemonade and mix well. Pour into pie shells.
Refrigerate about 1 hour before serving.

title: banana split brownie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare brownie mix according to package directions.
Place parchment paper on 15-inch baking stone.
Pour brownie mixture on paper and spread into a 14-inch circle.
(Do not bake without parchment paper or batter will run off stone while baking.)
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until set. Cool to room temperature.

title: fresh salsa
directions: In small nonmetal bowl, blend together; let set 1 to 2 hours. Keeps for 5 days.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Cut wing tips off at joint and discard; cut each wing in half at joint.
On rack in broiler pan, arrange wings.
Broil 6-inches from heat for 25 minutes or until browned, turning occasionally. Transfer to serving dish.

title: raisin energy squares
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Beat well.
Add oats and flour. Stir well.
Add remainder.
Spread evenly in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan, greased.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: low fat mayonnaise
directions: Beat eggs, salt, paprika and dry mustard in top of double boiler.
Gradually add lemon juice and milk, stirring constantly. Cook until thick, at least 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in oil.
Pour into jar, cover and refrigerate.
Stir before serving.
Makes 1 c.
1 Tbsp = 20 calories.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Use greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Put 4 noodles in bottom of pan.
Spread half of beef mixture over them.
Place another 4 noodles on top and spread remaining half of beef mixture over top.
Looks like a lot of liquid but it will be alright.
Seal tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until noodles are tender.

title: smothered steak
directions: Cut round steak into serving size pieces.
Dredge in flour and brown in a large skillet.
Mix soup and water and pour over steak. Cover and cook over medium heat for 30 minutes or until tender.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: rocky road cookie pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 12-inch pizza pan. Press cookie dough into bottom of pan.
Bake for 13 to 16 minutes or until light golden brown.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle evenly with nuts, marshmallows and chocolate chips.
Drizzle with caramel sauce. Bake an additional 5 to 10 minutes.
Cool completely.
Cut into wedges, 16 servings.
Can use jimmies or anything else for a favorite topping.

title: smoked sausage in noodle n kraut casserole
directions: Boil noodles in salted water for 20 minutes.
Place layer of noodles in casserole, cover with half the raw sauerkraut, then the layer of Eckrich smoked sausage cut in 1/2-inch slices.
Repeat. Add 1 cup of water and bake with cover on in 350° oven for 45-60 minutes.

title: raisin spice cookies
directions: Put raisins and water in a saucepan.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and allow to steam for 5 minutes. Drain raisins; retain 1/2 cup liquid.
Immediately put baking soda into liquid.
(This will cause bubbling action, so be sure to use 1 cup measure.)

title: mixed vegetable salad
directions: Combine vegetables and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients until sugar dissolves.
Mix all together and toss well.
Chill thoroughly before serving.
(Best if chilled overnight.)

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Layer all ingredients in a 4-quart Corning Ware dish, starting with asparagus.
Bake uncovered at 350° until bubbly and melted, approximately 30 minutes.
tags: cream of mushroom and chicken soup

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown the meat, then bake 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Add soup and mix together.
Serve by pouring meat on noodles.

title: lyn's chicken drummettes
directions: Place drummettes in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Pour dressing over completely.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° turning often. Finished when browned.

title: low-fat cottage cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add skim milk if needed for consistency. Makes 2 cups.
Has 15 calories per tablespoon.

title: spicy tomato and apple brew
directions: Combine first three ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a simmer.
Discard cloves.
Stir in hot sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour into mugs.
Garnish with celery sticks, if desired.

title: strawberry rhubarb pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt and flour.
Arrange half of the fruit in pie shell.
Sprinkle with half of the sugar mixture.
Repeat with remaining fruit and sugar.
Dot with butter.
Put on full top crust or lattice crust.
Sprinkle top crust with sugar.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes or until rhubarb is done and crust is browned.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Make cake according to package directions and bake.
While cake bakes, combine pineapple and sugar.
Bring to a boil and cook 2 minutes.
When cake is done, remove from oven.
Puncture holes all over cake with fork.
Pour pineapple mixture over cake while hot.
Let cake cool.
Make pudding and spread over cooled cake. Frost with whipped topping.

title: new england seafood chowder
directions: In a large kettle, place fish and enough water to cover.
Cook 10 minutes.
Remove fish and break into bite size pieces.
Measure liquid and add enough to make 4 cups.

title: easy potato soup
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a Dutch oven; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in soups and milk.
Heat thoroughly.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.
Garnish with shredded Cheddar cheese, diced, cooked ham or bacon.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix the mayo, sugar, vinegar.
Toss all together. Refrigerate.

title: hamburg soup
directions: In large pan, add tomatoes.
Break up a little; rinse can with 1/2 cup water.
Add sauce; rinse can with water.
Break up meat with your fingers, adding to the liquids, then the vegetables and bay leaf.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Add frozen vegetables.
Cook until they are tender.
Add water, if you need liquid.
Cook small noodles or small shells.

title: apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat all ingredients together and pour into pie crust.
Bake for 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sunday night supper salad(leftover salad)
directions: Mix meat and vegetables with French dressing.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Add pickles, eggs and mayonnaise.
Chill.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Add flour, sugar and brown sugar; beat until well blended.
Blend in melted butter.
Stir in morsels and nuts.
Pour into pie shell. Bake 1 hour.

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: Combine soup and butter.
Add remaining ingredients and mix with frozen potatoes.
Place in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, top with bread crumbs and paprika.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: spicy pasta pie
directions: Cook vermicelli according to package directions.
Drain well. Set aside.
Meanwhile, in large skillet cook turkey sausage, mushrooms, onions and garlic until sausage is no longer pink and onion is tender.
Drain fat, if necessary.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, Italian seasoning and crushed red pepper. Spray 9-inch quiche dish with nonstick spray.
Place half the cooked vermicelli in bottom of dish.
Top with half of Mozzarella cheese and half of sausage mixture.
Repeat layers.
Cover dish loosely with foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until heated through.
Top with Parmesan.
Let stand 10 minutes. Cut into wedges to serve.
Serves 6.

title: sugar plum cake
directions: Grease a Bundt pan and coat with sugar.
Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour batter into pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour. Cool for 10 minutes.

title: sweet and sauer meatballs
directions: Combine beef, seasonings, chestnuts and milk; form into meatballs.
Roll in flour and cook in frying pan in butter over medium heat, turning until all sides are brown and cooked through.

title: favorite pickled beets
directions: Trim tops of beets down to within 1 inch of beet; do not cut into beet or the color will "bleed" during cooking.
Clean.
Cook in boiling water to cover until tender.
Drain and cover with cold water.
Slip skins and trim off tops and roots.
Slice, if large.

title: meat loaf roll
directions: Rinse and drain frozen broccoli under cold water.
Mix hamburger, eggs, bread crumbs, catsup, milk, 1/2 teaspoon salt, pepper and oregano.
Pat hamburger mixture into rectangle, 12 x 10-inch, on a piece of aluminum foil, 18 x 15-inches.
Arrange broccoli on mixture to within 1/2 inch of edges.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon salt.
Arrange ham on broccoli.
Roll up carefully beginning at the 10-inch side using foil to lift.
Press edges and ends of roll to seal.
Place on rack in shallow roasting pan. Cook, uncovered, in 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours.
Overlap cheese on top; cook until melted, about 1 minute.
Center of meat loaf roll may be slightly pink due to ham.

title: special tea cakes
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, milk, vanilla and shortening.
Work in flour like you would for biscuit dough.
Knead and roll out on floured surface.
Cut out and bake on cookie sheet for 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.
Yields 2 dozen cakes.

title: garlic 'n lemon roast chicken
directions: In a large plastic bag on non-aluminum baking dish, combine onion and soup mix with olive oil and lemon juice.
Add chicken, turning to coat evenly.
Marinate in refrigerator 2 hours. Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove chicken and
marinade mixture to a 13 x 9-inch baking/roasting pan or leave in baking dish.
Bake chicken, uncovered, basting occasionally, 40 minutes or until done.

title: poppy seed loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour into 2 large, lightly greased loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until toothpick comes out clean.
Top will crack.

title: barbecued hamburger
directions: Brown onions and celery in pan (use oil).
Remove and add hamburger and sweet pepper.
Brown them, then put all ingredients together.
Add catsup.
Let cook through.
Add piccalilli, sugar, salt and pepper.
Simmer for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all all above ingredients together and pour into a 9 x 9 baking dish.
Cook at 400 degrees for 30 - 40 minutes; until top is golden in color.

title: best yet dressing
directions: Boil chicken in salted water until tender.
Bake corn bread according to directions on back of Martha White self-rising corn meal, using 4 eggs instead of one.
Cook bread.
When bread is cool, crumble bread in large bowl or pan.
Crumble the Ritz crackers in with bread.
Chop onion and add in.

title: bread pudding
directions: Butter bottom and sides of 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes, then bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt in top of double boiler. Add water and egg yolks; place over hot water and cook about 10 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from fire. Add lemon juice and rind. Cool. Pour into baked pie shell.

title: coleslaw dressing
directions: Mix together and pour over chopped cabbage.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate cheese.
Add mayonnaise and nuts.
Mix together real good.
Make into molds or into a ball.
Chill overnight in refrigerator.
Serve with strawberry jam and Ritz crackers.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Mix milk, oil and egg.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into sprayed or greased muffin pans.
Cook at 350° until lightly browned.

title: chicken "n" dumplings
directions: Cover chicken with water.
Add broth.
Bring to boil, then reduce to medium heat.
Add diced celery, onions and garlic.
Add salt, pepper, Accent and poultry seasoning to taste.
Cook all ingredients for 1 hour.
Then bring to another boil and drop tortilla strips into pot, then simmer for 10 minutes while stirring with a fork to keep dumplings from sticking.
Serves 4 to 5 people.

title: double chocolate fudge(5 pounds)
directions: *Filler can be anything like nuts, candied cherries, citron or raisins in any combination up to 4 cups.
Try experimenting with exotic ingredients like dried fruits and fruit peels.

title: popover pizza
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain. Stir in sauce mix, tomato sauce and water. Simmer 10 minutes. Spoon into greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Top with cheese slices.

title: pancake and waffle mix
directions: Mix.
Spray griddle or waffle iron with Pam.
Heat and spoon on mixture.
Pecans or blueberries may be added.
Serves 4.

title: pineapple cherry squares
directions: Mix together pineapple, cherries, juice, sugar, cornstarch and salt, cook until thick.
Add beaten yolks and cook 2 minutes longer.
Pour over crust.
Beat egg whites and add 1/4 sugar and spread over square.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Brown in a 400° oven.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Brown beef in 3-quart saucepan; drain off excess fat.
Add sauce and water; simmer about 10 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients, except lasagne, for filling.

title: easy beef roast
directions: Flour on both sides and brown in oil in hot skillet on top of stove.
After browning, put roast into roaster and cover with cream of mushroom soup and dry onion soup mix.
Salt and pepper to taste and cover tightly.
Bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes per pound.
If desired, potatoes and carrots can be added to the roast the last hour of baking.
Do not add water at any time.
It makes its own gravy if kept tightly covered.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Set up can of pumpkin as for pie.
Sprinkle with yellow cake mix.
Melt butter.
Pour on top of cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts on top. Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven until done. Tastes like pumpkin pie.
Serve with whipped cream, ice cream, etc.

title: fresh strawberry-rhubarb pie
directions: Mix together sugar and cornstarch in large saucepan.
Stir in water and add rhubarb.
Cook mixture over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally, just until rhubarb is tender and mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in strawberry gelatin until dissolved.
Refrigerate, stirring often, until mixture mounds when dropped from spoon.
Stir in strawberries.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat to boiling.
Pour over ribs, etc.
Keeps in refrigerator for weeks.

title: date cookies
directions: Mix dates, water and 1/4 cup sugar and boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add walnut meats.
Cool; cream butter and add brown sugar and 1/2 cup white sugar.
Blend well.
Add 1 well beaten egg and flour sifted with soda and salt.
Turn out on floured board and roll 1/4-inch thick.
Spread the dough with the cold mixture. Roll up like a jelly roll and wrap in waxed paper.
Let stand overnight and chill.
Slice and bake for about 12 minutes.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Dip chicken in egg and then flour.
In skillet, melt butter and brown chicken for 4 minutes, turning once.
Stir in Golden Herb with Lemon soup mix blended with water; arrange lemon on chicken. Bring to a boil.
Simmer, covered, 10 minutes or until chicken is done.
Makes 4 servings.
Serve with Lipton Golden Saute Chicken Broccoli angel hair pasta.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix everything together except Doritos and dressing. Just before you eat, add Doritos and dressing and toss well.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream margarine or butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing after each addition.
Sift the flour and baking powder together.
Add to the butter, sugar and egg mixture in four or five batches.
Stir in the sour cream and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes in a 350° oven.
Do not overcook.
Cake should be moist.
Cool cake in pan for 20 minutes.
Then remove and wrap in foil for 24 hours. Freezes well.

title: jo d's chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion in 1/2 tablespoon of butter.
Add all ingredients, except crackers. Mix well.
Put in casserole dish. Top with cracker crumbs.
Cook at 400° in oven until bubbles in middle, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: banana salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in loaf pan.
Freeze and slice to serve.

title: "heavenly moments"(melting moments)
directions: Mix flour with cornstarch and sugar in a bowl.
Blend in butter to form a soft dough.
Cover and chill until dough is firm. Shape into balls.
Roll in coconut and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly brown. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: cinnamon salad
directions: Mix cinnamon red hots, sugar and boiling water in pan.
Bring to a boil and stir until red hots are dissolved.
Add cherry gelatin and 1 cup cold water.
Chill until partially set.
Add apple, orange and nuts and chill until set firm.

title: oriental cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and onions.
Place in a large bowl.
Crush noodles and add to cabbage.
Mix seasoning package from noodles with the oil, vinegar, and Sweet N Low.
Mix well.
Roast almonds and sesame seeds.
Mix together and add to cabbage.
Pour oil mixture over cabbage when ready to eat.

title: tutti-frutti salad
directions: In large mixing bowl, place peaches, pineapple and fruit cocktail, using all juices.
Slice strawberries and add to other fruit.
Add instant pudding mixes.
(Do not prepare puddings according to package, just drop in bowl with fruit and mix.)
Add bananas, sliced.
Mix all and refrigerate.
To make low calorie, use sugar-free fruits and pudding mixes.

title: corn spoon bread
directions: Grease 2-quart baking dish. Beat egg whites at room temperature until stiff. Beat yolks until thick. Stir corn meal and salt into scalded milk, beating hard.
Cook a few seconds over low heat, stirring until consistency of thick mush.
Blend in corn and butter, then baking powder.
Fold in yolks, then whites. Pour into baking dish. Bake in a 375° oven for 35 minutes or until puffy golden brown.
Knife inserted in center should come out clean.

title: preacher cookies
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add milk, sugar and cocoa.
Place over medium heat.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Cool for 1 minute.

title: tomato consomme
directions: Combine broth, juice, onions, paste, thyme, basil and allspice in a large saucepan.
Simmer, uncovered, until onion is soft, 5-10 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in lemon juice. Just before serving, top each bowl with a spoonful of yogurt or sour cream, and a sprig of parsley.
Serve hot.

title: egg nog
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs.
Add sugar and salt.
Stir well. Add milk and vanilla.
Stir.
Pour into glass and sprinkle
with nutmeg.

title: pumpkin ice cream pie
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Bring just to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cool; beat in softened ice cream.
Add nuts.
Spread in pie shell and freeze until firm.
Garnish with whipped cream and nuts if desired.

title: ice cream cupcakes
directions: Mix the cake as directed on the box.
Put 1 or 1 1/2 tablespoons of cake mix in the cones and cook as directed for cupcakes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Put icing on top and add sprinkles. Should serve 20 to 30.

title: fruit dip
directions: Stir the orange juice (thawed) and milk together in container with lid.
Add the vanilla pudding; seal and shake.
Stir in sour cream; chill 2 hours.
Use with assorted fruits such as apples, oranges, bananas, strawberries, pineapple, cantaloupe, grapes, etc.

title: west virginia ham
directions: Your ham should be a country cured ham.
Soak it in water for a day, changing the water each 8 hours (3 times).

title: chocolate mochi
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients and mix well with an electric mixer.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake 1 hour.
Cool before cutting.
For easy cutting, grease knife with vegetable oil or butter.
Makes 24 servings.

title: backyard stew
directions: Brown the ground beef and drain.
Add soup and simmer 30 minutes.
Boil potatoes and fix as creamed potatoes.
Place on platter.
Make a well in the center.
Fill with meat mixture. Serve with salad.

title: parmesan garlic chicken
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Coat chicken breast halves with mixture. Cook in olive oil 8 to 10 minutes per side or until crispy.

title: turkey hash
directions: This is wonderful for leftover turkey.
Amount of potatoes depends on the amount of turkey you have.
Peel and cube potatoes, boil.
Cube meat.
Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add meat, then potatoes.
Prepare brown gravy mix and pour around hash.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: In a large bowl, with a wooden spoon, mix oil, sugar, eggs, vanilla and chocolate chips together.
Then sift flour and other dry ingredients into the mixture.
Mix all of the ingredients well.
Fold in apples.
Bake one hour at 325° in greased tube pan.

title: cherry berry
directions: Mix the sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla. Add the flour and baking powder, then add the milk with the soda dissolved in it. Batter will be thick and stiff, but fluffy. Spread in a 12 x 18-inch pan. Spread the cherries on one half of the cake and the blueberries on the other half.

title: chocolate supreme triffle (variation)
directions: Layer in glass bowl:
All cupcakes (quartered), then sprinkle Kahlua over them.
Add 1/2 pudding mixture; sprinkle 1/2 Heath bars (broken up), then 1/2 Cool Whip mixed with nuts and marshmallows.
Then repeat with pudding, Cool Whip mixture and sprinkle with rest of broken Heath bars.

title: chewy pecan cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat butter, sugars, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Stir in oats, raisins and nuts; mix well.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until light golden brown.
Remove from baking sheets to cool on wire racks.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix punch, 7-Up, pineapple juice, ice cream and lemon juice. Slice all of the fruit very thin and add to the punch mixture. Just before serving, add several trays of ice cubes.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: belgian steamed mussels
directions: Melt the butter in a pot and add the shallots and the celery. Cook, stirring occasionally until the vegetables are softened, about 5 minutes.
Add the mussels, thyme, bay leaf, parsley, pepper and salt.
Pour the beer over the mussels and cover the pot.
Bring them to a boil over high heat and steam the mussels until they are opening.
It will take about 4 minutes.
Be careful not to overcook the mussels, otherwise they will be tough.
Shake the pot several times to toss the mussels with the vegetables.
Spoon the hot mussels into soup plates along with some broth.
Sprinkle with a little bit of parsley just before serving.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
These ingredients can be mixed in a blender.
Pour in a deep 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake in preheated oven at 450°, then reduce heat to 350° and bake until crust is brown. Serves 6.

title: alaska salad
directions: Mix together first five ingredients, then add whipped cream and nuts. Chill 3 hours.

title: venison roast
directions: Combine tomato sauce, sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and chopped onion.
Place the roast on a large sheet of foil in baking dish and cover with bacon slices.
Pour the tomato sauce mixture over roast.
Fold and seal foil around the roast. Bake at 300° for 3 hours.

title: milky way cake
directions: Cream sugar and 1 stick of oleo.
Melt candy and 1 stick of oleo.
Mix eggs, flour and buttermilk.
Add all together.
Cook in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: chicken vegetable saute
directions: Cook chicken in skillet 10 minutes or until browned on both sides.
Remove chicken, keep warm.
Using same skillet, cook broccoli, carrots and mushrooms 5 minutes, stirring often.
Stir in soup, milk and pepper; heat to boiling.
Put chicken back in skillet and reduce heat to low, simmer 5 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender.
Garnish with lemon slices.
