title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry
ingredients together.	Beat egg whites and set aside. Mix milk
and
eggs
with	dry ingredients.
Cook in a double boiler over
low heat.
Add butter while cooking.
When mixture is thickened,	remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour into 2 baked pie
shells.
Top
with meringue and bake at 350° until meringue is brown.

title: easy dill pickles
directions: Put dill in 2-quart jar; add mustard seed, alum, sugar and salt.
Pack pickles in jar.
Add garlic.
Add vinegar to each jar. Fill with cold water.
Seal.
Put cans in a canner.
Bring to boil. Boil 1 minute.
Remove from canner; cool.
Store 30 days.
Ready to eat.
Wipe off tops of jars; seal.
After being in canner, if doesn't seal, redo the lids.

title: meringue
directions: Have egg whites at room temperature for best volume in beating.
Be sure egg whites are free from particles of egg yolk and beaters and bowl are not greasy.
Yolk and grease prevent egg whites from beating up.
Add cream of tartar and vanilla to egg whites and beat until soft peaks form.
Add sugar in 1 tablespoon portions, beating constantly.
With last addition of sugar, beat meringue until stiff peaks form.

title: punch
directions: When ready to serve, add Slice to other ingredients.

title: green chile pie
directions: Butter 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with green chiles.
Spread cheese over.
Pour eggs with water on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Done when knife placed into center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes before cutting.

title: hawaiian-coconut cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt into a bowl. Add shortening, sugars, eggs, water and vanilla.
Beat until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Fold in rolled oats and coconut.
Shape dough into small balls; place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen cookies.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: In heavy saucepan, cook sugar, margarine, syrup and salt over medium heat, stirring constantly.
After the mixture begins to boil, cook only 5 minutes more.
Remove from heat and add flavoring and soda.
Pour over popped corn.
Stir to coat.

title: porcupine casserole
directions: Combine beef, rice, onion, bell pepper, egg, Worcestershire, mustard, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt, 1/8 teaspoon pepper and garlic powder.
Form into 1 1/2-inch balls (about 18).
Place into a shallow 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine soup, water, ketchup and remaining salt and pepper; bring to a boil.
Pour over meat balls. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven; stir in cheese spread.

title: creamy banana pudding(by lounelle shaw, pendergrass, ga)
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Let come to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil one minute; remove from heat and add oatmeal, peanut butter and/or nuts and vanilla.
Mix and drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper and allow to cool.

title: poor man's chop suey
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole.
Cover and cook in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Combine veal, pork, rice, sugar, onion, salt and pepper. Separate leaves of cabbage and wilt them by placing in boiling water for a few minutes.
Drain leaves thoroughly.
Place about 1/2 cup of the mixture on each cabbage leaf and roll up securely. Place rolls in a baking pan.
Dot each with butter.
Pour tomato juice over the rolls.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: kapusta(hot cabbage soup)
directions: In a 6-quart kettle, combine cabbage, salt, pepper, onion and 1 1/2-quarts water. Bring to boiling, covered. Add beef, soup bone and tomato puree. Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 1 hour.
Add potatoes. Simmer, covered, 1 hour.

title: easy mexican chicken
directions: Boil and bone chicken. Mix together chicken, tomatoes and soups. Brown onion in margarine; add to chicken mixture. Layer Doritos, cheese and chicken mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pralines
directions: Make syrup of 3 cups sugar, salt and cream. Put on low heat to boil. Melt other cup of sugar in heavy cast-iron skillet until dissolved and light brown in color. Add syrup to this mixture and cook until it forms firm ball. Add pecans. Remove from heat and beat until creamy. Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: hot vegetable dip
directions: Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: granola
directions: Warm the honey to boiling with the oil. Pour over the first 5 ingredients. Bake in 350° oven 15 minutes; stir, then bake 15 minutes more. Add raisins after removing from the oven for the last time. Store in container at room temperature.

title: toll house pan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine butter, sugars and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour.
Stir in chocolate morsels and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool; cut into squares.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs well.
Then add the next 7 ingredients and beat until smooth.
Stir in the coconut, nuts, pineapple and carrots with a mixing spoon.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: elderberry jelly
directions: Remove large stems from fully ripe berries and crush.
Heat gently until juice starts to flow; then simmer, covered, 15 minutes.
Place in jelly bag and squeeze out juice.
Measure.
Add 1/4 cup lemon juice.
Mix Sure-Jell and bring to hard boil, stirring occasionally.
Add sugar at once, cook and stir.
When mixture returns to full boil (cannot be stirred down), cook and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat; skim off foam with metal spoon. Pour at once into glasses, leaving 1/2-inch at top.
Cover with 1/8-inch hot paraffin.
Cool, cover with loose fitting lids. Store in cool dry place.

title: party cheese ball
directions: *May use dried onion flakes.

title: beef brisket
directions: Place brisket in a 9 x 13-inch glass or ceramic baking dish. Combine tomato juice, celery, onion and garlic salts.
Pour over meat.
Cover or place in a large plastic bag.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: everlasting salad
directions: Combine apples, drained pineapple and macaroni rings in a large bowl.
Cook the lemon juice, beaten eggs and sugar mixture over low heat, stirring with a wooden spoon until thick. Cool 10 minutes.
Pour over ingredients.
When ready to serve, fold in whipped cream.

title: salsa(canning)
directions: Cook for 20 minutes all ingredients, lower heat when starts to boil.
Cook 20 minutes longer.
Pour into sterile jars; process 30 minutes in boiling water bath.
Makes 21 pints or 11 quarts.

title: chewy cranberry gingers
directions: In large bowl combine all ingredients except cranberries. Blend and stir in berries.
Chill dough for 1 hour or more. Shape into balls using a teaspoon.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375°, 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet immediately.

title: kentucky fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken.
Dip in dry mix.
Place on baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Spread melted margarine on top with a paintbrush.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lite lemony dessert
directions: Stir pie filling, yogurt and Cool Whip until mixed well. Break cake into bite-size pieces.
Layer filling, cake, filling, etc. into container.
Garnish with lemon slices if desired.
Can also be used as frosting.
Slice cake into 3 or 4 layers and frost between each layer with filling/yogurt/Cool Whip mixture.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in butter until tender.
Add 3 tablespoons of flour and milk until creamy.
Add olives, pimentos and drained mushrooms; add in cheese, Accent and hominy, drained. Mix altogether and let set overnight.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: trail bars
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with waxed paper.
In heavy saucepan, combine corn syrup, sugar and salt; bring to boil.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except chocolate chips; cool slightly.
Add chocolate chips; press into prepared pan.
Refrigerate 30 minutes; cut into bars.
Store in refrigerator.

title: bowl of sex
directions: Bake cake in two layers.
Use only one layer.
Crumble half of the one layer in a bowl.
Sprinkle 2 or 3 tablespoons of the Kahlua over the cake; spread layer of chocolate pudding on that and then layer of Cool Whip.
Crumble bars and sprinkle on top of Cool Whip.
Repeat, making two layers. Refrigerate until served.

title: holiday cookies
directions: Stir until fluffy.
Chill 1 hour.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: crumb cake
directions: Cream butter, margarine and sugars.
Add eggs, one at a time. Mix in vanilla wafers and milk.
Fold in coconut and nuts.
Bake in a greased tube pan at 300° for 1 hour, 30 minutes.
Frost with Hard Sauce.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix first four ingredients. Bake in shallow pan at 350° for 20 minutes; stir occasionally to break into crumbs.

Sprinkle 2/3 of crumbs into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Combine egg whites, sugar, strawberries, lemon juice and food coloring. Beat at high speed about 10 minutes. Fold in Cool Whip. Spoon over crumbs. Top with remaining crumbs. Freeze for 6 hours. Garnish with a fresh strawberry if desired.
Serves 12.

title: strawberry or raspberry rhubarb jam
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients gently for 4 minutes; take off burner.
Add the jello.
Have glasses hot.
Ladle in jam.
Keep stirring to keep fruit mixed evenly.
Wax when jam is hot.
Add more wax when cold.
Or seal with Kerr/Ball lid and store in refrigerator.

title: frosted cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries and sugar; let set overnight; drain.
Add grapes, nuts and pineapple to cranberries.

title: whole wheat banana bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a small bowl.
Set aside. Combine sugar and oil.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer for 2 minutes or until well blended.
Add egg.
Beat well.
Add flour alternately with bananas, beginning and ending with flour.
Blend well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.

title: chicken cutlet sandwich with spinach and mushrooms
directions: In 3 separate bowls, place flour, beaten eggs with milk and breadcrumbs.
Dip chicken cutlets in flour, then eggs, then coat with breadcrumbs.

title: lace cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Work in flour and beat in egg.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoon 2 1/2-inches apart on cookie sheet that has been lined with aluminum foil and sprayed.
Bake in a 375° oven for 5 minutes. Cool and peel off.	Store with layers of wax paper between.

title: cottage cheese cookies
directions: Cream margarine and cheese together.
Add flour and work it in to form a dough.
Chill for 1 hour or more.
Roll dough 1/8 inch thick.
Cut into 2 or 3-inch squares.
Place jam or preserves in center; fold squares to form triangles.
Seal edges tight.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: banana bombay salad
directions: Puree 3 bananas and whisk with lemon juice, mayonnaise, yogurt and tarragon.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Cut chicken or turkey into bite-size pieces.
Add cut green apples and raisins. Add walnuts and mix.
Cut remaining 2 bananas into thick chunks and add the banana puree blend to recipe.
Mix together.
Serve chilled.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: 1st Layer:
Melt margarine and pour over crushed Oreo cookies (reserve 1/2 cup cookies crushed).
Lightly pat mixture into bottom of oblong pan and refrigerate until firm.

title: broccoli soup
directions: In large saucepan, place broccoli, celery, onion and broth. Bring to boil; cover and simmer 8 minutes until vegetables are tender.
In medium bowl, combine milk, cornstarch, salt, pepper and thyme.
Add milk mixture to vegetable mixture and cook until soup is slightly thickened and just begins to boil (about 4 to 5 minutes), stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add cheese, stirring until melted.
Makes 4 servings.
(Recipe can be doubled nicely.)

title: quick chocolate sauce
directions: Pour syrup in small bowl.
Blend in pudding mix.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Let stand 10 minutes or slightly thickened.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: green salad with mandarin oranges
directions: Mix herb dressing with vinegar or balsamic vinegar.
Toss other ingredients together in bowl.
Pour dressing over.
Serve with crumbled blue cheese.

title: pumpkin cheese cake
directions: Mix and put crust in refrigerator.

title: brussels sprouts with onion
directions: Pull off any tough outer leaves of the sprouts.
Using a paring knife, make a couple of crossed gashes in the base of each sprout. Put sprouts in a saucepan and add water to cover and salt.
Bring to a boil and cook 10 to 12 minutes, or until tender.
Drain well. Heat butter in a saucepan; add onion, cumin, salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until onion is wilted.
Add sprouts and stir until sprouts are coated with butter and are hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mandarin crepes
directions: In a medium bowl, whisk together milk, flour, egg, 1 tablespoon sugar, oil and salt until blended and smooth.
Let stand for 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water until soft.
Cook ground beef until done.
Drain water off noodles and grease off ground beef. Then mix together in pan and put sauce in.
Then serve.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix flour and 1 cup of sugar together until smooth. Add milk. Melt margarine and pour into flour, sugar and milk mixture. Add peaches and pour into buttered dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup of sugar over top. Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: chocolate angel pie
directions: Beat egg whites with a pinch of salt until stiff, but not dry. Beat in cream of tartar and sugar by tablespoons.
Line in well-greased 9-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Bake at 275° for about 1 hour or until delicately brown.
Cool thoroughly.

title: jollof rice
directions: In a large skillet brown chicken pieces on both sides in hot oil about 15 minutes.
Remove; set aside.
Keep drippings.
Add onion to drippings; cook until tender but not brown.
Drain fat. Add chicken to skillet.
Combine undrained tomatoes, chicken broth, bay leaf, ginger, cinnamon or thyme, salt and ground red pepper.
Pour over chicken.
Do not stir.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Skim off fat.
Add rice. Make sure all rice is covered with liquid.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes more or until rice is tender.
Remove bay leaf. Sprinkle with snipped parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together first.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in a muffin tin at 400° for 15 minutes.
Muffins are best if batter is kept in refrigerator overnight before baking.
Batter will keep in refrigerator up to 6 weeks.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix together banana creme, whipped cream, sour cream and milk until blended well.
In another bowl, place vanilla wafers, then a layer of bananas.
Spoon enough banana mixture on top to cover. Repeat process until all the mixture is used, making sure mixture is the last step.
Refrigerate until ready to eat, or may be eaten immediately.

title: cherry tomato salad
directions: Wash cherry tomatoes and green onions.
Cut cherry tomatoes in half and place in bowl. Cut green onions and place in bowl with tomatoes.
Take oregano and crush with your hands, over the onions and tomatoes.
Drizzle olive oil and vinegar over salad, to taste. Cut up Feta cheese in small chunks and sprinkle over salad.

title: colleen's ribs
directions: Brown ribs at 400° for 1 hour.
Add sauce.
Lower temperature to 350°.
Cook, uncovered, for 45 minutes (baste and turn every 15 to 20 minutes).
Add water, if needed.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake for 40 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 to 15 minutes.
Can add pineapple juice instead of water.
(Two hours and 40 minutes, total.)

title: beer batter
directions: Covers 2 pounds of meat.
Dip meat, mushrooms, etc. and deep-fry.

title: chicken yakitori
directions: In small bowl, combine soy sauce, wine, ginger and garlic. Mix in the chicken pieces.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil and stir-fry livers.
Remove livers.
Add remaining oil to skillet and add drained chicken breast and then mushrooms and cook about 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Return livers to skillet with marinade, juice, cabbage and onion; cook about 3 minutes.
Add pea pods and cook 3 more minutes or until crisp-tender.
Add 2 tablespoons water and serve with Chinese noodles or vermicelli.

title: party potatoes
directions: Heat water, butter and onion salt until boiling.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish at 300° for 1 hour.

title: paradise salad
directions: Combine lime jello, boiling water and pineapple juice. Refrigerate and let cool.
Mix cream cheese, crushed pineapple and mayonnaise together.
Mix together the whipping cream and chopped nuts.
When jello mixture has cooled, mix all ingredients together.
Pour into container.
Let set 3 or 4 hours before serving.

title: potato soup
directions: In a large pot, put 2 1/2 quarts of water.
Add the carrot, onion and celery; bring to a boil.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add potatoes, salt and pepper.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Add flour with a small amount of water to make a paste.
Add a little of the hot liquid, mix and add to the soup to thicken it a little. Add the milk; bring back to a boil.
Serve.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix together the pudding, milk and Cool Whip.
Layer pudding mix, bananas and wafers.
Refrigerate.

title: where's-the-fat chocolate sauce
directions: In a small saucepan, stir together sugar, cocoa and cornstarch.
Add milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick and bubbly.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla.
Serve with ice cream, frozen yogurt, angel food cake and fresh fruit.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix the butter and sugar together, then add the beaten eggs and mix well.
Then add the flour to which the soda, salt and spices have been added.
Mix well.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan (greased) and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until it tests done.
Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: enchiladas with sour cream sauce
directions: Cut cooked chicken into 12 strips and sprinkle with salt to taste.
Set aside.
In large skillet, saute onions and garlic in butter until soft.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, green chilies, sugar, cumin, salt, oregano and basil.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Remove chicken.
Dip each tortilla in sauce.
Place 1 piece chicken on each tortilla with 2 tablespoons cheese.
Roll and place in 9 x 13-inch pan with seam down.
Blend sour cream into remaining sauce and pour over enchiladas.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate coconut bars supreme
directions: Measure 2/3 cup of dry cake mix; set aside.
Combine remaining cake mix, butter and 1 egg, mixing well.
Press into bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Make crust.
Bake.
Cream the cream cheese and sugar together. Spread on crust.
Mix pudding and milk together until thick enough.
Pour over cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip.
Can garnish with remainder of nuts or candy.
Chill.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray or oil bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with pecans and coconut.
Pour cake mix over the mixture.
Mix powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Pour over top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top will crack open as it bakes.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Cream egg and margarine. Add cake mix.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.

title: soft jumbo raisin cookies
directions: Boil water and raisins for 5 minutes; set aside to cool. Cream together shortening, eggs, sugar and vanilla in separate bowl.
Add nuts, flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice to cooled raisins.
Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: strawberry surprise
directions: Place cake in
a
large glass oblong dish.
Mix pudding with milk and ice
cream.
Pour
over
the
cake
and place in refrigerator.
Dissolve jello in boiling water, let cool.
Add the strawberries, and pour over the cake.
Store in refrigerator.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Cut broccoli, cauliflower and onion in small pieces.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over the broccoli, cauliflower and onions.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Combine crushed pineapple with juice and dry apricot Jell-O in saucepan.
Cook until Jell-O is completely dissolved, stirring constantly. Set aside to cool. Beat chilled milk with cream cheese until smooth. Fold into chilled Jell-O, do not beat.
Fold in carton of Cool Whip.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Combine butter, syrup and sugar in saucepan.
Let boil 5 minutes and add salt and soda.
Stir until foamy.
Add vanilla and peanuts.
Pour over popcorn and stir to coat.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Place chicken in bottom of baking dish.
Mix the sour cream and cream of chicken soup together until well blended.
Spread over chicken.
Crumble crackers on top of sour cream mixture.
Cut up margarine and place on top of crackers.
Bake for about 45 minutes to an hour at 350°.

title: tom's chicken
directions: In saucepan, combine first 8 ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until chicken and vegetables are tender.
Prepare rice according to package.
Serve mixture over rice.

title: pepper hash(relish)
directions: Grind all vegetables separately.
Cover peppers with boiling water.
Let stand 10 minutes; drain.
Add onions, sugar, salt and vinegar.
Stir, blending well.
Heat to boiling.
Boil 10 minutes. Seal in hot jars.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Combine about half the flour, brown sugar, peanut butter, shortening, egg, milk, vanilla and baking soda.
Beat with mixer on medium to high until thoroughly combined.
Beat in remaining flour.
Stir in oats.
Spread batter into an ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.

title: candy bar cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions. Pour into 3 greased and floured 8 inch cake pans. Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done. Cool 10 minutes in pans; remove and finish cooling on wire racks. Beat cream cheese, powdered and granulated sugars until mixture is creamy. Chop 8 of the candy bars. Fold candy bars and cream cheese into Cool Whip. Spread between cake layers, on top, and sides. Chop remaining candy bars and press on top and along bottom edge of cake. Very rich and delicious!

title: flaky pastry(for chicken pot pie)
directions: Combine the dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse corn meal.
Add ice water; stir lightly.
(Dough will be just moist enough to shape into a ball.)
Flop dough into a floured mixture in casserole dish.
Tuck the ends under and press firmly to sides of dish.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Cut in Crisco and peanut butter until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Blend in syrup and milk.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until brown.

title: oven baked round steak(nonfat)
directions: Season steak with your favorite seasonings.
Dredge steak in flour.
Heat a Teflon skillet with the shortening.
Brown cut up pieces for steaks.
Place in Dutch oven. Pour beef broth over steak.
Bake in oven at 350° until tender.

title: corned beef and cabbage casserole
directions: Saute in margarine the cabbage, celery and onions.
Add and mix well the drained noodles, corned beef, Swiss cheese, milk, dry mustard, caraway seed and pepper.
Spoon into greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes until heated.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix the tapioca pudding, jello and water together. Bring to a boil and cool. Add Cool Whip, enough to make creamy, then add oranges. Chill before serving.

title: my mom's dream bars
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients like a pie crust; press into an 8-inch square pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°; watch closely.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugar, butter and shortening in a bowl.
Add egg and beat.
Add vanilla.
Mix together baking soda, cinnamon, baking powder and flour.
Add to the batter.
Fold in oats, nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoons 2 inches apart on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: edna's brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together eggs, oil, vanilla and water.
In separate bowl, combine flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and pudding.
Mix together egg mixture, dry ingredients and walnuts.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour batter into pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let cool for 10 minutes. Cut into squares when still warm.
Sift powdered sugar over brownies.
Makes 25 to 30 pieces.

title: rice casserole
directions: Brown onion in margarine.
Put rice in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Add onion and 2 cans beef bouillon.
Stir.
Cover.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: breakfast sandwiches
directions: Crumble, cook and drain sausage.
Grease 9 x 13-inch dish. Butter both sides of bread slices.
Place 6 slices of buttered bread on bottom of baking dish.
Alternate sausage and cheese over the bread.
Cover with the remaining 6 slices of buttered bread. Mix the eggs, milk and seasoning in blender.
Pour over the "sandwiches" and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.
You can substitute your favorite meat and cheeses in this recipe.

title: banana cupcakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add beaten eggs.
Add sifted dry ingredients, alternating with milk, bananas and vanilla.
Fill greased muffin tins 1/2 full.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 minutes. This may be baked in two 8-inch layer pans at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach.
Drain and squeeze dry.
Mix all ingredients. Let stand several hours in refrigerator.
Serve in pumpernickel bread that has been cut out.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until crisp and tender. Drain. Saute onion in oleo until tender. Blend in soup, milk and cheese.
Heat thoroughly.
Pour over broccoli in casserole. Top with crumbs, if desired.
Heat at 350° until bubbly.

title: 3-2-1 pie crust
directions: Place flour in bowl; make well in center.
Add Crisco, water and salt, mixing all together.
Place in refrigerator a few hours or overnight.
Pinch desired amount.
Place on floured surface and work in just enough flour to roll.
Place in pie pan and flute edges or use as a 2 crust pie.
Bake at 425° until brown. Remaining dough may be refrigerated for a week or more.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and oil.
Add water and mix with hands.
Form into large ball.
Divide into 10 smaller ones.
Roll each flat with rolling pin and cook on very hot, ungreased griddle until lightly browned on each side.
Yields 10 tortillas.

title: chicken fantasia
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
On top of stove, saute ingredients, except chicken.
Pour over chicken which has been placed in oblong pan.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes.

title: tea syrup
directions: Pour water over tea.
Let cool for 15 minutes, then strain through tea strainer.
Add 1 2/3 cups sugar.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown meat and onion; drain.
Combine beans, tomatoes and soup with meat.
Line bottom of baking dish with Doritos.
Spread meat mixture on top.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions until tender.
Drain.
Mix with chicken soup and sour cream.

title: danish pastry apple bars
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Cut in shortening and margarine. Beat egg yolk in measuring cup, adding enough milk to make 2/3 cup liquid.
Mix well and stir into flour mixture.
Roll half the dough into a 17 x 12-inch rectangle.
Fit into and up sides of 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch baking pan.
Top with apples.
Combine sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle on top.
Roll out remaining dough and place over top.
Seal edges and cut slits in dough.
Beat egg white until frothy; brush on top of crust.
Bake in 375° oven for 50 minutes.
Combine powdered sugar and milk.
Drizzle on warm pastry.

title: orange salad
directions: Crush crackers and mix with butter.
Press on bottom of square dish.
Mix milk, oranges and frozen orange juice together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour on top of crust.
Chill.

title: macaroons
directions: Mix well.
Drop by spoonful 1-inch apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove at once.
Cool.

title: apple banana pecan bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening in large bowl.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add buttermilk, banana and apple and mix well.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to banana mixture and mix well.
Stir in pecans. Pour into greased miniature loaf pans and let stand for 20 minutes before baking.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until brown at 350°.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Chop cabbage, pepper and onion.
Mix other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over vegetables and cover tightly in covered container.
Chill.
Will keep for two weeks.

title: 5 pepper chicken fajitas(low-fat)
directions: Slice chicken into strips; place in large bowl and squeeze lime juice over chicken.
Add garlic, scallions, pepper, salt and cumin and toss.
Slice bell peppers into strips and set aside.
Wrap tortillas in clean cloth.
Place in oven at low setting while preparing fajita mixture.

title: nut cake
directions: Reserve
cup flour and sprinkle over nuts and fruit. Cream butter
and
sugar together.
Add beaten eggs, then add vanilla. Gradually
add flour.
Add nuts, fruit and remaining flour.
Bake in tube pan at 250° for 3 hours (until done) with pan of water under cake.

title: spam casserole
directions: In a 1 1/2 quart casserole, layer the ingredients except the milk.
Sprinkle salt and pepper between layers.
After all ingredients are layered, pour the can of evaporated milk over all, place pat of butter on top and bake at 350° for one hour (longer if potatoes are not tender) uncovered.
Ham may be used in place of Spam if desired.

title: quick fudge
directions: Heat all ingredients in saucepan over medium heat until smooth and creamy.
Add walnuts.
Pour mixture into wax paper-lined 9 x 9-inch square pan; let set.

title: honey mustard dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl, stirring well with a wire whisk.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Serve with salad greens, assorted sliced fresh fruits or as a dipping sauce for broiled, roasted or grilled poultry.

title: fluffy pink stuff
directions: Mix together and chill before serving.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place croutons in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; sprinkle with cheese.
Cook sausage in a skillet until meat is browned, stirring to crumble meat; drain.
Spoon sausage and mushrooms over cheese.
Combine eggs, 2 1/2 cups milk and mustard and mix well.
Pour over sausage.
Cover and refrigerate eight hours.
Combine mushroom soup and 1/2 cup milk.
Pour over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: sweet sour spareribs
directions: Beat together egg, yogurt, butter, maple syrup and vanilla. Add and whisk until just blended the pastry flour, baking powder, salt, baking soda and nutmeg.
Add nonfat milk to achieve desired consistency.
Use a nonstick griddle, if possible.
Serves two (with one leftover!).

title: russian tea
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Boil 5 minutes and remove cinnamon.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Combine boiling water and 3 tablespoons tea.
Steep 5 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.
Combine all when ready to serve.
Good hot punch.

title: pork chop-potato casserole
directions: In a pie pan, put breading.
Salt and pepper each chop and dredge in breading on both sides.
Brown well in skillet and set aside.
In a casserole sprayed with Pam, layer slices of raw potatoes, sliced onions and salt and pepper.
Use as many layers as you need, leaving room for browned chops as last layer.
Before adding chops, pour enough milk over potato/onion mixture, just even with last layer.
Add chops on top; cover with lid or foil. Bake in 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes and chops are tender.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash with 3 chicken bouillon cubes, then drain.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, oleo, milk, salt and cocoa together.
Boil 2 or 3 minutes.
Add peanut butter and oatmeal.
Spoon onto wax paper by the tablespoons full.
Let cool until hardened.

title: tangy vegetable salad
directions: Mix all together.
Pour marinade over all and let stand overnight.

title: monkey bread
directions: Put jelly and nuts in Bundt pan. Mix brown sugar and cinnamon. Dip biscuits in margarine, then brown sugar mix.
Place vertically in pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 25 minutes.

title: baked rice
directions: In baking dish, mix rice and consomme.
Saute onion and butter, then add to baking dish.
Bake in covered casserole dish for one hour at 375°.
Serve hot.
Delicious with meats.

title: pepperoni pizza dip
directions: In small bowl beat together first 5 ingredients.
Spread in a 9 or 10-inch quiche dish or pie pan.
Spread pizza sauce over top. Sprinkle with pepperoni, green onion and green pepper.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Bake 5 minutes more until cheese melts and it is heated through.
Serve with your preferred dippers.

title: fry pans
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add beaten eggs, sugar and chopped dates. Mix together and cook until dates are soft.
Add vanilla, Rice Krispies and nuts.
Mix.

title: filled patty shells
directions: In a medium bowl, combine the cheese, drained mushrooms and pimiento.
In small bowl, stir together the sour cream with salt, thyme and pepper.
Add the sour cream mixture to the turkey mixture.
Stir until well mixed.
Brush the dough with egg white. Place shells on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until golden brown.
Follow the package directions. Fill shells with chicken mixture.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve immediately.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate chips together in microwave. Blend in sugar, eggs and nuts.
Pour into two 9-inch pie shells or 1 deep dish pie shell.
Bake 40 minutes at 325°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes. Drain well. Combine other ingredients. Pour into well buttered casserole dish. Add topping (follows). Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms; chop fine.
In medium bowl, stir in cheese and onion.
Add all remaining ingredients except paprika.
Blend well.
Fill caps with mixture mounding slightly in center.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Arrange in shallow pan.
Bake in 350°
oven or zap in microwave.
Can be filled ahead but let reach room temperature (30 minutes)
before heating.

title: herbed french bread
directions: Cut loaf of bread lengthwise.
In a small bowl, mix all other ingredients and spread evenly on the two halves of bread.
Put bread back together, sandwich style and wrap in foil.
Heat on the back of a preheated grill for about 15 minutes.
Remove and cool for about 5 minutes before slicing.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Wash, clean and chop cauliflower, broccoli and onion.
Mix oil, mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; pour over vegetables.
Stir often.
Will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: mamma's red velvet celebration cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and flavoring well.
Make a paste of cocoa and food coloring and add to first mixture.
Add flour and buttermilk, alternating, starting and ending with flour. Mix baking soda and vinegar and add to batter, blend.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes in three 9-inch pans or two 10-inch round pans.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add eggs, one at a time, beating until no egg is seen.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Add jam and buttermilk. Pour into 3 oiled and floured layer cake pans.
Bake at 325° until tested done.
Frost with caramel frosting.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Boil cabbage leaves until tender.
Mix tomatoes, onions, sauce, paste, salt and pepper.
Remove 2 cups.
Mix ground beef, ground sausage and rice into sauce.
Fill cabbage leaf with meat mixture; roll cabbage around meat.
Place in Dutch oven.
Pour 2 cups sauce mix over cabbage rolls.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dedication day punch
directions: Combine mint, sugar and boiling water and simmer for 10 minutes.
Chill everything.
Mix all together to serve, adding ginger ale and sparkling water at the last minute.
Serves 50.

title: blender coconut pie
directions: Put in blender all at once on high speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into well-greased and floured 10-inch pie pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°, or until golden brown on top.
Let cool completely before cutting.

title: sourdough pizza
directions: Combine and roll out the dough.
Dash some oil over the top. Fix and bake, as you would for pizza, at 425° for 5 minutes.

title: tuna-noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to directions.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a greased 3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs or crushed potato chips. Bake in 350° oven 30 to 35 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: mother williams' "famous in fairfax" chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together in any order.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Makes 3 dozen small or 2 dozen large cookies.

title: cheese soup
directions: Dice potatoes, carrots, onion and celery.
Add salt, pepper, seasoned salt, beef bouillon cubes and water.
Boil until tender. Then add milk and Velveeta cheese.
Cook slow.
If too juicy, add small amount of cornstarch.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: In a skillet, cook sausage until browned; drain off excess fat. Separate crescent dough into triangles.
Place in a pan, sprayed lightly with no-stick spray, with points toward the center (use 12-inch pizza pan).
Press over bottom and up sides to form a crust; seal perforations.
Spoon sausage over crust.
Sprinkle with potatoes.
Top with Cheddar cheese.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Cut margarine into flour until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add oleo or shortening and milk and stir until dough clings together.
Knead dough, 10 to 12 strokes on lightly floured surface.
Roll out to a 12 to 16-inch rectangle.
Sprinkle sausage evenly on top dough.
Roll up, jelly roll style, starting from long side.

title: aunt mary's potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place into glass casserole dish.
Bake at 350°
for 1/2 hour or until cheese melts.
Can microwave instead of baking.
Microwave on High until cheese melts and casserole is hot, about 5 to 7 minutes.

title: dilly bread
directions: Warm cottage cheese over low fire.
Combine all ingredients, except yeast mixture.
Add yeast and 5 cups flour; mix well.
Let rise in greased bowl until double (1 hour).
Use regular bread pans or shape into 2 long rolls on cookie sheet.
Bake immediately at 350° for 35 minutes or let rise until lighter.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in large freezer.
Freeze as you would any homemade ice cream. This recipe is for a large freezer. For small freezer, cut recipe in half.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 3-inch baking dish coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Pour melted margarine over the top.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until browned.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Drain.
Place in buttered pan (10 x 12-inch is best).
Cook ground beef, sausage, onion and garlic until meat is done.
Drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, catsup, Worcestershire, basil and salt.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Cover spaghetti with cheese; cover with meat sauce.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: our best bran muffins
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Set aside. In large mixing bowl, combine All-Bran cereal and milk.
Let stand about 3 minutes or until cereal softens.
Add egg and oil; mix well.
Add flour mixture, stirring only until combined.
Portion batter evenly into 12 lightly greased 2 1/2-inch muffin pan cups. Bake in 400° oven about 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm.
Yield:
12 muffins.
Dietary Fiber:
4 g per muffin.

title: stress relief
directions: Mix all together. Stir well and serve on rocks. Garnish with cherries.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: light and zesty chicken 'n rice
directions: Place chicken breasts in 8 x 12-inch baking dish; top with salad dressing.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes.
Place rice, vegetables and 1/2 can French fried onions around and under chicken.
Combine bouillon and Italian seasoning; pour over rice and vegetables.
Bake, uncovered, 25 minutes.
Top with remaining onions; bake 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: To make crust, mix the Bisquick and sugar.
Add the egg; mix thoroughly until crumbly.
Use berries for 1 large pie.
Mix berries with 3/4 cup sugar, flour and a dash of cinnamon.
Heat until thickened; pour into a 9-inch pie dish.
Sprinkle crumbly mixture over top.
Dot with butter; bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: nana's corn pudding
directions: Pour creamed corn into glass casserole dish greased with butter.
Add eggs and beat one at a time into corn.
Add sugar and mix well with fork until well blended.
Add milk and beat in flour with fork.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until pudding is brown and bubbly.
Let set for about 10 minutes.

title: buckshots
directions: Mix peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Melt wax and chocolate over low heat in a double boiler.
Roll peanut butter mixture into balls.
Dip balls in melted chocolate.
Let cool on wax paper.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate.
Brown beef and onion. Drain.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread in pie plate.
Beat milk, Bisquick and eggs until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into plate.
Bake for 25 minutes. Top with tomatoes and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 5 to 8 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: stuffing balls
directions: Cook onion and celery in butter 5 minutes.
Add beaten eggs, 1/2 can soup and bread cubes to onion mixture.
Shape into balls. Place in a greased glass dish.
Mix other 1/2 can soup with 1 can water.
Pour over balls.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 300°. Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: mexican fiesta ole
directions: Cook noodles 3 minutes as package directs with soup base. Drain and rinse in cold water. Sprinkle cheese, olives and onion over noodles. Spoon on desired amount of salsa. Toss just before serving.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Place shortening, sugars, egg, water and vanilla in mixing bowl; beat thoroughly.
Sift together flour, salt and soda; add to shortening mixture and mix well.
Blend in oats, chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
